rah Brightman}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Timeless (Sarah Brightman Album)}}\n[[Category:1997 albums]]\n[[Category:Sarah Brightman albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Frank Peterson]]\n[[Category:East West Records albums]]\n\n\n{{1990s-pop-album-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=October 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Timeless\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Sarah Brightman]]\n| cover      = Sarah Brightman - Timeless.jpg\n| alt        =\n| caption    = \n| released   = 2 June 1997 (UK)<br />23 September 1997 (US)\n| recorded   = November 1996 - March 1997\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Crossover (music)|Classical Crossover]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=52|s=36}}\n| label      = [[East West Records]]\n| producer   = [[Frank Peterson]]\n| prev_title = [[Fly (Sarah Brightman album)|Fly]]\n| prev_year  = 1995\n| next_title = [[The Andrew Lloyd Webber Collection]]\n| next_year  = 1997\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n|rev1 = [[Allmusic]]\n|rev1score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>[{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r332098|pure_url=yes}} Allmusic review]</ref>\n}}<!-- Automatically generated by DASHBot-->\n'''''Timeless''''', known as '''''Time to Say Goodbye''''' in the US and Canada, is the fifth album by classical crossover [[soprano]] [[Sarah Brightman]] & the [[London Symphony Orchestra]]. The album went gold or platinum in 21 countries, selling over 1.4 million copies in the US alone,<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite magazine|url=http://www.sarah-brightman.com/BillboardJan2008/|title=Genre-Bending Brightman seeks crossover success with Symphony|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=22 July 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090823035128/http://www.sarah-brightman.com/BillboardJan2008/|archivedate=23 August 2009|df=dmy-all}}</ref> and topped the Billboard Classical Crossover chart in the US for 35 weeks. [[EMI]]'s [[Super Audio CD|SACD]] [[5.1]] release of the album is also entitle