{"title_page": "Chowder (TV series)", "text_new": "{{short description|American animated television series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2013}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Chowder\n| image                    = Chowder logo.png\n| genre                    = {{unbulleted list|[[Animation]]|[[Adventure film|Adventure]]|[[Surreal comedy]]<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/chowder | title=Chowder | access-date=April 9, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151003020806/http://www.metacritic.com/tv/chowder | archive-date=October 3, 2015 | url-status=live }}</ref>|[[Slapstick]]}}\n| creator                  = [[C. H. Greenblatt]]\n| writer                   = <!--Do not use when there are more than 5 writers. See Template:Infobox television instructions-->\n| director                 = {{unbulleted list|Eddy Houchins <small>(also supervising director)</small>|Kris Sherwood|Majella Milne <small>(2008\u201310)</small>|[[Mike Milo]] <small>(2008\u201310)</small>|Juli Hashiguchi <small>(2007\u201308)</small>|Shaun Cashman <small>(2007\u201308)</small>}}\n| creative_director        = [[William Reiss]]\n| voices                   = {{unbulleted list|[[Nicky Jones (actor)|Nicky Jones]]|[[Dwight Schultz]]|[[Kevin Michael Richardson]]|[[John DiMaggio]]|[[Tara Strong]]|C. H. Greenblatt|[[Dana Snyder]]|[[Liliana Mumy]]|[[Mindy Sterling]]|[[Diedrich Bader]]}}\n| theme_music_composer     = C.H. Greenblatt, Dan Boer & Zac Pike\n| composer                 = Dan Boer & Zac Pike\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 3\n| num_episodes             = 49 (93 segments)\n| list_episodes            = List of Chowder episodes\n| executive_producer       = C. H. Greenblatt\n| producer                 = Louis J. Cuck\n| runtime                  = 22 minutes\n| company                  = [[Cartoon Network Studios]]<br>[[Screen Novelties]] <small>(stopmotion segments)</small><br>[[Hong Ying Animation|Hong Ying Animation Entertainment]] <small>(animation services)</small>\n| distributor              = [[Warner Bros. Television Distribution]]\n| network                  = [[Cartoon Network]]\n| picture_format           = [[1080i]] ([[16:9]] [[HDTV]])\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2007|11|2}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|2010|8|7}}\n| website                  = \n| image_size               = 250\n}}\n\n'''''Chowder''''' is an American [[animated television series]] created by [[C. H. Greenblatt]] for [[Cartoon Network]].<ref>{{cite book |last1=Perlmutter |first1=David |title=The Encyclopedia of American Animated Television Shows |date=2018 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1538103739 |pages=123\u2013125 }}</ref>\n\n''Chowder'' premiered on November 2, 2007, and ran for three seasons with 49 total episodes. It received mostly positive reviews, as well as one [[Primetime Emmy Award]] win, six [[Annie Award]] nominations, and two additional Emmy Award nominations during its run. The series finale, \"Chowder Grows Up\", aired on August 7, 2010.\n\n==Plot==\nThe series follows an aspiring young chef apprentice named Chowder and his day-to-day adventures in Chef Mung Daal's [[catering]] company. Although he means well, Chowder often finds himself in predicaments due to his [[Gourmand|perpetual appetite]] and his nature as a [[wikt:scatterbrain|scatterbrain]]. It is animated with both [[traditional animation]] as well as short [[stop motion]] and [[puppet]] sequences that are inter-cut into episodes and the end credits. Stop motion sequences are produced by [[Screen Novelties]].\n\n==Characters==\n{{fanpov|section|date=December 2019}}\nEach character is named after a type of food or dish.\n\n===Main===\n*'''Chowder''' (voiced by [[Nicky Jones (actor)|Nicky Jones]]): A 12-year-old chubby purple {{not a typo|[[cat]]/[[bear]]/[[rabbit]]}}<ref name=CNUKfacts>{{cite web|title=Character Facts of the Week: Chowder|url=http://www.cartoonnetwork.co.uk/blogs/character-facts-of-the-week-chowder|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140910053503/http://www.cartoonnetwork.co.uk/blogs/character-facts-of-the-week-chowder|archivedate=September 10, 2014|date=March 20, 2012|quote=Chowder is a mix between a cat, bear, and rabbit.}}</ref> hybrid who serves as an apprentice under the chef [[Mung Daal]], Chowder lives with Mung Daal and his wife, Truffles, in a room at the top of the catering business. Chowder wants to become a great chef, but he is very impulsive and scatterbrained and often gives in to his urges. He is always hungry and eats anything, even a customer's order. Chowder can also regurgitate objects, and he is used as a storage container by the other characters. According to Greenblatt, he is a composite of a cat, a bear and a rabbit, and his species was verified in at least one episode.<ref>{{cite episode|title=The Puckerberry Overlords|series=Chowder|airdate=January 18, 2008}}</ref> C. H. Greenblatt voiced his adult self in the last episode. In the final episode, \u201cChowder Grows Up\u201d Chowder takes over the Catering Company, has his own apprentice and marries Panini. He is also a father to 50 babies.\n*'''Mung Daal''' (voiced by [[Dwight Schultz]]): The elderly chef who runs the catering company at which Chowder works.<ref name=\"cn-bio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/tv_shows/chowder/index.html|title=Chowder|publisher=Cartoon Network|accessdate=April 26, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130429100538/http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/tv_shows/chowder/index.html|archive-date=April 29, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> Although his exact age has not been stated, he has mentioned that he has cooked for at least 386 years,<ref name=\"certifrycation\">{{cite episode|title=Certifrycation Class|series=Chowder|airdate=November 16, 2007}}</ref> and he celebrated 450 years of marriage to Truffles (see below).<ref name=\"mung\">{{cite episode|title=Mung on the Rocks|series=Chowder|airdate=March 6, 2008}}</ref> He is a light on blue-colored humanoid and is named after the [[Indian cuisine|Indian dish]] [[Mung bean|mung]] [[dal|daal]], that Greenblatt had originally planned to give Mung an [[Indian accent]], but later decided against it.<ref name=\"food\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/10/real-world-food-counterparts.html|title=Real World Food Counterparts|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=October 12, 2008|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=January 31, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090201224541/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/10/real-world-food-counterparts.html|archive-date=February 1, 2009|url-status=live}}</ref> In the final episode, Mung is now retired with Truffles, leaving the catering company to Chowder.\n*'''Shnitzel''' (voiced by [[Kevin Michael Richardson]] in \"The Froggy Apple Crumple Thumpkin\", and [[John DiMaggio]] afterward): A 38-year-old taupe rock monster and professional chef who works at Mung Daal's Catering Company. His vocabulary consists almost entirely of \"radda\", while it's translated as \"okay\", although he sometimes says other simple words.<ref name=\"radda\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/01/shnitzel-faq.html|title=Shnitzel FAQ|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=January 1, 2008|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=April 7, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080105142731/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/01/shnitzel-faq.html|archive-date=January 5, 2008|url-status=live}}</ref> He talks in the episode \"The Trouble with Truffles\" because he finally gets calm enough. Shnitzel is the \"[[straight man]]\" to the other more excitable characters and is frequently agitated. He gets stuck with menial labor or cleanup duty, as well as the heavy lifting because he is extremely strong. Although usually angered by Chowder's antics, Shnitzel really has a soft spot for Chowder, as he cries when it was thought that Chowder has vanished forever.<ref name=\"radda\"/><ref name=\"chowder-prem\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/10/just-two-weeks-until-chowder-premiere.html|title=Just Two Weeks Until Chowder Premiere|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=July 18, 2007|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=November 9, 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071118022353/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/10/just-two-weeks-until-chowder-premiere.html|archive-date=November 18, 2007|url-status=live}}</ref> Kevin Michael Richardson voiced Shnitzel for the debut episode \"The Froggy Apple Crumple Thumpkin\" and was replaced at the last moment by DiMaggio due to Richardson being busy with other projects at the time.<ref name=\"radda\"/> In the final episode, Schnitzel has left the catering company and live a happy life with his wife, Endive.\n*'''Truffles Daal''' (voiced by [[Tara Strong]]): A [[mushroom]] [[pixie]]/[[fairy]] and Mung Daal's wife who handles the business side of Mung's catering business. She is an extreme [[Four Temperaments#choleric|choleric]]. Greenblatt said that he based Truffles on his mother.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/11/mahjongg-night.html|title=Mahjongg Night|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|work=Nerd Armada|date=November 28, 2007|accessdate=September 14, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110823031150/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/11/mahjongg-night.html|archive-date=August 23, 2011|url-status=live}}</ref> Greenblatt said that he initially found difficulty in working on any story with Truffles since the character could be \"so abrasive\" that the ''Chowder'' staff had to be \"a little more sensitive about finding her softer side.\" Greenblatt said that the staff eventually decided that \"a little Truffles goes a long way.\" Therefore, she would appear occasionally in ''Chowder'' in a manner similar to how [[Oscar the Grouch]] appears on ''[[Sesame Street]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bakertoons.blogspot.com/2009/08/exit-interview-with-ch-greenblatt.html|title=Exit interview with C.H. Greenblatt|first=Charles|last=Brubaker|date=August 31, 2009|work=Baking the Baker|accessdate=September 15, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708024534/http://bakertoons.blogspot.com/2009/08/exit-interview-with-ch-greenblatt.html|archive-date=July 8, 2011|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2009/08/were-off.html|title=We're Off!|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=August 31, 2009|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=September 15, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110923091741/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2009/08/were-off.html|archive-date=September 23, 2011|url-status=live}}</ref> In the final episode, Truffles retired along with Mung, possibly giving her Job to Panini.<!--Link 1 is the interview, link 2 is to confirm that he did the interview-->\n*'''Kimchi''' (voiced by C. H. Greenblatt): Chowder's pet, who lives in a cage next to his bed. Kimchi is an anthropomorphic flatus (due to the unpleasant odor of [[kimchi]]). He likes things with odors unpleasant for the other characters, and he \"talks\" by making flatulent sounds. Kimchi was first seen in the episode \"The Froggy Apple Crumple Thumpkin\". Kimchi is usually shown with a blank personality but in \"Stinky Love\" it is shown that he has an opinion.<ref name=\"toonzone\"/> What happens to Kimchi in the final episode is unknown, but it\u2019s possible that he still lives with Chowder.\n*'''Gazpacho''' (voiced by [[Dana Snyder]]): A [[woolly mammoth]] storekeeper who sells strange [[produce]] and ingredients at the farmer's market. He does his best to offer advice to Chowder when needed. He lives with his overbearing mother, who never appears on screen, but is present at the end of episode \"Gazpacho!\". In \"The Spookiest House in Marzipan\" it is hinted at that Gazpacho has no mother, and that he actually suffers with [[dissociative identity disorder]], but creator Greenblatt says this was merely to \"pay homage to ''[[Psycho (1960 film)|Psycho]]''\". Gazpacho shows no interest in moving out and improving his own life. Gazpacho's worst enemies are [[ninja]]s. Greenblatt named him after the cold soup [[gazpacho]]; Greenblatt said that he did not know why, but the name suited the character immediately.<ref name=\"food\"/> In the final episode, Gazpacho closed the stand, and became a nomad. He later pursued his dream and open a Comedy Night Club.\n*'''Panini''' (voiced by [[Liliana Mumy]]): A 12-year-old pink [[cabbit]] who has a crush on Chowder and reminds him at every opportunity. Chowder does not return the feelings and responds with \"I'm not your boyfriend!\" whenever she greets him. Panini is an apprentice to Ms. Endive, and is also possessive of Chowder. Panini gets jealous when she sees Chowder with another girl, in which Chowder really does to avoid her. Her original character concept had her [[bullying|bully]] Chowder in a manner described by Greenblatt as similar to [[Angelica Pickles]] from ''[[Rugrats]]''.<ref name=\"OldPanEn\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2009/06/early-endive-panini-designs.html|title=Early Endive & Panini Designs|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=June 15, 2009|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=June 22, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090714054958/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2009/06/early-endive-panini-designs.html|archive-date=July 14, 2009|url-status=live}}</ref> Greenblatt removed the pointy ears since he felt this did not fit in with the rounded shapes in ''Chowder''. Greenblatt did not like characters similar to Angelica and believed that he needed to make Panini \"cuter and sweeter\".<ref name=\"OldPanEn\"/> Greenblatt said that the details of Panini formed when the creator decided that Panini had a crush on Chowder; since Chowder is not old enough to fall in love with females, according to Greenblatt this aspect would frustrate Chowder \"in a more fun way\".<ref name=\"OldPanEn\"/> In the last episode, it is shown that Chowder finally returned Panini's feelings and accepted her because he realizes that he made Panini's life miserable and they are married with many kids and was voiced by [[Grey DeLisle]]. Panini's name literally means \"sandwiches\" in Italian, while her former name, Borlotti, is a type of beans. In the final episode Panini married Chowder, and is currently a mother of 50, she then promised Chowder to stop having more. It\u2019s also likely that she took over Truffles old job.\n*'''Gorgonzola''' (voiced by Will Shadley): A young green [[rat]] apprentice candle holder with an unlikeable attitude. He shows jealousy over Chowder which is, in fact Chowder having a better job than him.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/07/gorgonzola.html|title=Gorgonzola|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=July 18, 2007|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=November 9, 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071107091545/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/07/gorgonzola.html|archive-date=November 7, 2007|url-status=live}}</ref> He will occasionally use Chowder, and if forced, will partner with him in games. Since [[blue cheese]] was one of the few foods Greenblatt disliked, he decided to use the name \"[[Gorgonzola (cheese)|gorgonzola]]\" for a character who did not get along with Chowder. Gorgonzola resembles a green [[opossum]] or a green [[rat]]. He wears tattered brown clothes and no shoes, and has a partially melted candle on his head (for traditional reasons). He is desperate to get cash, and will do almost anything to get it. Gorgonzola also loves to play Sniffleball, as seen in the episode ''Sniffleball''. Despite his unpleasant and boastful attitude to Chowder, Chowder sees him as a close friend, which irritates him even more. Gorgonzola is an apprentice to Stilton, who is a candle holder, hence why both characters have burning candles on their heads.<ref name=\"food\"/> In the final episode, Gorgonzola runs a very successful company, most likely involving candle holding.\n*'''Ms. Endive''' (voiced by [[Mindy Sterling]]): An [[obesity|obese]], intelligent, and somewhat snobbish 46-year-old female chef who teaches cooking to Panini with strict discipline. She is usually depicted as gargantuan in size. This is shown in the episode \"The Apprentice Games\" where Mung Daal and Chowder enter the games by riding on Endive's posterior. She regularly berates Mung Daal, whom she considers a rival. In the episode \"Chowder's Girlfriend\", it is revealed she despises boys and boyfriends because her fianc\u00e9 did not show up on their wedding day. Ms. Endive is first seen in the second episode with Panini, \"Chowder's Girlfriend\". The creator describes her as [[Martha Stewart]] with [[Oompa-Loompa]] colors.<ref name=\"endive\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/04/endive.html|title=Ms. Endive|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=April 19, 2007|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=November 9, 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071118022158/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/04/endive.html|archive-date=November 18, 2007|url-status=live}}</ref> Greenblatt chose to name her after the [[endive]] since endive is bitter and Belgian endive is fancy; hence the character is bitter and fancy.<ref name=\"food\"/> Endive's character stayed constant throughout the initial development. The long nose, which changed from a rectangular shape to a triangle shape for the final version, represents how Endive looks down at other characters. It was revealed in later episodes that Ms. Endive is in love with Shnitzel. Greenblatt said that he felt that her evolution throughout the series was fun to observe, especially when William Reiss wrote plots involving Endive.<ref name=\"OldPanEn\"/> In the final episode, Endive is living a happy life with her Husband, Schnitzel.\n\n===Recurring===\n*'''Kiwi''' (voiced by C. H. Greenblatt) is a [[photorealistic]] pink creature who always gives advice to Chowder and his friends and occasionally provides interstitial narrations, especially at times where particularly corny humor is displayed. His name is revealed (for the first and only time ever in the show's run) in the episode \"Brain Grub\", where it is known that after Chowder alters the animated universe, Kiwi is reduced to selling used cars.\n*'''Ceviche''' (voiced by Elan Garfias): A young yellow (and somewhat androgynous) [[goat]] apprentice to Pat\u00e9 and Panini's best friend, Ceviche was introduced in the episode \"The Apprentice Games\". He practices aerobic-style dancing and is very charitable and kind to others. Because of his admirable attitude and amazing talents (as well as good looks, as it was shown on one episode that he has a well-sculpted body) he is well-liked.  He is good friends with Panini and will make unwanted advances upon her, which are either refused or unnoticed. Ceviche is also a close friend to Chowder. He has a crush on Panini.  He speaks in a [[wikt:monotone|monotonous]] voice and serves as [[deadpan]] humor for the show.\n*'''Pat\u00e9''' (voiced by John DiMaggio): A tall, well-sculpted [[humanoid]] ballet dance master and operatic singer with a deep voice, grass-green hair, a small black hat, and exaggerated lips who is the mentor of Ceviche. Pat\u00e9 was introduced briefly on the second episode of the first show ''Chowder's Girlfriend'' (Episode #1b), where he sings \"I'm Not Your Boyfriend\" on stage to Panini (on behalf of Chowder) in front of an audience. His name, however, was revealed for the first time on ''The Apprentice Games'' (Episode 20), where he appeared as a judge for the Marzipan City Apprentice Games. In that same episode, it was also revealed that he lives in another dimension, as was shown by the portal through which he and Ceviche made their entrance and exit.\n*'''Chestnut''' (originally voiced by [[Tone L\u014dc]], then [[John DiMaggio]]): Like the food, Chestnut is small and tough. He is a tiny, [[blue]] horned [[devil]]-like creature with a deep, gravelly voice and, to many character's surprise, is physically very strong.  Because of his size, he uses everyday objects as other things (e.g. using a briefcase for a hydrofoil, or a hat as a vacation home). He sings small songs to himself, usually consisting of his catchphrase of \"Dinka-loo, dinka-lee.\" He is teacher of the BLTs, a parody of the [[SAT]]s. He always refers to himself in the [[Grammatical person|third person]] when speaking.\n*'''Reuben''' (voiced by [[Paul Reubens]]): A pig who is a [[confidence trick|conman]] and steals from others.\n*'''Mr. Fugu''' (voiced by [[Bob Joles]]): A sentient floating balloon who is said to be Mung's most frequent customer. He is proven to be more greedy than Chowder and never shares any food with him. He is often seen with his valet, Foie Gras, a [[Maneki-neko]] (meows provided by [[George Takei]]) holding Mr. Fugu's string as he cannot control his flotation.\n*'''Sgt. Hoagie''' (voiced by [[Diedrich Bader]]): He is a [[dog]] who is a police officer in Marzipan City. In ''The Hot Date'', he was going out on a date after several years and asked the other cops for advice.\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Main|List of Chowder episodes}}\n{{:List of Chowder episodes}}\nA total of 49 episodes were aired in the series. Season 1, which consists of 20 episodes, started on November 2, 2007, with the series premiere, entitled \"The Froggy Apple Crumble Thumpkin/Chowder's Girlfriend\". Season 1 ended on July 24, 2008, with the special \"The Apprentice Games\". Season 2 also contains 20 episodes, debuting on October 1, 2008, with \"The Arborians/The Garage Sale\", and ending with \"A Faire to Remember/Tofu-Town Showdown\", broadcasting on September 29, 2009, and October 6, 2009, respectively. Season 3 consists of only 9 episodes, premiering October 12, 2009, with \"The Blast Raz\", and ending with the series finale, entitled \"Chowder Grows Up\", which aired on August 7, 2010.\n\n==Development==\n[[File:ChowderPuppets.jpg|thumb|The puppet versions of the characters Chowder (a Hand-Rod puppet) and Mung Daal]]\nDuring his time working on Nickelodeon's ''[[SpongeBob SquarePants]]'', Greenblatt had been sketching various characters for his own animation series concept.<ref name=\"toonzone\"/> Greenblatt originally based the premise on the idea of the sorcerer's apprentice style of story, such as ''[[The Sword in the Stone (1963 film)|The Sword in the Stone]]''. The plot devices were modified so that the story revolves around a master chef who teaches his young apprentice how to cook. Chowder himself was developed with no specific species in mind, but rather with the intentions of invoking the image of a child's soft squeeze toy.<ref name=\"kitty-interview\"/> Some of the inspiration comes from [[Dr. Seuss]], with other inspiration from [[Saturday morning cartoon]]s.<ref name=\"kitty-interview\"/><ref name=\"armada\">{{cite web |url=http://forum.newsarama.com/showthread.php?t=139420 |title=Meet the Master Chef&nbsp;\u2013 C.H. Greenblatt |date=December 12, 2007 |first=Steve |last=Fritz |publisher=Animated Shorts |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090122105026/http://forum.newsarama.com/showthread.php?t=139420 |archivedate=January 22, 2009 |accessdate=April 26, 2013 |url-status=dead |df=mdy }}</ref>\n\nGreenblatt pitched the concept to Cartoon Network in the mid-2000s, when he began working as a writer and storyboard artist for ''[[The Grim Adventures of Billy & Mandy]]'', and two years later the series was approved with another year for production before the pilot episode aired. Greenblatt estimates he spent about seven years working on ''Chowder'' before the show made it to air in 2007.<ref name=\"toonzone\"/>\n\n==Production and format==\nEpisodes are produced in seasons which consist of twenty 24-minute episodes. Each episode is produced with a 30-second puppet sequence that is meant to run over the ending credits.<ref name=\"season2\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/06/let-new-chowders-begin.html|title=Let the New Chowders Begin!!|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=June 3, 2008|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=June 4, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708054506/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/06/let-new-chowders-begin.html|archive-date=July 8, 2011|url-status=live}}</ref> Episodes can be purchased from the [[iTunes Store]] in the United States which are delivered with the sequences as are episodes which are available on Cartoon Network's VOD website also within the United States.<ref name=\"kitty-interview\"/><ref name=\"puppets\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/02/more-puppets.html|title=More Puppets|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=February 7, 2008|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=March 4, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101203005913/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/02/more-puppets.html|archive-date=December 3, 2010|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOne of the unusual design features of the show is the patterns used on the clothing or players. The patterns are developed as a full-screen image and then sent to the production house, where the characters are modified to fill the patterns in over the character clothing.<ref name=\"toonzone\">{{cite web|url=http://www.toonzone.net/2007/10/toon-zone-interviews-c-h-greenblatt-on-crafting-chowder/|title=Toon Zone Interviews C.H. Greenblatt on Crafting \"Chowder\"|first=Ed|last=Liu|date=October 30, 2007|publisher=Toon Zone|accessdate=March 4, 2008|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130703111526/http://www.toonzone.net/2007/10/toon-zone-interviews-c-h-greenblatt-on-crafting-chowder/|archive-date=July 3, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"kitty-interview\">{{cite web|url=http://kittysneezes.com/2008/02/08/interview-ch-greenblatt-207/|title=Interview: C.H. Greenblatt|first=Joe|last=Meyer|date=February 8, 2008|work=KittySneezes.com|accessdate=March 4, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130116025642/http://kittysneezes.com/2008/02/08/interview-ch-greenblatt-207/|archive-date=January 16, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"patterns\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/01/chowder-patterns.html|title=Chowder Patterns|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=January 29, 2008|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=March 4, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080516031555/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/01/chowder-patterns.html|archive-date=May 16, 2008|url-status=live}}</ref> Using this technique, when a character moves, their patterns do not follow, but display as a \"static\" background. A similar technique was used in the ''[[Monkey Island (series)|Monkey Island]]'' video game series (particularly for the Stan), the Nickelodeon series [[The Off-Beats]], and the [[Mr. Bean (animated TV series)|''Mr. Bean'' animated series]].<ref name=\"armada\"/>\n\nThe show is also known for the very wide variety of media used in various episodes. These include animation using watercolors and ink-and-paint in addition to the cartoon's classic pattern style. It also uses stop motion animation with real food, action figures and clay; live-action scenes with the voice actors of the show and puppets; both marionette and hand-controlled. This was also sometimes used in ''[[Courage the Cowardly Dog]]''. It boasts one of the most diverse varieties of mediums used in any single series.\n\n==Cancellation==\n''Chowder'' was cancelled by Cartoon Network in August 2009, as the network felt the show did not fit its new demographic of older boys, favoring shows such as the live-action ''[[Destroy, Build, Destroy]]'' instead.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://chgreenblatt.tumblr.com/post/152842491532/you-mentioned-in-an-ask-that-you-went-through-the | title=Tumblr | access-date=November 15, 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161116103638/http://chgreenblatt.tumblr.com/post/152842491532/you-mentioned-in-an-ask-that-you-went-through-the | archive-date=November 16, 2016 | url-status=live }}</ref> On his blog, C.H. Greenblatt expressed relief about having his schedule freed up by the cancellation, saying: \"I didn't really think there'd be this many upsides to having a show officially cancelled by a network, but I'm feeling happier than I've been in a long time. Since we've only got post-production, my schedule finally eases up. I haven't had a break like this in a long, long time... ''Chowder'' has opened up a lot of awesome possibilities for me, and creatively I'm feeling more inspired than ever.\"<ref name=\"blogspot\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2009/08/hot-girl.html|title=The Hot Girl|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=August 13, 2009|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=January 2, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120311091937/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2009/08/hot-girl.html|archive-date=March 11, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Home media==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n|+''Chowder'' home video releases\n! colspan=3 rowspan=2|Season !! rowspan=2|Episodes !! rowspan=2|Volume !! colspan=2|Release dates !! rowspan=2|Episode(s) include\n|-\n! {{USA}} !! {{THA}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.toonzone.net/forums/threads/dvd-releases-from-mvd-in-thailand.5527321 |title=DVD releases from MVD in Thailand |access-date=April 24, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160424214131/http://www.toonzone.net/forums/threads/dvd-releases-from-mvd-in-thailand.5527321/ |archive-date=April 24, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=5 style=\"background:#1E5994\"| || rowspan=5|[[List of Chowder episodes#Season 1 (2007\u201308)|1]]\n| rowspan=5|2007\u201308 || rowspan=5|20 || rowspan=2|1 || November 4, 2008<ref>{{cite web|asin=B001DSNFQ4|title=Chowder, Vol. 1 (2008)}}</ref> || rowspan=2|November 10, 2010 || rowspan=2|\"The Froggy Apple Crumple Thumpkin\" / \"Chowder's Girlfriend\" \u2022 \"Grubble Gum\" \u2013 \"The Sing Beans\" \u2022 \"Mahjongg Night\" \u2013 \"The Flibber-Flabber Diet\"\n|-\n| May 6, 2014\n|-\n| 2 || March 3, 2009<ref>{{cite web|asin=B001MEJYBY|title=Chowder, Vol. 2 (2009)}}</ref> || December 15, 2010 || \"Burple Nurples\" / \"Shnitzel Makes a Deposit\" \u2022 \"The Wrong Address\" / \"The Wrong Customer\" \u2022 \"Gazpacho Stands Up\" \u2013 \"Mung on the Rocks\"\n|-\n| 3 || {{n/a}} || January 19, 2010 || \"The Heavy Sleeper\" \u2013 \"The Rat Sandwich\"\n|-\n| 4 || {{n/a}} || February 15, 2011 || \"Chowder Loses His Hat\" \u2013 \"The Apprentice Games\"\n|-\n! rowspan=5 style=\"background:#5C1F99\"| || rowspan=5|[[List of Chowder episodes#Season 2 (2008\u201309)|2]]\n| rowspan=5|2008\u201309 || rowspan=5|20 || 5 || {{n/a}} || March 15, 2011 || \"The Arborians\" \u2013 \"The Catch Phrase\"\n|-\n| 6 || {{n/a}} || April 8, 2011 || \"The Hot Date\" \u2013 \"The Deadly Maze\" \u2022 \"The B.L.T.'s\" \u2013 \"The Dinner Theater\"\n|-\n| 7 || {{n/a}} || May 10, 2011 || \"Kid Shnitzel\" / \"Gazpacho Fights Back\" \u2022 \"Big Ball\" \u2013 \"The Blackout\"\n|-\n| 8 || {{n/a}} || June 14, 2011 || \"The Dice Cycle\" \u2013 \"The Grape Worm\"\n|-\n| rowspan=2|9 || rowspan=2 style=\"background:#ececec;color:#2d2d2d\"|<small>N/A</small> || rowspan=2|July 26, 2011 || rowspan=2| \"A Faire to Remember\" \u2013 \"The Birthday Suits\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 style=\"background:#991F5C\"| || rowspan=2|[[List of Chowder episodes#Season 3 (2009\u201310)|3]]\n| rowspan=2|2009\u201310 || rowspan=2|9\n|-\n| 10 || {{n/a}} || August 24, 2011 || \"The Heist\" \u2013 \"Chowder Grows Up\"\n|}\nThe entire series has been released in ten [[DVD region code#3|Region 3]] [[pan and scan|fullscreen]] DVD volumes in Thailand from MVD Company Limited.\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critics===\nChowder received mostly positive reviews. Barry Garron of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' thought that the show would appeal to children and adults alike, using exotic artwork, unusual settings, and a zany cast of characters.<ref name=\"hollywood\">{{cite journal|url=http://208.115.47.50/cartoonnetwork/article_images/NXE913120_1_H.pdf |title=Chowder |first=Barry |last=Garron |date=November 2, 2007 |page=47 |journal=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5oDZGw1pO?url=http://208.115.47.50/cartoonnetwork/article_images/NXE913120_1_H.pdf |archivedate=March 14, 2010 |accessdate=April 26, 2013 |url-status=dead |df=mdy }}</ref> On Toon Zone, Ed Liu expands on the animation and crazy antics of the characters, pointing that \"the humor is kid-friendly without being juvenile\" and praising it for getting laughs, \"without resorting to an excess of toilet humor, even if Chowder's pet happens to be a sentient fart cloud.\"<ref name=\"toonzone-review\">{{cite web|url=http://www.toonzone.net/2007/11/chowder-is-satisfying-comfort-food/|title=\"Chowder\" is Satisfying Comfort Food|first=Ed|last=Liu|date=November 2, 2007|publisher=Toon Zone|accessdate=February 18, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131025005642/http://www.toonzone.net/2007/11/chowder-is-satisfying-comfort-food/|archive-date=October 25, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> Aaron H. Bynum on ''Animation Insider'' wrote, \"Featuring brightly colored environments, stylishly matted/fixed background artwork and humorously designed characters with unique personalities to boot, ''Chowder'' is one of the network's largest creative accomplishments in recent years.\"<ref name=\"insider\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animationinsider.net/article.php?articleID=1529|title=New 'Chowder' Animation Ready to Serve|first=Aaron H.|last=Bynum|date=October 24, 2007|work=Animation Insider|accessdate=February 18, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081222150449/http://www.animationinsider.net/article.php?articleID=1529|archive-date=December 22, 2008|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Awards and nominations===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! '''Year'''\n! '''Association'''\n! '''Category'''\n! '''Recipient'''\n! '''Result'''\n|-\n| 2008\n| [[Annie Awards]]\n| Best Animated Television Production for Children<ref name=\"annies08\">{{cite web|url=http://annieawards.org/35th-annie-awards|title=35th Annual Annie Nominations and Awards Recipients|work=AnnieAwards.org|publisher=[[ASIFA-Hollywood]]|accessdate=March 4, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081204082048/http://annieawards.org/35thwinners.html|archive-date=December 4, 2008|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| ''Chowder''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2008\n| Annie Awards\n| Writing in an Animated Television Production<ref name=\"annies08\"/>\n| C.H. Greenblatt and William Reiss<br />{{small|for \"Burple Nurples\"}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2008\n| [[Emmy Awards]]\n| Outstanding Special Class&nbsp;\u2014 Short-format Animated Programs<ref name=\"emmys\">{{cite web|url=http://www.emmys.com/shows/chowder|title=Chowder|work=[[Emmys.com]]|publisher=[[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]]|accessdate=July 9, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120501003329/http://www.emmys.com/shows/chowder|archive-date=May 1, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| C.H. Greenblatt, [[Brian A. Miller]], et al.<br />{{small|for \"Burple Nurples\"}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2009\n| Annie Awards\n| Production Design in an Animated Television Production<ref name=\"annies09\">{{cite web|url=http://annieawards.org/36th-annie-awards|title=36th Annual Annie Nominations and Awards Recipients|work=AnnieAwards.org|publisher=ASIFA-Hollywood|accessdate=July 9, 2012|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/69zPVGfIi?url=http://annieawards.org/legacy36th.html|archive-date=August 17, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| Dan Krall<br />{{small|for \"The Heavy Sleeper\"}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2009\n| Annie Awards\n| Voice Acting in an Animated Television Production<ref name=\"annies09\"/>\n| Dwight Schultz<br />{{small|as Mung Daal}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2009\n| Emmy Awards\n| Outstanding Individual Achievement in Animation<ref name=\"emmys\"/>\n| Joe Binggeli\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2010\n| Annie Awards\n| Voice Acting in a Television Production<ref name=\"annies10\">{{cite web|url=http://annieawards.org/37th-annie-awards|title=37th Annual Annie Nominations and Awards Recipients|work=AnnieAwards.org|publisher=ASIFA-Hollywood|accessdate=July 9, 2012|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6OY2jk0n5?url=http://annieawards.org/37th-annie-awards|archive-date=April 3, 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| Nicky Jones<br />{{small|as Chowder}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2010\n| Annie Awards\n| Voice Acting in a Television Production<ref name=\"annies10\"/>\n| Dwight Schultz<br />{{small|as Mung Daal}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2010\n| Emmy Awards\n| Outstanding Short-format Animated Program<ref name=\"emmys\"/>\n| [[Brian A. Miller]], C.H. Greenblatt, et al.<br />{{small|for \"The Toots\"}}\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n== Impact ==\nIn 2019, [[Lil Nas X]] made a music video of a remix of his song \"[[Panini (song)|Panini]]\" and named it after the ''Chowder'' character of the same name, and later made a music video for a remix of his song featuring characters from ''Chowder''. Although Greenblatt was not involved in the production of the music video, he did praise the video on his Tumblr blog.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://chgreenblatt.tumblr.com/post/187682692082/did-you-have-any-involvement-with-lil-nas-xs-new|title=Nerd Armada|website=Nerd Armada|date=September 13, 2019|accessdate=2019-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190924201429/https://chgreenblatt.tumblr.com/post/187682692082/did-you-have-any-involvement-with-lil-nas-xs-new|archive-date=September 24, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Portal|Cartoon Network|Cartoon|Animation|United States|Television}}\n* {{IMDb title|1140100|Chowder}}\n* {{bcdb|Other_Studios/C/Cartoon_Network_Studios/Chowder/|Chowder}}\n* ''[http://www.tv.com/shows/chowder/ Chowder]'' at [[TV.com]]\n\n{{Cartoon Network original programming}}\n\n[[Category:Chowder (TV series)| ]]\n[[Category:2007 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:2000s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:2000s American surreal comedy television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American surreal comedy television series]]\n[[Category:American animated television programs featuring anthropomorphic characters]]\n[[Category:American children's animated adventure television series]]\n[[Category:American children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:American children's animated fantasy television series]]\n[[Category:American television programs featuring puppetry]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about children]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about families]]\n[[Category:Cartoon Network Studios series and characters]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Metafictional television series]]\n[[Category:Television series created by C. H. Greenblatt]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American animated television series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2013}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Chowder\n| image                    = Chowder logo.png\n| genre                    = {{unbulleted list|[[Animation]]|[[Adventure film|Adventure]]|[[Surreal comedy]]<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/chowder | title=Chowder | access-date=April 9, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151003020806/http://www.metacritic.com/tv/chowder | archive-date=October 3, 2015 | url-status=live }}</ref>|[[Slapstick]]}}\n| creator                  = [[C. H. Greenblatt]]\n| writer                   = <!--Do not use when there are more than 5 writers. See Template:Infobox television instructions-->\n| director                 = {{unbulleted list|Eddy Houchins <small>(also supervising director)</small>|Kris Sherwood|Majella Milne <small>(2008\u201310)</small>|[[Mike Milo]] <small>(2008\u201310)</small>|Juli Hashiguchi <small>(2007\u201308)</small>|Shaun Cashman <small>(2007\u201308)</small>}}\n| creative_director        = [[William Reiss]]\n| voices                   = {{unbulleted list|[[Nicky Jones (actor)|Nicky Jones]]|[[Dwight Schultz]]|[[Kevin Michael Richardson]]|[[John DiMaggio]]|[[Tara Strong]]|C. H. Greenblatt|[[Dana Snyder]]|[[Liliana Mumy]]|[[Mindy Sterling]]|[[Diedrich Bader]]}}\n| theme_music_composer     = C.H. Greenblatt, Dan Boer & Zac Pike\n| composer                 = Dan Boer & Zac Pike\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 3\n| num_episodes             = 49 (93 segments)\n| list_episodes            = List of Chowder episodes\n| executive_producer       = C. H. Greenblatt\n| producer                 = Louis J. Cuck\n| runtime                  = 22 minutes\n| company                  = [[Cartoon Network Studios]]<br>[[Screen Novelties]] <small>(stopmotion segments)</small><br>[[Hong Ying Animation|Hong Ying Animation Entertainment]] <small>(animation services)</small>\n| distributor              = [[Warner Bros. Television Distribution]]\n| network                  = [[Cartoon Network]]\n| picture_format           = [[1080i]] ([[16:9]] [[HDTV]])\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2007|11|2}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|2010|8|7}}\n| website                  = \n| image_size               = 250\n}}\n\n'''''Chowder''''' is an American [[animated television series]] created by [[C. H. Greenblatt]] for [[Cartoon Network]].<ref>{{cite book |last1=Perlmutter |first1=David |title=The Encyclopedia of American Animated Television Shows |date=2018 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1538103739 |pages=123\u2013125 }}</ref>\n\n''Chowder'' premiered on November 2, 2007, and ran for three seasons with 49 total episodes. It received mostly positive reviews, as well as one [[Primetime Emmy Award]] win, six [[Annie Award]] nominations, and two additional Emmy Award nominations during its run. The series finale, \"Chowder Grows Up\", aired on August 7, 2010.\n\n==Plot==\nThe series follows an aspiring young chef apprentice named Chowder and his day-to-day adventures in Chef Mung Daal's [[catering]] company. Although he means well, Chowder often finds himself in predicaments due to his [[Gourmand|perpetual appetite]] and his nature as a [[wikt:scatterbrain|scatterbrain]]. It is animated with both [[traditional animation]] as well as short [[stop motion]] and [[puppet]] sequences that are inter-cut into episodes and the end credits. Stop motion sequences are produced by [[Screen Novelties]].\n\n==Characters==\n{{fanpov|section|date=December 2019}}\nEach character is named after a type of food or dish.\n\n===Main===\n*'''Chowder''' (voiced by [[Nicky Jones (actor)|Nicky Jones]]): A 12-year-old chubby purple {{not a typo|[[cat]]/[[bear]]/[[rabbit]]}}<ref name=CNUKfacts>{{cite web|title=Character Facts of the Week: Chowder|url=http://www.cartoonnetwork.co.uk/blogs/character-facts-of-the-week-chowder|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140910053503/http://www.cartoonnetwork.co.uk/blogs/character-facts-of-the-week-chowder|archivedate=September 10, 2014|date=March 20, 2012|quote=Chowder is a mix between a cat, bear, and rabbit.}}</ref> hybrid who serves as an apprentice under the chef [[Mung Daal]], Chowder lives with Mung Daal and his wife, Truffles, in a room at the top of the catering business. Chowder wants to become a great chef, but he is very impulsive and scatterbrained and often gives in to his urges. He is always hungry and eats anything, even a customer's order. Chowder can also regurgitate objects, and he is used as a storage container by the other characters. According to Greenblatt, he is a composite of a cat, a bear and a rabbit, and his species was verified in at least one episode.<ref>{{cite episode|title=The Puckerberry Overlords|series=Chowder|airdate=January 18, 2008}}</ref> C. H. Greenblatt voiced his adult self in the last episode. In the final episode, \u201cChowder Grows Up\u201d Chowder takes over the Catering Company, has his own apprentice and gets married to Panini. He is also a father to 50 babies.\n*'''Mung Daal''' (voiced by [[Dwight Schultz]]): The elderly chef who runs the catering company at which Chowder works.<ref name=\"cn-bio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/tv_shows/chowder/index.html|title=Chowder|publisher=Cartoon Network|accessdate=April 26, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130429100538/http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/tv_shows/chowder/index.html|archive-date=April 29, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> Although his exact age has not been stated, he has mentioned that he has cooked for at least 386 years,<ref name=\"certifrycation\">{{cite episode|title=Certifrycation Class|series=Chowder|airdate=November 16, 2007}}</ref> and he celebrated 450 years of marriage to Truffles (see below).<ref name=\"mung\">{{cite episode|title=Mung on the Rocks|series=Chowder|airdate=March 6, 2008}}</ref> He is a light on blue-colored humanoid and is named after the [[Indian cuisine|Indian dish]] [[Mung bean|mung]] [[dal|daal]], that Greenblatt had originally planned to give Mung an [[Indian accent]], but later decided against it.<ref name=\"food\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/10/real-world-food-counterparts.html|title=Real World Food Counterparts|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=October 12, 2008|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=January 31, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090201224541/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/10/real-world-food-counterparts.html|archive-date=February 1, 2009|url-status=live}}</ref> In the final episode, Mung is now retired with Truffles, leaving the catering company to Chowder.\n*'''Shnitzel''' (voiced by [[Kevin Michael Richardson]] in \"The Froggy Apple Crumple Thumpkin\", and [[John DiMaggio]] afterward): A 38-year-old taupe rock monster and professional chef who works at Mung Daal's Catering Company. His vocabulary consists almost entirely of \"radda\", while it's translated as \"okay\", although he sometimes says other simple words.<ref name=\"radda\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/01/shnitzel-faq.html|title=Shnitzel FAQ|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=January 1, 2008|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=April 7, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080105142731/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/01/shnitzel-faq.html|archive-date=January 5, 2008|url-status=live}}</ref> He talks in the episode \"The Trouble with Truffles\" because he finally gets calm enough. Shnitzel is the \"[[straight man]]\" to the other more excitable characters and is frequently agitated. He gets stuck with menial labor or cleanup duty, as well as the heavy lifting because he is extremely strong. Although usually angered by Chowder's antics, Shnitzel really has a soft spot for Chowder, as he cries when it was thought that Chowder has vanished forever.<ref name=\"radda\"/><ref name=\"chowder-prem\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/10/just-two-weeks-until-chowder-premiere.html|title=Just Two Weeks Until Chowder Premiere|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=July 18, 2007|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=November 9, 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071118022353/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/10/just-two-weeks-until-chowder-premiere.html|archive-date=November 18, 2007|url-status=live}}</ref> Kevin Michael Richardson voiced Shnitzel for the debut episode \"The Froggy Apple Crumple Thumpkin\" and was replaced at the last moment by DiMaggio due to Richardson being busy with other projects at the time.<ref name=\"radda\"/> In the final episode, Schnitzel has left the catering company and live a happy life with his wife, Endive.\n*'''Truffles Daal''' (voiced by [[Tara Strong]]): A [[mushroom]] [[pixie]]/[[fairy]] and Mung Daal's wife who handles the business side of Mung's catering business. She is an extreme [[Four Temperaments#choleric|choleric]]. Greenblatt said that he based Truffles on his mother.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/11/mahjongg-night.html|title=Mahjongg Night|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|work=Nerd Armada|date=November 28, 2007|accessdate=September 14, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110823031150/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/11/mahjongg-night.html|archive-date=August 23, 2011|url-status=live}}</ref> Greenblatt said that he initially found difficulty in working on any story with Truffles since the character could be \"so abrasive\" that the ''Chowder'' staff had to be \"a little more sensitive about finding her softer side.\" Greenblatt said that the staff eventually decided that \"a little Truffles goes a long way.\" Therefore, she would appear occasionally in ''Chowder'' in a manner similar to how [[Oscar the Grouch]] appears on ''[[Sesame Street]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bakertoons.blogspot.com/2009/08/exit-interview-with-ch-greenblatt.html|title=Exit interview with C.H. Greenblatt|first=Charles|last=Brubaker|date=August 31, 2009|work=Baking the Baker|accessdate=September 15, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708024534/http://bakertoons.blogspot.com/2009/08/exit-interview-with-ch-greenblatt.html|archive-date=July 8, 2011|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2009/08/were-off.html|title=We're Off!|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=August 31, 2009|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=September 15, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110923091741/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2009/08/were-off.html|archive-date=September 23, 2011|url-status=live}}</ref> In the final episode, Truffles retired along with Mung, possibly giving her Job to Panini.<!--Link 1 is the interview, link 2 is to confirm that he did the interview-->\n*'''Kimchi''' (voiced by C. H. Greenblatt): Chowder's pet, who lives in a cage next to his bed. Kimchi is an anthropomorphic flatus (due to the unpleasant odor of [[kimchi]]). He likes things with odors unpleasant for the other characters, and he \"talks\" by making flatulent sounds. Kimchi was first seen in the episode \"The Froggy Apple Crumple Thumpkin\". Kimchi is usually shown with a blank personality but in \"Stinky Love\" it is shown that he has an opinion.<ref name=\"toonzone\"/> What happens to Kimchi in the final episode is unknown, but it\u2019s possible that he still lives with Chowder.\n*'''Gazpacho''' (voiced by [[Dana Snyder]]): A [[woolly mammoth]] storekeeper who sells strange [[produce]] and ingredients at the farmer's market. He does his best to offer advice to Chowder when needed. He lives with his overbearing mother, who never appears on screen, but is present at the end of episode \"Gazpacho!\". In \"The Spookiest House in Marzipan\" it is hinted at that Gazpacho has no mother, and that he actually suffers with [[dissociative identity disorder]], but creator Greenblatt says this was merely to \"pay homage to ''[[Psycho (1960 film)|Psycho]]''\". Gazpacho shows no interest in moving out and improving his own life. Gazpacho's worst enemies are [[ninja]]s. Greenblatt named him after the cold soup [[gazpacho]]; Greenblatt said that he did not know why, but the name suited the character immediately.<ref name=\"food\"/> In the final episode, Gazpacho closed the stand, and became a nomad. He later pursued his dream and open a Comedy Night Club.\n*'''Panini''' (voiced by [[Liliana Mumy]]): A 12-year-old pink [[cabbit]] who has a crush on Chowder and reminds him at every opportunity. Chowder does not return the feelings and responds with \"I'm not your boyfriend!\" whenever she greets him. Panini is an apprentice to Ms. Endive, and is also possessive of Chowder. Panini gets jealous when she sees Chowder with another girl, in which Chowder really does to avoid her. Her original character concept had her [[bullying|bully]] Chowder in a manner described by Greenblatt as similar to [[Angelica Pickles]] from ''[[Rugrats]]''.<ref name=\"OldPanEn\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2009/06/early-endive-panini-designs.html|title=Early Endive & Panini Designs|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=June 15, 2009|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=June 22, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090714054958/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2009/06/early-endive-panini-designs.html|archive-date=July 14, 2009|url-status=live}}</ref> Greenblatt removed the pointy ears since he felt this did not fit in with the rounded shapes in ''Chowder''. Greenblatt did not like characters similar to Angelica and believed that he needed to make Panini \"cuter and sweeter\".<ref name=\"OldPanEn\"/> Greenblatt said that the details of Panini formed when the creator decided that Panini had a crush on Chowder; since Chowder is not old enough to fall in love with females, according to Greenblatt this aspect would frustrate Chowder \"in a more fun way\".<ref name=\"OldPanEn\"/> In the last episode, it is shown that Chowder finally returned Panini's feelings and accepted her because he realizes that he made Panini's life miserable and they are married with many kids and was voiced by [[Grey DeLisle]]. Panini's name literally means \"sandwiches\" in Italian, while her former name, Borlotti, is a type of beans. In the final episode Panini married Chowder, and is currently a mother of 50, she then promised Chowder to stop having more. It\u2019s also likely that she took over Truffles old job.\n*'''Gorgonzola''' (voiced by Will Shadley): A young green [[rat]] apprentice candle holder with an unlikeable attitude. He shows jealousy over Chowder which is, in fact Chowder having a better job than him.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/07/gorgonzola.html|title=Gorgonzola|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=July 18, 2007|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=November 9, 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071107091545/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/07/gorgonzola.html|archive-date=November 7, 2007|url-status=live}}</ref> He will occasionally use Chowder, and if forced, will partner with him in games. Since [[blue cheese]] was one of the few foods Greenblatt disliked, he decided to use the name \"[[Gorgonzola (cheese)|gorgonzola]]\" for a character who did not get along with Chowder. Gorgonzola resembles a green [[opossum]] or a green [[rat]]. He wears tattered brown clothes and no shoes, and has a partially melted candle on his head (for traditional reasons). He is desperate to get cash, and will do almost anything to get it. Gorgonzola also loves to play Sniffleball, as seen in the episode ''Sniffleball''. Despite his unpleasant and boastful attitude to Chowder, Chowder sees him as a close friend, which irritates him even more. Gorgonzola is an apprentice to Stilton, who is a candle holder, hence why both characters have burning candles on their heads.<ref name=\"food\"/> In the final episode, Gorgonzola runs a very successful company, most likely involving candle holding.\n*'''Ms. Endive''' (voiced by [[Mindy Sterling]]): An [[obesity|obese]], intelligent, and somewhat snobbish 46-year-old female chef who teaches cooking to Panini with strict discipline. She is usually depicted as gargantuan in size. This is shown in the episode \"The Apprentice Games\" where Mung Daal and Chowder enter the games by riding on Endive's posterior. She regularly berates Mung Daal, whom she considers a rival. In the episode \"Chowder's Girlfriend\", it is revealed she despises boys and boyfriends because her fianc\u00e9 did not show up on their wedding day. Ms. Endive is first seen in the second episode with Panini, \"Chowder's Girlfriend\". The creator describes her as [[Martha Stewart]] with [[Oompa-Loompa]] colors.<ref name=\"endive\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/04/endive.html|title=Ms. Endive|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=April 19, 2007|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=November 9, 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071118022158/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2007/04/endive.html|archive-date=November 18, 2007|url-status=live}}</ref> Greenblatt chose to name her after the [[endive]] since endive is bitter and Belgian endive is fancy; hence the character is bitter and fancy.<ref name=\"food\"/> Endive's character stayed constant throughout the initial development. The long nose, which changed from a rectangular shape to a triangle shape for the final version, represents how Endive looks down at other characters. It was revealed in later episodes that Ms. Endive is in love with Shnitzel. Greenblatt said that he felt that her evolution throughout the series was fun to observe, especially when William Reiss wrote plots involving Endive.<ref name=\"OldPanEn\"/> In the final episode, Endive is living a happy life with her Husband, Schnitzel.\n\n===Recurring===\n*'''Kiwi''' (voiced by C. H. Greenblatt) is a [[photorealistic]] pink creature who always gives advice to Chowder and his friends and occasionally provides interstitial narrations, especially at times where particularly corny humor is displayed. His name is revealed (for the first and only time ever in the show's run) in the episode \"Brain Grub\", where it is known that after Chowder alters the animated universe, Kiwi is reduced to selling used cars.\n*'''Ceviche''' (voiced by Elan Garfias): A young yellow (and somewhat androgynous) [[goat]] apprentice to Pat\u00e9 and Panini's best friend, Ceviche was introduced in the episode \"The Apprentice Games\". He practices aerobic-style dancing and is very charitable and kind to others. Because of his admirable attitude and amazing talents (as well as good looks, as it was shown on one episode that he has a well-sculpted body) he is well-liked.  He is good friends with Panini and will make unwanted advances upon her, which are either refused or unnoticed. Ceviche is also a close friend to Chowder. He has a crush on Panini.  He speaks in a [[wikt:monotone|monotonous]] voice and serves as [[deadpan]] humor for the show.\n*'''Pat\u00e9''' (voiced by John DiMaggio): A tall, well-sculpted [[humanoid]] ballet dance master and operatic singer with a deep voice, grass-green hair, a small black hat, and exaggerated lips who is the mentor of Ceviche. Pat\u00e9 was introduced briefly on the second episode of the first show ''Chowder's Girlfriend'' (Episode #1b), where he sings \"I'm Not Your Boyfriend\" on stage to Panini (on behalf of Chowder) in front of an audience. His name, however, was revealed for the first time on ''The Apprentice Games'' (Episode 20), where he appeared as a judge for the Marzipan City Apprentice Games. In that same episode, it was also revealed that he lives in another dimension, as was shown by the portal through which he and Ceviche made their entrance and exit.\n*'''Chestnut''' (originally voiced by [[Tone L\u014dc]], then [[John DiMaggio]]): Like the food, Chestnut is small and tough. He is a tiny, [[blue]] horned [[devil]]-like creature with a deep, gravelly voice and, to many character's surprise, is physically very strong.  Because of his size, he uses everyday objects as other things (e.g. using a briefcase for a hydrofoil, or a hat as a vacation home). He sings small songs to himself, usually consisting of his catchphrase of \"Dinka-loo, dinka-lee.\" He is teacher of the BLTs, a parody of the [[SAT]]s. He always refers to himself in the [[Grammatical person|third person]] when speaking.\n*'''Reuben''' (voiced by [[Paul Reubens]]): A pig who is a [[confidence trick|conman]] and steals from others.\n*'''Mr. Fugu''' (voiced by [[Bob Joles]]): A sentient floating balloon who is said to be Mung's most frequent customer. He is proven to be more greedy than Chowder and never shares any food with him. He is often seen with his valet, Foie Gras, a [[Maneki-neko]] (meows provided by [[George Takei]]) holding Mr. Fugu's string as he cannot control his flotation.\n*'''Sgt. Hoagie''' (voiced by [[Diedrich Bader]]): He is a [[dog]] who is a police officer in Marzipan City. In ''The Hot Date'', he was going out on a date after several years and asked the other cops for advice.\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Main|List of Chowder episodes}}\n{{:List of Chowder episodes}}\nA total of 49 episodes were aired in the series. Season 1, which consists of 20 episodes, started on November 2, 2007, with the series premiere, entitled \"The Froggy Apple Crumble Thumpkin/Chowder's Girlfriend\". Season 1 ended on July 24, 2008, with the special \"The Apprentice Games\". Season 2 also contains 20 episodes, debuting on October 1, 2008, with \"The Arborians/The Garage Sale\", and ending with \"A Faire to Remember/Tofu-Town Showdown\", broadcasting on September 29, 2009, and October 6, 2009, respectively. Season 3 consists of only 9 episodes, premiering October 12, 2009, with \"The Blast Raz\", and ending with the series finale, entitled \"Chowder Grows Up\", which aired on August 7, 2010.\n\n==Development==\n[[File:ChowderPuppets.jpg|thumb|The puppet versions of the characters Chowder (a Hand-Rod puppet) and Mung Daal]]\nDuring his time working on Nickelodeon's ''[[SpongeBob SquarePants]]'', Greenblatt had been sketching various characters for his own animation series concept.<ref name=\"toonzone\"/> Greenblatt originally based the premise on the idea of the sorcerer's apprentice style of story, such as ''[[The Sword in the Stone (1963 film)|The Sword in the Stone]]''. The plot devices were modified so that the story revolves around a master chef who teaches his young apprentice how to cook. Chowder himself was developed with no specific species in mind, but rather with the intentions of invoking the image of a child's soft squeeze toy.<ref name=\"kitty-interview\"/> Some of the inspiration comes from [[Dr. Seuss]], with other inspiration from [[Saturday morning cartoon]]s.<ref name=\"kitty-interview\"/><ref name=\"armada\">{{cite web |url=http://forum.newsarama.com/showthread.php?t=139420 |title=Meet the Master Chef&nbsp;\u2013 C.H. Greenblatt |date=December 12, 2007 |first=Steve |last=Fritz |publisher=Animated Shorts |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090122105026/http://forum.newsarama.com/showthread.php?t=139420 |archivedate=January 22, 2009 |accessdate=April 26, 2013 |url-status=dead |df=mdy }}</ref>\n\nGreenblatt pitched the concept to Cartoon Network in the mid-2000s, when he began working as a writer and storyboard artist for ''[[The Grim Adventures of Billy & Mandy]]'', and two years later the series was approved with another year for production before the pilot episode aired. Greenblatt estimates he spent about seven years working on ''Chowder'' before the show made it to air in 2007.<ref name=\"toonzone\"/>\n\n==Production and format==\nEpisodes are produced in seasons which consist of twenty 24-minute episodes. Each episode is produced with a 30-second puppet sequence that is meant to run over the ending credits.<ref name=\"season2\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/06/let-new-chowders-begin.html|title=Let the New Chowders Begin!!|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=June 3, 2008|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=June 4, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708054506/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/06/let-new-chowders-begin.html|archive-date=July 8, 2011|url-status=live}}</ref> Episodes can be purchased from the [[iTunes Store]] in the United States which are delivered with the sequences as are episodes which are available on Cartoon Network's VOD website also within the United States.<ref name=\"kitty-interview\"/><ref name=\"puppets\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/02/more-puppets.html|title=More Puppets|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=February 7, 2008|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=March 4, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101203005913/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/02/more-puppets.html|archive-date=December 3, 2010|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOne of the unusual design features of the show is the patterns used on the clothing or players. The patterns are developed as a full-screen image and then sent to the production house, where the characters are modified to fill the patterns in over the character clothing.<ref name=\"toonzone\">{{cite web|url=http://www.toonzone.net/2007/10/toon-zone-interviews-c-h-greenblatt-on-crafting-chowder/|title=Toon Zone Interviews C.H. Greenblatt on Crafting \"Chowder\"|first=Ed|last=Liu|date=October 30, 2007|publisher=Toon Zone|accessdate=March 4, 2008|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130703111526/http://www.toonzone.net/2007/10/toon-zone-interviews-c-h-greenblatt-on-crafting-chowder/|archive-date=July 3, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"kitty-interview\">{{cite web|url=http://kittysneezes.com/2008/02/08/interview-ch-greenblatt-207/|title=Interview: C.H. Greenblatt|first=Joe|last=Meyer|date=February 8, 2008|work=KittySneezes.com|accessdate=March 4, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130116025642/http://kittysneezes.com/2008/02/08/interview-ch-greenblatt-207/|archive-date=January 16, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"patterns\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/01/chowder-patterns.html|title=Chowder Patterns|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=January 29, 2008|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=March 4, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080516031555/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2008/01/chowder-patterns.html|archive-date=May 16, 2008|url-status=live}}</ref> Using this technique, when a character moves, their patterns do not follow, but display as a \"static\" background. A similar technique was used in the ''[[Monkey Island (series)|Monkey Island]]'' video game series (particularly for the Stan), the Nickelodeon series [[The Off-Beats]], and the [[Mr. Bean (animated TV series)|''Mr. Bean'' animated series]].<ref name=\"armada\"/>\n\nThe show is also known for the very wide variety of media used in various episodes. These include animation using watercolors and ink-and-paint in addition to the cartoon's classic pattern style. It also uses stop motion animation with real food, action figures and clay; live-action scenes with the voice actors of the show and puppets; both marionette and hand-controlled. This was also sometimes used in ''[[Courage the Cowardly Dog]]''. It boasts one of the most diverse varieties of mediums used in any single series.\n\n==Cancellation==\n''Chowder'' was cancelled by Cartoon Network in August 2009, as the network felt the show did not fit its new demographic of older boys, favoring shows such as the live-action ''[[Destroy, Build, Destroy]]'' instead.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://chgreenblatt.tumblr.com/post/152842491532/you-mentioned-in-an-ask-that-you-went-through-the | title=Tumblr | access-date=November 15, 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161116103638/http://chgreenblatt.tumblr.com/post/152842491532/you-mentioned-in-an-ask-that-you-went-through-the | archive-date=November 16, 2016 | url-status=live }}</ref> On his blog, C.H. Greenblatt expressed relief about having his schedule freed up by the cancellation, saying: \"I didn't really think there'd be this many upsides to having a show officially cancelled by a network, but I'm feeling happier than I've been in a long time. Since we've only got post-production, my schedule finally eases up. I haven't had a break like this in a long, long time... ''Chowder'' has opened up a lot of awesome possibilities for me, and creatively I'm feeling more inspired than ever.\"<ref name=\"blogspot\">{{cite web|url=http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2009/08/hot-girl.html|title=The Hot Girl|first=C.H.|last=Greenblatt|date=August 13, 2009|work=Nerd Armada|accessdate=January 2, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120311091937/http://nerdarmada.blogspot.com/2009/08/hot-girl.html|archive-date=March 11, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Home media==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n|+''Chowder'' home video releases\n! colspan=3 rowspan=2|Season !! rowspan=2|Episodes !! rowspan=2|Volume !! colspan=2|Release dates !! rowspan=2|Episode(s) include\n|-\n! {{USA}} !! {{THA}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.toonzone.net/forums/threads/dvd-releases-from-mvd-in-thailand.5527321 |title=DVD releases from MVD in Thailand |access-date=April 24, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160424214131/http://www.toonzone.net/forums/threads/dvd-releases-from-mvd-in-thailand.5527321/ |archive-date=April 24, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=5 style=\"background:#1E5994\"| || rowspan=5|[[List of Chowder episodes#Season 1 (2007\u201308)|1]]\n| rowspan=5|2007\u201308 || rowspan=5|20 || rowspan=2|1 || November 4, 2008<ref>{{cite web|asin=B001DSNFQ4|title=Chowder, Vol. 1 (2008)}}</ref> || rowspan=2|November 10, 2010 || rowspan=2|\"The Froggy Apple Crumple Thumpkin\" / \"Chowder's Girlfriend\" \u2022 \"Grubble Gum\" \u2013 \"The Sing Beans\" \u2022 \"Mahjongg Night\" \u2013 \"The Flibber-Flabber Diet\"\n|-\n| May 6, 2014\n|-\n| 2 || March 3, 2009<ref>{{cite web|asin=B001MEJYBY|title=Chowder, Vol. 2 (2009)}}</ref> || December 15, 2010 || \"Burple Nurples\" / \"Shnitzel Makes a Deposit\" \u2022 \"The Wrong Address\" / \"The Wrong Customer\" \u2022 \"Gazpacho Stands Up\" \u2013 \"Mung on the Rocks\"\n|-\n| 3 || {{n/a}} || January 19, 2010 || \"The Heavy Sleeper\" \u2013 \"The Rat Sandwich\"\n|-\n| 4 || {{n/a}} || February 15, 2011 || \"Chowder Loses His Hat\" \u2013 \"The Apprentice Games\"\n|-\n! rowspan=5 style=\"background:#5C1F99\"| || rowspan=5|[[List of Chowder episodes#Season 2 (2008\u201309)|2]]\n| rowspan=5|2008\u201309 || rowspan=5|20 || 5 || {{n/a}} || March 15, 2011 || \"The Arborians\" \u2013 \"The Catch Phrase\"\n|-\n| 6 || {{n/a}} || April 8, 2011 || \"The Hot Date\" \u2013 \"The Deadly Maze\" \u2022 \"The B.L.T.'s\" \u2013 \"The Dinner Theater\"\n|-\n| 7 || {{n/a}} || May 10, 2011 || \"Kid Shnitzel\" / \"Gazpacho Fights Back\" \u2022 \"Big Ball\" \u2013 \"The Blackout\"\n|-\n| 8 || {{n/a}} || June 14, 2011 || \"The Dice Cycle\" \u2013 \"The Grape Worm\"\n|-\n| rowspan=2|9 || rowspan=2 style=\"background:#ececec;color:#2d2d2d\"|<small>N/A</small> || rowspan=2|July 26, 2011 || rowspan=2| \"A Faire to Remember\" \u2013 \"The Birthday Suits\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 style=\"background:#991F5C\"| || rowspan=2|[[List of Chowder episodes#Season 3 (2009\u201310)|3]]\n| rowspan=2|2009\u201310 || rowspan=2|9\n|-\n| 10 || {{n/a}} || August 24, 2011 || \"The Heist\" \u2013 \"Chowder Grows Up\"\n|}\nThe entire series has been released in ten [[DVD region code#3|Region 3]] [[pan and scan|fullscreen]] DVD volumes in Thailand from MVD Company Limited.\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critics===\nChowder received mostly positive reviews. Barry Garron of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' thought that the show would appeal to children and adults alike, using exotic artwork, unusual settings, and a zany cast of characters.<ref name=\"hollywood\">{{cite journal|url=http://208.115.47.50/cartoonnetwork/article_images/NXE913120_1_H.pdf |title=Chowder |first=Barry |last=Garron |date=November 2, 2007 |page=47 |journal=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5oDZGw1pO?url=http://208.115.47.50/cartoonnetwork/article_images/NXE913120_1_H.pdf |archivedate=March 14, 2010 |accessdate=April 26, 2013 |url-status=dead |df=mdy }}</ref> On Toon Zone, Ed Liu expands on the animation and crazy antics of the characters, pointing that \"the humor is kid-friendly without being juvenile\" and praising it for getting laughs, \"without resorting to an excess of toilet humor, even if Chowder's pet happens to be a sentient fart cloud.\"<ref name=\"toonzone-review\">{{cite web|url=http://www.toonzone.net/2007/11/chowder-is-satisfying-comfort-food/|title=\"Chowder\" is Satisfying Comfort Food|first=Ed|last=Liu|date=November 2, 2007|publisher=Toon Zone|accessdate=February 18, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131025005642/http://www.toonzone.net/2007/11/chowder-is-satisfying-comfort-food/|archive-date=October 25, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> Aaron H. Bynum on ''Animation Insider'' wrote, \"Featuring brightly colored environments, stylishly matted/fixed background artwork and humorously designed characters with unique personalities to boot, ''Chowder'' is one of the network's largest creative accomplishments in recent years.\"<ref name=\"insider\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animationinsider.net/article.php?articleID=1529|title=New 'Chowder' Animation Ready to Serve|first=Aaron H.|last=Bynum|date=October 24, 2007|work=Animation Insider|accessdate=February 18, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081222150449/http://www.animationinsider.net/article.php?articleID=1529|archive-date=December 22, 2008|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Awards and nominations===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! '''Year'''\n! '''Association'''\n! '''Category'''\n! '''Recipient'''\n! '''Result'''\n|-\n| 2008\n| [[Annie Awards]]\n| Best Animated Television Production for Children<ref name=\"annies08\">{{cite web|url=http://annieawards.org/35th-annie-awards|title=35th Annual Annie Nominations and Awards Recipients|work=AnnieAwards.org|publisher=[[ASIFA-Hollywood]]|accessdate=March 4, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081204082048/http://annieawards.org/35thwinners.html|archive-date=December 4, 2008|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| ''Chowder''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2008\n| Annie Awards\n| Writing in an Animated Television Production<ref name=\"annies08\"/>\n| C.H. Greenblatt and William Reiss<br />{{small|for \"Burple Nurples\"}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2008\n| [[Emmy Awards]]\n| Outstanding Special Class&nbsp;\u2014 Short-format Animated Programs<ref name=\"emmys\">{{cite web|url=http://www.emmys.com/shows/chowder|title=Chowder|work=[[Emmys.com]]|publisher=[[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]]|accessdate=July 9, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120501003329/http://www.emmys.com/shows/chowder|archive-date=May 1, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| C.H. Greenblatt, [[Brian A. Miller]], et al.<br />{{small|for \"Burple Nurples\"}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2009\n| Annie Awards\n| Production Design in an Animated Television Production<ref name=\"annies09\">{{cite web|url=http://annieawards.org/36th-annie-awards|title=36th Annual Annie Nominations and Awards Recipients|work=AnnieAwards.org|publisher=ASIFA-Hollywood|accessdate=July 9, 2012|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/69zPVGfIi?url=http://annieawards.org/legacy36th.html|archive-date=August 17, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| Dan Krall<br />{{small|for \"The Heavy Sleeper\"}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2009\n| Annie Awards\n| Voice Acting in an Animated Television Production<ref name=\"annies09\"/>\n| Dwight Schultz<br />{{small|as Mung Daal}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2009\n| Emmy Awards\n| Outstanding Individual Achievement in Animation<ref name=\"emmys\"/>\n| Joe Binggeli\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2010\n| Annie Awards\n| Voice Acting in a Television Production<ref name=\"annies10\">{{cite web|url=http://annieawards.org/37th-annie-awards|title=37th Annual Annie Nominations and Awards Recipients|work=AnnieAwards.org|publisher=ASIFA-Hollywood|accessdate=July 9, 2012|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6OY2jk0n5?url=http://annieawards.org/37th-annie-awards|archive-date=April 3, 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| Nicky Jones<br />{{small|as Chowder}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2010\n| Annie Awards\n| Voice Acting in a Television Production<ref name=\"annies10\"/>\n| Dwight Schultz<br />{{small|as Mung Daal}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2010\n| Emmy Awards\n| Outstanding Short-format Animated Program<ref name=\"emmys\"/>\n| [[Brian A. Miller]], C.H. Greenblatt, et al.<br />{{small|for \"The Toots\"}}\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n== Impact ==\nIn 2019, [[Lil Nas X]] made a music video of a remix of his song \"[[Panini (song)|Panini]]\" and named it after the ''Chowder'' character of the same name, and later made a music video for a remix of his song featuring characters from ''Chowder''. Although Greenblatt was not involved in the production of the music video, he did praise the video on his Tumblr blog.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://chgreenblatt.tumblr.com/post/187682692082/did-you-have-any-involvement-with-lil-nas-xs-new|title=Nerd Armada|website=Nerd Armada|date=September 13, 2019|accessdate=2019-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190924201429/https://chgreenblatt.tumblr.com/post/187682692082/did-you-have-any-involvement-with-lil-nas-xs-new|archive-date=September 24, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Portal|Cartoon Network|Cartoon|Animation|United States|Television}}\n* {{IMDb title|1140100|Chowder}}\n* {{bcdb|Other_Studios/C/Cartoon_Network_Studios/Chowder/|Chowder}}\n* ''[http://www.tv.com/shows/chowder/ Chowder]'' at [[TV.com]]\n\n{{Cartoon Network original programming}}\n\n[[Category:Chowder (TV series)| ]]\n[[Category:2007 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:2000s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:2000s American surreal comedy television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American surreal comedy television series]]\n[[Category:American animated television programs featuring anthropomorphic characters]]\n[[Category:American children's animated adventure television series]]\n[[Category:American children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:American children's animated fantasy television series]]\n[[Category:American television programs featuring puppetry]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about children]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about families]]\n[[Category:Cartoon Network Studios series and characters]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Metafictional television series]]\n[[Category:Television series created by C. H. Greenblatt]]\n", "name_user": "Jellysandwich0", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chowder_(TV_series)"}
{"title_page": "Heart Book (All Nations Gospel Publishers)", "text_new": "{{Unreferenced|date=April 2020}}\n'''THE HEART OF MAN OR THE SPIRITUAL HEART MIRROR'''\n\n(''An Allegorical Representation in Ten Pictures'')\n\nTHE HEART OF MAN BOOKLET\n\nThis Booklet originated in France in 1732, was revised and rewritten for the mission fields of Africa by Rev. J.R. [https://globalchristiancenter.com/missions-inspiration/22542-memories-of-a-godly-missionary Gschwend]  in 1929, and has subsequently been translated and printed under copyright in over 538 indigenous languages by [http://www.angp.org ALL NATIONS GOSPEL PUBLISHERS] who are distributing it today in 127 mission countries. People of all languages, classes and religions are being led by this booklet to experience the deep spiritual truth and significance of God\u2019s message to mankind as expressed by the prophet [[Ezekiel]] 586 years before [[Christ]], \u201cI will give you a new heart and a new mind then you will be my people, and I will be your [[God]]!\u201d Ezekiel 36:26-28.\n\nThe text used is from the compact (or shorter) format of the booklet. Different formats of the booklet including the complete booklet in .pdf format can be downloaded free of charge.\n\nQuotes from [[Scripture]] was taken from [[Good News Bible|The Good News Bible]] \n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|ALL NATIONS GOSPEL PUBLISHERS\n|http://www.angp.org/index.php?id=25\n|-\n|Text written:\n|1929\n|-\n|Written by:\n|Rev. J.R. Gschwend\n|-\n|Text and pictures owned by:\n|ALL NATIONS GOSPEL PUBLISHERS\n|-\n|Number of translations available\n|481\n|-\n|Latest mission report:\n|http://www.angp.org/fileadmin/angp/sites/pdf/AN_englisch_aktuell.pdf\n|-\n|Download all booklets from:\n|https://angp-hb.co.za/\n|-\n|Download Booklet Format:\n|https://angp-hb.co.za/booklet-format/\n|-\n|Download Cell phone Format:\n|https://angp-hb.co.za/cellphone-format/\n|-\n|Download Print Format:\n|https://angp-hb.co.za/print-format/\n|-\n|Download Compact Format:\n|https://angp-hb.co.za/compact-format/\n|}\n\n== THE HEART OF MAN: THE TEMPLE OF GOD OR THE WORKSHOP OF SATAN ==\n'''(1 John 3:4-10)'''\n[[File:The heart of man booklet.jpg|alt=The Heart of man|thumb|The Heart of man booklet]]\nAs you read this book, please bear in mind that it is like a mirror in which you will be able to see yourself. Whether you are a heathen or a Christian, one who does not believe in [[Christ]] or a backslider, you will see yourself as [[God]] sees you. \u201cMan looks at the outward appearance, but I look at the heart.\u201d (1 Sam. 16:7). God sees us as we really are.\n\n[[Satan]] is the father of all lies. He is the prince of darkness and god of this world, who disguises himself as an angel of light to lead men and women the wrong way. In these days, as in times past, there are many false [[apostles]] who disguise themselves, pretending to be apostles of Christ. And no wonder, for Satan himself is transformed (disguised) into an angel of light (2 Corinthians 11:13,14). Satan, the god of this world, keeps people in the dark so that they cannot see that God loves them or that Jesus died to save them (2 Cor. 4:4). All sinners and those who do not believe are spiritually dead and blind concerning God. They are ruled by the evil of this world (Eph. 2:1-2). Unless their eyes are opened in some way to their lost condition, they are heading for eternal destruction. The person who says, \u201cI have never sinned\u201d is deceiving himself. For \u201cThe Son of God appeared for this very reason, to destroy what the devil had done.\u201d (1 John 3:8). \u201cSo then, submit to God. Resist the devil, and he will run away from you. Come near to God, and He will come near to you.\u201d (James 4:7,8)\n\nAs you read this book and study its pictures, you will be able to see your own heart. Allow God\u2019s searchlight to show you the condition of your heart. Acknowledge your sins and do not deny their existence, for God\u2019s Word tells us that \u201cIf we say that we have no sin, we deceive ourselves, and there is no truth in us. But if we confess our sins to God, He will keep His promise and do what is right: He will forgive us our sins and purify us from all our wrongdoing.\u201d (1 John 1:1-10). \u201cThe blood of Jesus, His Son, purifies us from every sin\u201d.\n\nYou are ruled either by Satan or by God; you are a slave to sin or a servant of God. If sin controls your life, do not deny it, but cry out to God. He will set you free through Jesus Christ who came to this world to save sinners, to break the power of Satan and sin over us. He is our Saviour. You are in the presence of a holy God who knows all the secrets, the hidden thoughts and actions of your life. It is impossible to hide yourself and actions from God, for \u201cGod made our ears \u2013 can\u2019t He hear? He made our eyes \u2013 can\u2019t He see?\u201d (Ps. 94:9).\n\nThe Lord keeps close watch over the whole world to give strength to those whose hearts are loyal to Him.\u201d (2 Chron.16:9).\n\nHe watches every step men take. There is no darkness dark enough to hide a sinner from God.\u201d (Job 34:21,22).\n\nBut [[Jesus]] did not trust Himself to them, because He knew them all.\u201d (John 2:24).\n\nTherefore \u201chappy are those whose sins are forgiven, whose wrongs are pardoned. Happy is the man whom the Lord does not accuse of doing wrong and who is free from all deceit.\u201d (Ps. 32:1-2).\n\n== THE SINNERS HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The sinners heart P1.jpg|alt=This picture shows the heart of a wordly sinful man or woman, described in the Bible as a sinner.|thumb|The Sinners Heart]]\n'''This picture shows the heart of a worldly sinful man or woman, described in the Bible as a sinner.'''\nBelow the head in this picture, the heart of man can be seen occupied by various animals which speak of the many different sins in the human heart, as the heart is the centre and breeding place of our sins. God tells us by the mouth of His prophet Jeremiah, that \u201cNobody can understand the human heart. There is nothing else so deceitful; it is too sick to be healed.\u201d (Jeremiah 17:9)\n\nJesus Himself confirms this by saying, \u201cFor from the inside, from a person\u2019s heart, come the evil ideas which lead him to do immoral things; to rob, kill, commit adultery, be greedy, and do all sorts of evil things; deceit, indecency, jealousy, slander, pride, and folly \u2013 all these evil things come from inside a person and make him unclean\u201d (Mark 7:21-23)\n\nThe bleary, red eyes speak of drunkenness.  \u201cDon\u2019t let wine tempt you, even though it is rich red, though it sparkles in the cup, and it goes down smoothly. The next morning you will feel as if you have been bitten by a poisonous snake.\u201d (Proverbs 23:31-32)\n\nDifferent animals and signs used in the pictures reminds us of the following sins:\n\n=== The [[Peacock]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nWhile the beauty of the peacock is admired by everybody, here in the heart of man, it speaks of the sin of pride.\n\n=== The [[goat]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe goat represents bodily desires, immorality, adultery.\n\n=== The [[pig]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe pig speaks of the sins of drunkenness and gluttony. It is a dirty animal eagerly swallowing up everything in its way, clean or dirty, and in the same way a sinful heart devours every immoral suggestion, expression, picture, literature, etc.\n\n=== The [[tortoise]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe tortoise speaks of laziness, sluggishness to obey and witchcraft. \u201cA lazy man who refuses to work is only killing himself, all he does is think about what he would like to have.\u201d  (Prov. 21:25,26).\n\n=== The [[leopard]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe leopard is a very savage and cruel beast. Hatred, anger and a bad temper often rule the heart of man and many times lead to murder. \u201cKeep your temper under control; it is foolish to harbour a grudge.\u201d (Eccl. 7:9)\n\n=== The [[snake]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe snake represents the devil who is very deceitful, clever and misleading, and does everything possible to destroy our relationship with God.\n\n=== The [[frog]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe frog speaks here of the sins of greediness and the love of money which is the source of all evil (1 Tim. 6:10). Certain frogs in the Congo have been seen eating ants by the hundreds until they burst and died.\n\n=== [[Satan]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nSatan is the father of all lies, and is the one who persuades us to sin, and then he rules our hearts.\n\n=== The [[star]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe star speaks of the conscience in the heart of every man. Even in the bad heart the conscience is still there, but is being ignored, and cannot therefore help this person.\n\n=== The eye of [[God]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe eye of God sees everything that goes on in the heart. Nothing can be hidden from His flaming eye, and therefore He knows and sees all the secret thoughts and intentions of the heart. Whether you do your evil deeds in the darkest night, in the thickest forest, in the deepest ditch or wherever it may be, God sees it.\n\n=== The little tongues of fire[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe little tongues of fire round about the heart show the love of God surrounding the sinful heart. While God hates sin He loves man and does not want the death of a sinner, but that he should turn away from his sins and live. Jesus came to save sinners. There is great joy in heaven over one sinner that repents (Luke 15:7). The little tongues also speak of the blood of Jesus Christ, \u201cthe Lamb of God, who takes away the sin of the world.\u201d (John 1:29).\n\n=== The [[angel]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe angel represents the Word of God. God wants to speak to those who have been deceived and are carrying heavy loads of sin, so that they may turn from their sinful ways and let the light and love of God come into their hearts.\n\n=== The [[dove]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe dove is a sign of the Holy Spirit, the Spirit who reveals the truth about God, about sin and what is right, and about God\u2019s judgement (John 15:26).\n\n== THE HEART CONVINCED OF SIN[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The heart convinced of sin P2.jpg|alt=The Heart convinced of sin|center|thumb|The Heart convinced of sin]]\n'''This picture shows the heart of a man who is sorry for his sins and is beginning to look for God.'''\n\nHere we see the sinner beginning to take notice of the message of God and to open his heart to the love of God. The Holy Spirit begins to shine into the dark and sinful heart. The light of God comes into his heart to drive all darkness away. When God\u2019s light comes in, darkness has to go. Sin, described here by all the various animals, has to go. Therefore, dear reader, allow Jesus, the Light of the world, to come into your heart, and darkness and the evil actions of darkness must leave the heart, as shown in this picture.\n\nJesus said, \u201cI am the light of the world. Whoever follows me will have the light of life and will never walk in darkness.\u201d (John 8:12).\n\nYour heart is intended to be God\u2019s house, God\u2019s temple. He wants to live in it, make it beautiful, fill it with light, love and joy. Jesus not only came to forgive us our sins, but He came to deliver us and set us free from the power and domination of sin.\n\n\u201cIf the Son ([[Jesus]]) sets you free, then you will be really free.\u201d (John 8:36).\n\n== THE REPENTING HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The repenting heart P3.jpg|alt=The repenting heart|center|thumb|The repenting heart]]\n'''This picture shows us the heart of someone who is really serious about finding the right relationship with God.'''\n\nAs he sees the cross which the angel, the Word of God, shows to him, it breaks his now sorry heart, and he is moved with deep, heartfelt regret and sorrow over his many sins. As he sees the great love of God expressed in Christ Jesus, this love melts his heart, especially as he begins to realise that Jesus Christ, the Son of God, came to take away his many sins, as He was willing to die in his place on the cross.\n\nThe love and peace of God enter his heart as he begins to realise that \u201cthe blood of Jesus, His Son, purifies us from every sin.\u201d (1 John 1:7).\n\n\u201cCreate a pure heart in me, O God, and put a new and loyal spirit in me.\u201d (Psalm 51:10).\n\nAgain God\u2019s Word says, \u201cI am pleased with those who are humble and repentant, who fear me and obey me.\u201d (Isa. 66:2).\n\nThe Holy Spirit makes the words of Jesus clear to him, \u201cCourage, my son (daughter)! Your sins are forgiven.\u201d (Matt. 9:2).\n\n== DYING WITH CHRIST[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:Dying with Christ P4.jpg|alt=Dying with Christ|center|thumb|Dying with Christ]]\n'''This picture speaks of a Christian who has found perfect peace and eternal salvation through the death of our Lord and Saviour, Jesus Christ.'''\n\nThis person boasts in nothing else except \u201conly about the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ; for by means of His cross the world is dead to us, and we are dead to the world.\u201d (Gal. 6:14). Jesus died on the cross so that we too, might \u201cdie to sin and live for righteousness\u201d (1 Peter 2:24); a Christian dead to the world. We are commanded to \u201clet the Spirit direct our lives, and we will not satisfy the desires of the human nature.\u201d (Gal. 5:16,25).\n\nDo you declare openly that you have given your heart to Jesus Christ, by what you say and do? Or are you ashamed to let others know? Jesus said, \u201cIf anyone declares publicly that he belongs to me, I will do the same for him before my Father in heaven. But if anyone rejects me publicly, I will reject him before my Father in heaven.\u201d(Matt. 10:32,33). Jesus also said, \u201cWhoever does not take up his cross and follow in my steps is not fit to be my disciple.\u201d (Matt. 10:38). Happy are those who find protection in the Rock, Jesus Christ!\n\n== THE TEMPLE OF GOD[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The Temple of God P5.jpg|alt=The temple of God|center|thumb|The temple of God]]\n'''This picture shows the clean and purified heart of the sinner who has been saved by God\u2019s grace and mercy.'''\n\nThe heart has now become a true temple of God. Sin has been driven out. Instead of the various animals controlled by Satan, the father of lies, we see the Holy Spirit, the Spirit of Truth, living in the heart. Instead of being the breeding place of sin, the heart has become a beautiful, fruit-bearing tree or garden, bearing the fruits of the Spirit, such as love, joy, peace, humility, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness, self control and others which are acceptable and pleasing to God and man (Gal. 5:22-23). He has now become a fruit- bearing branch of the real vine \u2013 our Lord Jesus Christ. The secret of this fruit-bearing is that he remains united with Christ, and Christ and His words remain in him (John 15:1-10).\n\n\u201cHappy are the pure in heart; they will see God!\u201d (Matt.5:8). King David knew that the greatest battle was taking place in his own heart and recognizing his deep spiritual need, prayed, \u201cCreate a pure heart in me, O God, and put a new and loyal spirit in me.\u201d (Psalm 51:10). Nobody is able to purify his own heart, or to create a clean heart, unless through truly repenting he comes to God as David did, asking God to create a pure heart in him.\n\n== THE TEMPTED AND DEVIDED HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The tempted and devided heart P6.jpg|alt=The tempted and divided heart|center|thumb|The tempted and divided heart]]\n'''This is the sad picture of one who has fallen back into his old ways. One eye is starting to close, showing that he is beginning to grow cold and sleepy in his relationship with God.'''\n\nThe light inside has grown dim, and the pictures in his heart, showing his readiness to suffer with Christ, have fallen and are no longer upright. He is surrounded by temptations to which he is slowly giving in instead of resisting them. Instead of listening to God\u2019s voice he now begins to listen to the devil\u2019s cunning suggestions and false promises. Although he may still be a church-goer, hiding his desires for the things of the world under a form of religion, the love for God has grown cold in his heart. Obey the warnings of our Lord Jesus when He says, \u201cKeep watch and pray that you will not fall into temptation.\u201d (Matt. 26:41). \u201cWhoever thinks he is standing firm had better be careful that he does not fall.\u201d (1Cor.10:12). We must put on all the armour that God gives us, so that we will be able to stand up against the devil\u2019s evil tricks. (Eph. 6:11-18).\n\n== THE FALLEN OR STUBBORN HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The fallen or stubborn heart P7.jpg|alt=The fallen or stubborn heart|center|thumb|The fallen or stubborn heart]]\n'''This picture reveals the condition of the person who has fallen completely into his old ways again, in spite of what God did for him.'''\n\nAfter this person was once in God\u2019s light and had tasted heaven\u2019s gift and received his share of the Holy Spirit, he has abandoned his faith. (Heb. 6:4). Jesus Himself described the backsliders\u2019 condition when He said, \u201cWhen an evil spirit goes out of a person, it travels over dry country looking for a place to rest. If it can\u2019t find one, it says to itself, \u2018I will go back to my house.\u2019 So it goes back and finds the house clean and tidy. Then it goes out and brings seven other spirits even worse than itself, and they come and live there. So when it is all over, that person is in a worse state than he was at the beginning.\u201d (Luke 11:24-26).\n\n\u201cWhat happened to them shows that the proverbs are true; \u2018A dog goes back to what it has vomited\u2019 and \u2018A pig that has been washed goes back to roll in the mud.\u2019 \u201d (2 Peter 2:22). If you continue to be stubborn, and love darkness rather than light, there is no hope, no help, because you are choosing death instead of life \u2013 \u201csin pays its wage - death.\u201d (Rom. 6:23).\n\n== THE SINNERS JUDGEMENT[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The sinners judgement P8.jpg|alt=The sinners judgement|center|thumb|The sinners judgement]]\n'''Here we find the stubborn sinner who did not want to open his heart to God again.'''\n\nThe false pleasures of sin have disappeared, and the awful reality of the high and dreadful cost of sin now has to be faced. The agonies of hell are becoming real to him. Although he now longs to pray, he finds he cannot communicate with God whose love he has rejected for so long. His friends are afraid to stand at his bedside, and their empty words of comfort cannot help him now. His riches can neither lengthen his life, nor save his soul, nor reduce the agony of his soul.\n\nHe begins to realise that \u201cit is a terrifying thing to fall into the hands of the living God!\u201d (Heb. 10:31). He had hoped to give his life to God when it suited him. This dying sinner who rejected the forgiveness and love of God during his lifetime now has to hear the voice of his Judge, the Saviour whom he rejected saying: \u201cAway from me, you that are under God\u2019s curse! Away to the eternal fire which has been prepared for the devil and his angels!\u201d (Matt. 25:41).\n\n\u201cEveryone must die once, and after that be judged by God.\u201d (Heb. 9:27).\n\n== THE VICTORIOUS HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The victorious heart P9.jpg|alt=The victorious heart|center|thumb|The victorious heart]]\n'''This picture shows a Christian who remains faithful and wins the victory over painful tests and temptations.'''\n\nWhile he is tempted on all sides, he remains firm and holds out to the end, being victorious through Jesus Christ. He has not only entered the Christian race, but he is continuing in it, running with determination, \u201ckeeping his eyes fixed on Jesus, on whom our faith depends from beginning to end.\u201d (Heb. 12:1,2). He remembers the words of Jesus. \u201cHappy are you when people insult you and persecute you and tell all kinds of evil lies against you because you are my followers. Be happy and glad, for a great reward is kept for you in heaven.\u201d (Matt. 5:11,12).\n\nThis person is ready to meet God, and is like a tree that grows beside a stream; that bears fruit at the right time (Ps. 1:3); like a branch of the real vine, bearing much fruit. He does not know the fear of death, for the perfect love of God, which he has received through the Holy Spirit, has filled his heart.\n\n== THE GLORIOUS HOMEGOING[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The glorious homegoing P10.jpg|alt=The glorious homegoing|center|thumb|The glorious homegoing]]\n'''Jesus said, \u201cI am the resurrection and the life. Whoever believes in me will live, even though he dies; and whoever lives and believes in me will never die.\u201d (John 1:25,26).'''\n\n\u201cWhoever hears my words and believes in Him who sent me has eternal life. He will not be judged, but has already passed from death to life.\u201d (John 5:24). Death holds neither fear nor punishment for the Christian. \u201cDeath is destroyed; victory is complete! Where death is your victory? Where death is your power to hurt?\u2026 Thanks be to God who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ!\u201d(1 Cor. 15:54-57)\n\nA person who has lived and walked with God is not afraid of death. When the time comes for him to die, he will go gladly, as the Apostle Paul puts it, \u201cI want very much to leave this life and to be with Christ, which is a far better thing.\u201d (Phil. 1:23)\n\n\u201cThen I heard a voice from heaven saying, \u2018Write this: Happy are those who from now on die in the service of the Lord!\u2019 \u2018Yes indeed!\u2019 answers the Spirit. \u2018They will enjoy rest from their hard work, because the results of their service go with them.\u201d (Rev. 14:13).\n\n== Prayer[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n''\u201cHe watches every step men take. There is no darkness dark enough to hide a sinner from God\u201d Job 34:21-22''\n\n''\u201cSo then, submit to God. Resist the devil, and he will run away from you. Come close to God, and He will come near you.\u201d James 4:7-8''\n\n''\u201cFor this is how God loved the world: He gave his one and only Son, so that everyone who believes in him will not perish but have eternal life. John 3:16''\n\n'''Let us pray:''' \n\n'''My father in heaven, I am really sorry for the sins in my heart. I want your light to shine into my heart, to remove all the bad things that are ruining my life. Please give me a new heart, and fill my heart with your own presence. Please help me to live a life that will be pleasing to you, and that will help me to be the person I should be. I ask this in the Name of Jesus. AMEN'''\n\n''\u201chappy are those whose sins are forgiven, whose wrongs are pardoned. Happy is the man whom the Lord does not accuse of doing wrong and who is free from all deceit\u201d Ps. 32:1-2''\u2003\n", "text_old": "{{Unreferenced|date=April 2020}}\n'''THE HEART OF MAN OR THE SPIRITUAL HEART MIRROR'''\n\n(''An Allegorical Representation in Ten Pictures'')\n\nTHE HEART OF MAN BOOKLET\n\nThis Booklet originated in France in 1732, was revised and rewritten for the mission fields of Africa by Rev. J.R. [https://globalchristiancenter.com/missions-inspiration/22542-memories-of-a-godly-missionary Gschwend]  in 1929, and has subsequently been translated and printed under copyright in over 538 indigenous languages by [http://www.angp.org ALL NATIONS GOSPEL PUBLISHERS] who are distributing it today in 127 mission countries. People of all languages, classes and religions are being led by this booklet to experience the deep spiritual truth and significance of God\u2019s message to mankind as expressed by the prophet [[Ezekiel]] 586 years before [[Christ]], \u201cI will give you a new heart and a new mind then you will be my people, and I will be your [[God]]!\u201d Ezekiel 36:26-28.\n\nThe text used is from the compact (or shorter) format of the booklet. Different formats of the booklet including the complete booklet in .pdf format can be downloaded free of charge.\n\nQuotes from [[Scripture]] was taken from [[Good News Bible|The Good News Bible]] \n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|ALL NATIONS GOSPEL PUBLISHERS\n|[[www.angp.org]]\n|-\n|Text written:\n|1929\n|-\n|Written by:\n|Rev. J.R. Gschwend\n|-\n|Text and pictures owned by:\n|ALL NATIONS GOSPEL PUBLISHERS\n|-\n|Number of translations available\n|481\n|-\n|Latest mission report:\n|<nowiki>http://www.angp.org/fileadmin/angp/sites/pdf/AN_englisch_aktuell.pdf</nowiki>\n|-\n|Download all booklets from:\n|[[Www.angp-hb.co.za|http://www.angp-hb.co.za]]\n|-\n|Download Booklet Format:\n|https://angp-hb.co.za/booklet-format/\n|-\n|Download Cell phone Format:\n|https://angp-hb.co.za/cellphone-format/\n|-\n|Download Print Format:\n|https://angp-hb.co.za/print-format/\n|-\n|Download Compact Format:\n|https://angp-hb.co.za/compact-format/\n|}\n\n== THE HEART OF MAN: THE TEMPLE OF GOD OR THE WORKSHOP OF SATAN ==\n'''(1 John 3:4-10)'''\n[[File:The heart of man booklet.jpg|alt=The Heart of man|thumb|The Heart of man booklet]]\nAs you read this book, please bear in mind that it is like a mirror in which you will be able to see yourself. Whether you are a heathen or a Christian, one who does not believe in [[Christ]] or a backslider, you will see yourself as [[God]] sees you. \u201cMan looks at the outward appearance, but I look at the heart.\u201d (1 Sam. 16:7). God sees us as we really are.\n\n[[Satan]] is the father of all lies. He is the prince of darkness and god of this world, who disguises himself as an angel of light to lead men and women the wrong way. In these days, as in times past, there are many false [[apostles]] who disguise themselves, pretending to be apostles of Christ. And no wonder, for Satan himself is transformed (disguised) into an angel of light (2 Corinthians 11:13,14). Satan, the god of this world, keeps people in the dark so that they cannot see that God loves them or that Jesus died to save them (2 Cor. 4:4). All sinners and those who do not believe are spiritually dead and blind concerning God. They are ruled by the evil of this world (Eph. 2:1-2). Unless their eyes are opened in some way to their lost condition, they are heading for eternal destruction. The person who says, \u201cI have never sinned\u201d is deceiving himself. For \u201cThe Son of God appeared for this very reason, to destroy what the devil had done.\u201d (1 John 3:8). \u201cSo then, submit to God. Resist the devil, and he will run away from you. Come near to God, and He will come near to you.\u201d (James 4:7,8)\n\nAs you read this book and study its pictures, you will be able to see your own heart. Allow God\u2019s searchlight to show you the condition of your heart. Acknowledge your sins and do not deny their existence, for God\u2019s Word tells us that \u201cIf we say that we have no sin, we deceive ourselves, and there is no truth in us. But if we confess our sins to God, He will keep His promise and do what is right: He will forgive us our sins and purify us from all our wrongdoing.\u201d (1 John 1:1-10). \u201cThe blood of Jesus, His Son, purifies us from every sin\u201d.\n\nYou are ruled either by Satan or by God; you are a slave to sin or a servant of God. If sin controls your life, do not deny it, but cry out to God. He will set you free through Jesus Christ who came to this world to save sinners, to break the power of Satan and sin over us. He is our Saviour. You are in the presence of a holy God who knows all the secrets, the hidden thoughts and actions of your life. It is impossible to hide yourself and actions from God, for \u201cGod made our ears \u2013 can\u2019t He hear? He made our eyes \u2013 can\u2019t He see?\u201d (Ps. 94:9).\n\nThe Lord keeps close watch over the whole world to give strength to those whose hearts are loyal to Him.\u201d (2 Chron.16:9).\n\nHe watches every step men take. There is no darkness dark enough to hide a sinner from God.\u201d (Job 34:21,22).\n\nBut [[Jesus]] did not trust Himself to them, because He knew them all.\u201d (John 2:24).\n\nTherefore \u201chappy are those whose sins are forgiven, whose wrongs are pardoned. Happy is the man whom the Lord does not accuse of doing wrong and who is free from all deceit.\u201d (Ps. 32:1-2).\n\n== THE SINNERS HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The sinners heart P1.jpg|alt=This picture shows the heart of a wordly sinful man or woman, described in the Bible as a sinner.|thumb|The Sinners Heart]]\n'''This picture shows the heart of a worldly sinful man or woman, described in the Bible as a sinner.'''\nBelow the head in this picture, the heart of man can be seen occupied by various animals which speak of the many different sins in the human heart, as the heart is the centre and breeding place of our sins. God tells us by the mouth of His prophet Jeremiah, that \u201cNobody can understand the human heart. There is nothing else so deceitful; it is too sick to be healed.\u201d (Jeremiah 17:9)\n\nJesus Himself confirms this by saying, \u201cFor from the inside, from a person\u2019s heart, come the evil ideas which lead him to do immoral things; to rob, kill, commit adultery, be greedy, and do all sorts of evil things; deceit, indecency, jealousy, slander, pride, and folly \u2013 all these evil things come from inside a person and make him unclean\u201d (Mark 7:21-23)\n\nThe bleary, red eyes speak of drunkenness.  \u201cDon\u2019t let wine tempt you, even though it is rich red, though it sparkles in the cup, and it goes down smoothly. The next morning you will feel as if you have been bitten by a poisonous snake.\u201d (Proverbs 23:31-32)\n\nDifferent animals and signs used in the pictures reminds us of the following sins:\n\n=== The [[Peacock]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nWhile the beauty of the peacock is admired by everybody, here in the heart of man, it speaks of the sin of pride.\n\n=== The [[goat]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe goat represents bodily desires, immorality, adultery.\n\n=== The [[pig]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe pig speaks of the sins of drunkenness and gluttony. It is a dirty animal eagerly swallowing up everything in its way, clean or dirty, and in the same way a sinful heart devours every immoral suggestion, expression, picture, literature, etc.\n\n=== The [[tortoise]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe tortoise speaks of laziness, sluggishness to obey and witchcraft. \u201cA lazy man who refuses to work is only killing himself, all he does is think about what he would like to have.\u201d  (Prov. 21:25,26).\n\n=== The [[leopard]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe leopard is a very savage and cruel beast. Hatred, anger and a bad temper often rule the heart of man and many times lead to murder. \u201cKeep your temper under control; it is foolish to harbour a grudge.\u201d (Eccl. 7:9)\n\n=== The [[snake]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe snake represents the devil who is very deceitful, clever and misleading, and does everything possible to destroy our relationship with God.\n\n=== The [[frog]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe frog speaks here of the sins of greediness and the love of money which is the source of all evil (1 Tim. 6:10). Certain frogs in the Congo have been seen eating ants by the hundreds until they burst and died.\n\n=== [[Satan]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nSatan is the father of all lies, and is the one who persuades us to sin, and then he rules our hearts.\n\n=== The [[star]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe star speaks of the conscience in the heart of every man. Even in the bad heart the conscience is still there, but is being ignored, and cannot therefore help this person.\n\n=== The eye of [[God]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe eye of God sees everything that goes on in the heart. Nothing can be hidden from His flaming eye, and therefore He knows and sees all the secret thoughts and intentions of the heart. Whether you do your evil deeds in the darkest night, in the thickest forest, in the deepest ditch or wherever it may be, God sees it.\n\n=== The little tongues of fire[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe little tongues of fire round about the heart show the love of God surrounding the sinful heart. While God hates sin He loves man and does not want the death of a sinner, but that he should turn away from his sins and live. Jesus came to save sinners. There is great joy in heaven over one sinner that repents (Luke 15:7). The little tongues also speak of the blood of Jesus Christ, \u201cthe Lamb of God, who takes away the sin of the world.\u201d (John 1:29).\n\n=== The [[angel]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe angel represents the Word of God. God wants to speak to those who have been deceived and are carrying heavy loads of sin, so that they may turn from their sinful ways and let the light and love of God come into their hearts.\n\n=== The [[dove]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe dove is a sign of the Holy Spirit, the Spirit who reveals the truth about God, about sin and what is right, and about God\u2019s judgement (John 15:26).\n\n== THE HEART CONVINCED OF SIN[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The heart convinced of sin P2.jpg|alt=The Heart convinced of sin|center|thumb|The Heart convinced of sin]]\n'''This picture shows the heart of a man who is sorry for his sins and is beginning to look for God.'''\n\nHere we see the sinner beginning to take notice of the message of God and to open his heart to the love of God. The Holy Spirit begins to shine into the dark and sinful heart. The light of God comes into his heart to drive all darkness away. When God\u2019s light comes in, darkness has to go. Sin, described here by all the various animals, has to go. Therefore, dear reader, allow Jesus, the Light of the world, to come into your heart, and darkness and the evil actions of darkness must leave the heart, as shown in this picture.\n\nJesus said, \u201cI am the light of the world. Whoever follows me will have the light of life and will never walk in darkness.\u201d (John 8:12).\n\nYour heart is intended to be God\u2019s house, God\u2019s temple. He wants to live in it, make it beautiful, fill it with light, love and joy. Jesus not only came to forgive us our sins, but He came to deliver us and set us free from the power and domination of sin.\n\n\u201cIf the Son ([[Jesus]]) sets you free, then you will be really free.\u201d (John 8:36).\n\n== THE REPENTING HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The repenting heart P3.jpg|alt=The repenting heart|center|thumb|The repenting heart]]\n'''This picture shows us the heart of someone who is really serious about finding the right relationship with God.'''\n\nAs he sees the cross which the angel, the Word of God, shows to him, it breaks his now sorry heart, and he is moved with deep, heartfelt regret and sorrow over his many sins. As he sees the great love of God expressed in Christ Jesus, this love melts his heart, especially as he begins to realise that Jesus Christ, the Son of God, came to take away his many sins, as He was willing to die in his place on the cross.\n\nThe love and peace of God enter his heart as he begins to realise that \u201cthe blood of Jesus, His Son, purifies us from every sin.\u201d (1 John 1:7).\n\n\u201cCreate a pure heart in me, O God, and put a new and loyal spirit in me.\u201d (Psalm 51:10).\n\nAgain God\u2019s Word says, \u201cI am pleased with those who are humble and repentant, who fear me and obey me.\u201d (Isa. 66:2).\n\nThe Holy Spirit makes the words of Jesus clear to him, \u201cCourage, my son (daughter)! Your sins are forgiven.\u201d (Matt. 9:2).\n\n== DYING WITH CHRIST[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:Dying with Christ P4.jpg|alt=Dying with Christ|center|thumb|Dying with Christ]]\n'''This picture speaks of a Christian who has found perfect peace and eternal salvation through the death of our Lord and Saviour, Jesus Christ.'''\n\nThis person boasts in nothing else except \u201conly about the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ; for by means of His cross the world is dead to us, and we are dead to the world.\u201d (Gal. 6:14). Jesus died on the cross so that we too, might \u201cdie to sin and live for righteousness\u201d (1 Peter 2:24); a Christian dead to the world. We are commanded to \u201clet the Spirit direct our lives, and we will not satisfy the desires of the human nature.\u201d (Gal. 5:16,25).\n\nDo you declare openly that you have given your heart to Jesus Christ, by what you say and do? Or are you ashamed to let others know? Jesus said, \u201cIf anyone declares publicly that he belongs to me, I will do the same for him before my Father in heaven. But if anyone rejects me publicly, I will reject him before my Father in heaven.\u201d(Matt. 10:32,33). Jesus also said, \u201cWhoever does not take up his cross and follow in my steps is not fit to be my disciple.\u201d (Matt. 10:38). Happy are those who find protection in the Rock, Jesus Christ!\n\n== THE TEMPLE OF GOD[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The Temple of God P5.jpg|alt=The temple of God|center|thumb|The temple of God]]\n'''This picture shows the clean and purified heart of the sinner who has been saved by God\u2019s grace and mercy.'''\n\nThe heart has now become a true temple of God. Sin has been driven out. Instead of the various animals controlled by Satan, the father of lies, we see the Holy Spirit, the Spirit of Truth, living in the heart. Instead of being the breeding place of sin, the heart has become a beautiful, fruit-bearing tree or garden, bearing the fruits of the Spirit, such as love, joy, peace, humility, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness, self control and others which are acceptable and pleasing to God and man (Gal. 5:22-23). He has now become a fruit- bearing branch of the real vine \u2013 our Lord Jesus Christ. The secret of this fruit-bearing is that he remains united with Christ, and Christ and His words remain in him (John 15:1-10).\n\n\u201cHappy are the pure in heart; they will see God!\u201d (Matt.5:8). King David knew that the greatest battle was taking place in his own heart and recognizing his deep spiritual need, prayed, \u201cCreate a pure heart in me, O God, and put a new and loyal spirit in me.\u201d (Psalm 51:10). Nobody is able to purify his own heart, or to create a clean heart, unless through truly repenting he comes to God as David did, asking God to create a pure heart in him.\n\n== THE TEMPTED AND DEVIDED HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The tempted and devided heart P6.jpg|alt=The tempted and divided heart|center|thumb|The tempted and divided heart]]\n'''This is the sad picture of one who has fallen back into his old ways. One eye is starting to close, showing that he is beginning to grow cold and sleepy in his relationship with God.'''\n\nThe light inside has grown dim, and the pictures in his heart, showing his readiness to suffer with Christ, have fallen and are no longer upright. He is surrounded by temptations to which he is slowly giving in instead of resisting them. Instead of listening to God\u2019s voice he now begins to listen to the devil\u2019s cunning suggestions and false promises. Although he may still be a church-goer, hiding his desires for the things of the world under a form of religion, the love for God has grown cold in his heart. Obey the warnings of our Lord Jesus when He says, \u201cKeep watch and pray that you will not fall into temptation.\u201d (Matt. 26:41). \u201cWhoever thinks he is standing firm had better be careful that he does not fall.\u201d (1Cor.10:12). We must put on all the armour that God gives us, so that we will be able to stand up against the devil\u2019s evil tricks. (Eph. 6:11-18).\n\n== THE FALLEN OR STUBBORN HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The fallen or stubborn heart P7.jpg|alt=The fallen or stubborn heart|center|thumb|The fallen or stubborn heart]]\n'''This picture reveals the condition of the person who has fallen completely into his old ways again, in spite of what God did for him.'''\n\nAfter this person was once in God\u2019s light and had tasted heaven\u2019s gift and received his share of the Holy Spirit, he has abandoned his faith. (Heb. 6:4). Jesus Himself described the backsliders\u2019 condition when He said, \u201cWhen an evil spirit goes out of a person, it travels over dry country looking for a place to rest. If it can\u2019t find one, it says to itself, \u2018I will go back to my house.\u2019 So it goes back and finds the house clean and tidy. Then it goes out and brings seven other spirits even worse than itself, and they come and live there. So when it is all over, that person is in a worse state than he was at the beginning.\u201d (Luke 11:24-26).\n\n\u201cWhat happened to them shows that the proverbs are true; \u2018A dog goes back to what it has vomited\u2019 and \u2018A pig that has been washed goes back to roll in the mud.\u2019 \u201d (2 Peter 2:22). If you continue to be stubborn, and love darkness rather than light, there is no hope, no help, because you are choosing death instead of life \u2013 \u201csin pays its wage - death.\u201d (Rom. 6:23).\n\n== THE SINNERS JUDGEMENT[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The sinners judgement P8.jpg|alt=The sinners judgement|center|thumb|The sinners judgement]]\n'''Here we find the stubborn sinner who did not want to open his heart to God again.'''\n\nThe false pleasures of sin have disappeared, and the awful reality of the high and dreadful cost of sin now has to be faced. The agonies of hell are becoming real to him. Although he now longs to pray, he finds he cannot communicate with God whose love he has rejected for so long. His friends are afraid to stand at his bedside, and their empty words of comfort cannot help him now. His riches can neither lengthen his life, nor save his soul, nor reduce the agony of his soul.\n\nHe begins to realise that \u201cit is a terrifying thing to fall into the hands of the living God!\u201d (Heb. 10:31). He had hoped to give his life to God when it suited him. This dying sinner who rejected the forgiveness and love of God during his lifetime now has to hear the voice of his Judge, the Saviour whom he rejected saying: \u201cAway from me, you that are under God\u2019s curse! Away to the eternal fire which has been prepared for the devil and his angels!\u201d (Matt. 25:41).\n\n\u201cEveryone must die once, and after that be judged by God.\u201d (Heb. 9:27).\n\n== THE VICTORIOUS HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The victorious heart P9.jpg|alt=The victorious heart|center|thumb|The victorious heart]]\n'''This picture shows a Christian who remains faithful and wins the victory over painful tests and temptations.'''\n\nWhile he is tempted on all sides, he remains firm and holds out to the end, being victorious through Jesus Christ. He has not only entered the Christian race, but he is continuing in it, running with determination, \u201ckeeping his eyes fixed on Jesus, on whom our faith depends from beginning to end.\u201d (Heb. 12:1,2). He remembers the words of Jesus. \u201cHappy are you when people insult you and persecute you and tell all kinds of evil lies against you because you are my followers. Be happy and glad, for a great reward is kept for you in heaven.\u201d (Matt. 5:11,12).\n\nThis person is ready to meet God, and is like a tree that grows beside a stream; that bears fruit at the right time (Ps. 1:3); like a branch of the real vine, bearing much fruit. He does not know the fear of death, for the perfect love of God, which he has received through the Holy Spirit, has filled his heart.\n\n== THE GLORIOUS HOMEGOING[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The glorious homegoing P10.jpg|alt=The glorious homegoing|center|thumb|The glorious homegoing]]\n'''Jesus said, \u201cI am the resurrection and the life. Whoever believes in me will live, even though he dies; and whoever lives and believes in me will never die.\u201d (John 1:25,26).'''\n\n\u201cWhoever hears my words and believes in Him who sent me has eternal life. He will not be judged, but has already passed from death to life.\u201d (John 5:24). Death holds neither fear nor punishment for the Christian. \u201cDeath is destroyed; victory is complete! Where death is your victory? Where death is your power to hurt?\u2026 Thanks be to God who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ!\u201d(1 Cor. 15:54-57)\n\nA person who has lived and walked with God is not afraid of death. When the time comes for him to die, he will go gladly, as the Apostle Paul puts it, \u201cI want very much to leave this life and to be with Christ, which is a far better thing.\u201d (Phil. 1:23)\n\n\u201cThen I heard a voice from heaven saying, \u2018Write this: Happy are those who from now on die in the service of the Lord!\u2019 \u2018Yes indeed!\u2019 answers the Spirit. \u2018They will enjoy rest from their hard work, because the results of their service go with them.\u201d (Rev. 14:13).\n\n== Prayer[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n''\u201cHe watches every step men take. There is no darkness dark enough to hide a sinner from God\u201d Job 34:21-22''\n\n''\u201cSo then, submit to God. Resist the devil, and he will run away from you. Come close to God, and He will come near you.\u201d James 4:7-8''\n\n''\u201cFor this is how God loved the world: He gave his one and only Son, so that everyone who believes in him will not perish but have eternal life. John 3:16''\n\n'''Let us pray:''' \n\n'''My father in heaven, I am really sorry for the sins in my heart. I want your light to shine into my heart, to remove all the bad things that are ruining my life. Please give me a new heart, and fill my heart with your own presence. Please help me to live a life that will be pleasing to you, and that will help me to be the person I should be. I ask this in the Name of Jesus. AMEN'''\n\n''\u201chappy are those whose sins are forgiven, whose wrongs are pardoned. Happy is the man whom the Lord does not accuse of doing wrong and who is free from all deceit\u201d Ps. 32:1-2''\u2003\n", "name_user": "ChristoDorfling", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heart_Book_(All_Nations_Gospel_Publishers)"}
{"title_page": "Sci-Hub", "text_new": "{{short description|Website providing free access to millions of research papers}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name = Sci-Hub\n| logo = File:Scihub raven.png\n| logo_size = 100px\n| logo_caption = \n| logo_alt = Official logo of Sci-Hub depicting black raven drawing with reddish key in mouth\n| screenshot = \n| screenshot_size = <!-- default 300px -->\n| screenshot_alt = \n| url = [https://sci-hub.tw/about sci-hub.tw]<br/>\n[https://sci-hub.si/about sci-hub.si]<br/>[https://sci-hub.uno/about sci-hub.uno]<br/>[https://sci-hub.ren/about sci-hub.ren]\n| ip = <!-- Not currently accessible via any IP address -->\n| commercial = No\n| type = [[File sharing]]\n| registration = Not required\n| language = {{ubl|English|Russian{{efn|Article viewer only appears in Russian}} }}\n| num_users = \n| content_license = Hosts material without regard to copyright\n| owner = \n| author = [[Alexandra Elbakyan]]\n| editor = \n| launch_date = {{start date and age|2011|04|16|df=yes}}<ref name=\"icann\">{{cite web|title=sci-hub.org|url=https://whois.icann.org/en/lookup?name=sci-hub.org|website=ICANN WHOIS|accessdate=28 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180309140050/https://whois.icann.org/en/lookup?name=sci-hub.org|archive-date=9 March 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| alexa = <!--do not fill: too hard to evaluate due to it having multiple domains and continuously switching domains-->\n| current_status = Active\n}}\n{{File sharing sidebar}}\n'''Sci-Hub''' is a website that provides free access to millions of [[academic paper|research papers]] and books, [[copyright infringement|without regard to copyright]],<ref name=\"eLife\"/> by bypassing publishers' [[paywall]]s in various ways.<ref name=\"eLife\"/><ref name=Bohannon/><ref name=\"Elbakyan2017\" />\n\nSci-Hub was founded by [[Alexandra Elbakyan]] in 2011 in [[Kazakhstan]] in response to the high cost of research papers behind paywalls. The site is extensively used worldwide.<ref name=\"eLife\" /><ref name=Bohannon/> In January 2020, the site's owners said that it contained 78 million academic articles and served approximately 400,000 requests per day.<ref name=\"roskomsvoboda\">{{cite web|url=https://roskomsvoboda.org/49416/|title=Sci-Hub \u043e\u0442\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043b \u0432\u043e\u0441\u044c\u043c\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0435|website=Roskomsvoboda.org|date=6 September 2019|access-date=2019-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191021170135/https://roskomsvoboda.org/49416/|archive-date=21 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The number of articles claimed is frequently updated on the site's home page, being over 81 million in early March 2020.\n\nSci-Hub and Elbakyan were sued twice for [[copyright infringement]] in the United States in 2015 and 2017, and lost both cases, leading to loss of some of its Internet [[domain name]]s.<ref name=Chawla/>  The site has cycled through different domain names since then.<ref name=\"eLife\">{{Cite journal |last=Himmelstein |first=Daniel S |last2=Romero |first2=Ariel Rodriguez |last3=Levernier |first3=Jacob G |last4=Munro |first4=Thomas Anthony |last5=McLaughlin |first5=Stephen Reid |last6=Greshake Tzovaras |first6=Bastian |last7=Greene |first7=Casey S |title=Sci-Hub provides access to nearly all scholarly literature|journal=eLife |volume=7 |doi=10.7554/eLife.32822 |issn=2050-084X |pmc=5832410 |pmid=29424689|year=2018 }}</ref>\n\nSci-Hub has been lauded by some<ref name=WaPo/> in the [[Scientific community|scientific]], academic, and publishing communities<ref name=\":7\" /> for providing access to knowledge generated by the scientific community. Others have criticized it for violating copyright,<ref name=Bohannon/><ref name=\":4\"/> threatening the economic viability of publishers,<ref name=shadowill/> potentially compromising universities' [[network security]] and jeopardizing legitimate access to papers by university staff.<ref name=RussellSanchez/>\n\n==History==\n[[File:Scihub Feb 2016 pop-adjusted.png|thumb|300px|Number of papers downloaded from Sci-Hub per capita by country (September 2015 to February 2016)<ref name=\"datadryad.org\">{{Cite book |last1=Bohannon|first1=John|last2=Elbakyan|first2=Alexandra |title= Data from: Who's downloading pirated papers? Everyone |publisher= Dryad Digital Repository|doi= 10.5061/dryad.q447c |date=2016-04-28|type=Data Set|chapter=Open access}}</ref><ref name=Bohannon/>]]\nSci-Hub was created by [[Alexandra Elbakyan]], who was born in [[Kazakhstan]] in 1988.<ref name=BohannonBio/>  Elbakyan earned her undergraduate degree at [[Satbayev Kazakh National Technical University|Kazakh National Technical University]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Lifeboat Foundation Bios: Alexandra A. Elbakyan|url=http://lifeboat.com/ex/bios.alexandra.a.elbakyan|publisher=Lifeboat Foundation|accessdate=15 February 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100507022228/http://lifeboat.com/ex/bios.alexandra.a.elbakyan|archivedate=7 May 2010|df=}}</ref> studying information technology, then worked for a year for a computer security firm in Moscow, then joined a research team at the [[University of Freiburg]] in Germany in 2010 that was working on a [[brain\u2013computer interface]].<ref name=BohannonBio/> She found the lab dull and became interested in [[transhumanism]].<ref name=BohannonBio/> After attending a transhumanism conference in the United States, Elbakyan spent her remaining time in the country doing a research internship at [[Georgia Institute of Technology]].<ref name=BohannonBio/>  She later returned to Kazakhstan, where her participation in research\u2010sharing forums led her to conceive of a way to automate the process of sharing.<ref name=BohannonBio>{{cite journal |last1=Bohannon |first1=John |title=The frustrated science student behind Sci-Hub |journal=Science |volume=352 |issue=6285 |pages=511 |date=28 April 2016 |url=https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2016/04/frustrated-science-student-behind-sci-hub?IntCmp=scihub-1-11 |language=en |bibcode=2016Sci...352..511B |doi=10.1126/science.352.6285.511 |pmid=27126021 |access-date=27 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181027233538/https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2016/04/frustrated-science-student-behind-sci-hub?IntCmp=scihub-1-11 |archive-date=27 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> The Sci-Hub website was launched on 5 September 2011.<ref name=\"eLife\" />\n\n=== Legal situation ===\n{{See also|Copyright infringement#Legality of downloading}}\nSci-Hub has cycled through domain names, some of which have been blocked by [[domain name registry|domain registry operators]].<ref name=\"eLife\"/> Sci-Hub remained reachable via alternative domains such as [[.io]],<ref name=\"eLife\"/> then [[.cc]], and [[.bz]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Johnston |first1=Joyce |title=Sci-Hub as Criminal: A Publisher's View |url=https://www.oif.ala.org/oif/?p=6905 |work=Office for Intellectual Freedom of the American Library Association: Intellectual Freedom Blog |date=8 July 2016 |access-date=30 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031052322/https://www.oif.ala.org/oif/?p=6905 |archive-date=31 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Sci-Hub has also been accessible at times by directly entering the [[IP address]], or through a [[.onion]] [[Tor (anonymity network)|Tor]] Hidden Service.<ref name=\"Gardner\">{{Cite news |url=https://crl.acrl.org/index.php/crl/article/view/16578 |title=Fast and Furious (at Publishers): The Motivations behind Crowdsourced Research Sharing |last=Gardner |first=Carolyn Caffrey |date=2017-04-19 |work=College & Research Libraries |access-date=2018-10-19 |last2=Gardner |first2=Gabriel J. |issue=2 |volume=78 |language=en |doi=10.5860/crl.78.2.16578 |issn=2150-6701 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181020094951/https://crl.acrl.org/index.php/crl/article/view/16578 |archive-date=2018-10-20 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/05/piracy-site-for-academic-journals-playing-game-of-domain-name-whac-a-mole/|title=Piracy site for academic journals playing game of domain-name Whac-A-Mole|last=Kravets|first=David|date=5 May 2016|work=Ars Technica|access-date=15 June 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170909231538/https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/05/piracy-site-for-academic-journals-playing-game-of-domain-name-whac-a-mole/|archive-date=9 September 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==== United States ====\nIn 2015, [[Elsevier]] filed a lawsuit against Sci-Hub, in ''Elsevier et al. v. Sci-Hub et al.'', at the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of New York]].<ref name=\"Schiermeier2017\" /> [[Library Genesis]] (LibGen) was also a defendant in the case<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web |title= Academic Publishing Giant Fights to Keep Science Paywalled |url= http://www.gizmodo.com.au/2015/06/academic-publishing-giant-fights-to-keep-science-paywalled/ |work= Gizmodo |publisher= Gawker Media |accessdate= 5 October 2015 |first= Maddie |last= Stone |date= 2015-06-15 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20151006170125/http://www.gizmodo.com.au/2015/06/academic-publishing-giant-fights-to-keep-science-paywalled/ |archive-date= 6 October 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |title= Elsevier acts against research article pirate sites and claims irreparable harm |url= https://theconversation.com/elsevier-acts-against-research-article-pirate-sites-and-claims-irreparable-harm-43293 |date= 15 June 2015 |work= The Conversation |publisher= The Conversation Trust |accessdate= 5 October 2015 |first= David |last= Glance |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20151006181704/https://theconversation.com/elsevier-acts-against-research-article-pirate-sites-and-claims-irreparable-harm-43293 |archive-date= 6 October 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|author=Kravets, David|date=2016-04-03|url=https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/04/a-spiritual-successor-to-aaron-swartz-is-angering-publishers-all-over-again/|title=A spiritual successor to Aaron Swartz is angering publishers all over again|website=arstechnica.com|access-date=2016-08-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170111180537/http://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/04/a-spiritual-successor-to-aaron-swartz-is-angering-publishers-all-over-again/|archive-date=2017-01-11|url-status=live}}</ref>  which may be based in either the Netherlands<ref name=\":0\" /> or also in Russia.<ref>{{Cite news |first = Henry |last = Mance |title = Publishers win landmark case against ebook pirates |url = http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/988850e0-038c-11e5-a70f-00144feabdc0.html |newspaper = [[Financial Times]] |issn = 0307-1766 |publisher = [[The Nikkei]] |date = 26 May 2015 |accessdate = 5 October 2015 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150708065407/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/988850e0-038c-11e5-a70f-00144feabdc0.html |archive-date = 8 July 2015 |url-status=live }}{{paywall}}</ref> It was the largest copyright infringement case that had been filed in the US, or in the world, at the time.<ref name=Greco2017>{{cite journal |last1=Greco |first1=Albert N. |title=The Kirtsaeng and SCI-HUB Cases: The Major U.S. Copyright Cases in the Twenty-First Century |journal=Publishing Research Quarterly |date=8 June 2017 |volume=33 |issue=3 |pages=238\u2013253 |doi=10.1007/s12109-017-9522-7}}</ref>  Elsevier alleged that Sci-Hub violated copyright law and induced others to do so, and it alleged violations of the [[Computer Fraud and Abuse Act]] as well as inducements to violate that law.<ref name=Greco2017/> Elsevier asked for monetary damages and an [[injunction]] to stop the sharing of the papers.<ref name=Greco2017/>\n\nAt the time the website was hosted in [[Saint Petersburg|St. Petersburg]], Russia, where judgments made by American courts were not enforceable,<ref name=\":0\" /> and Sci-Hub did not defend the lawsuit.<ref name=\"Schiermeier2017\"/>  In June 2017, the court awarded Elsevier [[US$]]15 million in damages for copyright infringement by Sci-Hub and others in a [[default judgment]].<ref name=\"Schiermeier2017\">{{Cite journal|last=Schiermeier|first=Quirin|title=US court grants Elsevier millions in damages from Sci-Hub|url=http://www.nature.com/news/us-court-grants-elsevier-millions-in-damages-from-sci-hub-1.22196|journal= Nature |language=en|doi=10.1038/nature.2017.22196|year=2017|access-date=2017-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170622200235/http://www.nature.com/news/us-court-grants-elsevier-millions-in-damages-from-sci-hub-1.22196|archive-date=2017-06-22|url-status=live}}</ref> The judgment found that Sci-Hub used accounts of students and academic institutions to access articles through Elsevier's platform [[ScienceDirect]].<ref name=\":0\" /> The judgment also granted the injunction, which led to the loss of the original sci-hub.org domain.<ref name=\"eLife\" /><ref name=shadowill/><ref name=\"independent\">{{cite web|last1=Henderson|first1=Emma|title=Pirate website offering millions of academic papers for free refuses to close despite lawsuit|date=15 February 2016|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/pirate-website-offering-millions-of-academic-papers-for-free-refuses-to-close-despite-law-suit-a6875001.html|work=The Independent|publisher=Independent Print Limited|accessdate=15 February 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160217205512/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/pirate-website-offering-millions-of-academic-papers-for-free-refuses-to-close-despite-law-suit-a6875001.html|archive-date=17 February 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2017, the [[American Chemical Society]] (ACS) filed a lawsuit against Sci-Hub in the [[United States District Court for the Eastern District of Virginia]], alleging copyright and trademark infringement; it sought judgment US$4.8 million from Sci-Hub in damages, and [[Internet service provider]] blocking of the Sci-Hub website.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.insidehighered.com/quicktakes/2017/09/06/american-chemical-society-moves-block-access-sci-hub|title=American Chemical Society Moves to Block Access to Sci-Hub|work=Inside Higher Ed|first=Lindsay|last=McKenzie|date=6 September 2017|access-date=6 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906195809/https://www.insidehighered.com/quicktakes/2017/09/06/american-chemical-society-moves-block-access-sci-hub|archive-date=6 September 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On 6 November 2017, the ACS was granted a [[default judgment]], and a permanent injunction was granted against all parties in active concert or participation with Sci-Hub that has notice of the injunction, \"including any Internet search engines, web hosting and Internet service providers, domain name registrars, and domain name registries\", to cease facilitating access to the service.<ref name=Chawla>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/11/court-demands-search-engines-and-internet-service-providers-block-sci-hub|title=Court demands that search engines and internet service providers block Sci-Hub|work=Science {{!}} AAAS|first=Dalmeet Singh|last=Chawla|date=6 November 2017|language=en|access-date=7 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171123071628/http://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/11/court-demands-search-engines-and-internet-service-providers-block-sci-hub|archive-date=23 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=EFF2017>{{Cite web |url=https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2017/11/another-court-overreaches-site-blocking-order-targeting-sci-hub |title=Another Court Overreaches With Site-Blocking Order Targeting Sci-Hub |last=Stoltz |first=Mitch |date=2017-11-10 |website=Electronic Frontier Foundation |language=en |access-date=2018-10-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181207180328/https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2017/11/another-court-overreaches-site-blocking-order-targeting-sci-hub |archive-date=2018-12-07 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 23 November 2017, four Sci-Hub domains had been rendered inactive by the court order<ref>{{cite news |last1=Silver |first1=Andrew |title=Sci-Hub domains inactive following court order |url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2017/11/23/sci_hubs_become_inactive_following_court_order/ |work=The Register |date=23 November 2017 |language=en |access-date=27 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181017123635/https://www.theregister.co.uk/2017/11/23/sci_hubs_become_inactive_following_court_order/ |archive-date=17 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> and its [[CloudFlare]] account was terminated.<ref name=Scientist2018>{{cite news |last1=Kwon |first1=Diana |title=Sci-Hub Loses Domains and Access to Some Web Services |url=https://www.the-scientist.com/daily-news/sci-hub-loses-domains-and-access-to-some-web-services-30264 |work=The Scientist Magazine |date=20 February 2018 |language=en |access-date=23 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181122145223/https://www.the-scientist.com/daily-news/sci-hub-loses-domains-and-access-to-some-web-services-30264 |archive-date=22 November 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 2018 and 2019, the White House Office of the US Trade Representative named Sci-Hub as one of the most \"notorious market\" sites in the world.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ustr.gov/sites/default/files/2018_Notorious_Markets_List.pdf|title=USTR|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019, ''[[The Washington Post]]'' reported that the US Justice Department was investigating whether Sci-Hub founder Alexandra Elbakyan had links with Russian intelligence, in part due to the suspicion that tacit approval or assistance of the Russians is required for an operation of the scale of Sci-Hub.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/justice-department-investigates-sci-hub-founder-on-suspicion-of-working-for-russian-intelligence/2019/12/19/9dbcb6e6-2277-11ea-a153-dce4b94e4249_story.html|title= Justice Department Investigates Sci-Hub Founder on Suspicion of Working For Russian Intelligence|work=Washington Post|last=|first=|date=December 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Sweden ====\nIn October 2018, Swedish [[ISP]]s were forced to block access to Sci-Hub after a court case instigated by Elsevier; [[Bahnhof]], a large Swedish ISP, in return soft-blocked the Elsevier website.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://thewire.in/the-sciences/elsevier-forces-isp-to-block-access-to-sci-hub-isp-blocks-elsevier-as-well/|title=Elsevier Forces ISP to Block Access to Sci-Hub, ISP Blocks Elsevier as Well|date=2018-11-05|access-date=2018-12-04|work=The Wire|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205003221/https://thewire.in/the-sciences/elsevier-forces-isp-to-block-access-to-sci-hub-isp-blocks-elsevier-as-well|archive-date=2018-12-05|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==== Russia ====\nIn November 2018, Russia's [[Federal Service for Supervision of Communications, Information Technology and Mass Media]]  blocked Sci-Hub and its mirror websites after a [[Moscow City Court]] ruling to comply with Elsevier's and [[Springer Nature]]'s complaints regarding intellectual property infringement.<ref>{{cite web|author=Dalmeet Singh Chawla|url=https://www.chemistryworld.com/news/sci-hub-blocked-in-russia-following-ruling-by-moscow-court/3009838.article|title=Sci-Hub blocked in Russia following ruling by Moscow court|website=Chemistry World|publisher=Royal Society of Chemistry|date=3 December 2018|access-date=2018-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181215224127/https://www.chemistryworld.com/news/sci-hub-blocked-in-russia-following-ruling-by-moscow-court/3009838.article|archive-date=15 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The site moved to another domain and is still available online as of 22 October 2019.<ref name=\"roskomsvoboda\" />\n\n==== France ====\nOn 7 March 2019, following a complaint by Elsevier and Springer Nature, a French court ordered French [[ISP]]s to block access to Sci-Hub and [[Library Genesis]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Marc Rees|url=https://www.nextinpact.com/news/107689-les-principaux-fai-francais-doivent-bloquer-sci-hub-et-libgen.htm|title=Les principaux FAI fran\u00e7ais doivent bloquer Sci-Hub et LibGen|website=NextInpact|date=30 March 2019|access-date=2019-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403021242/https://www.nextinpact.com/news/107689-les-principaux-fai-francais-doivent-bloquer-sci-hub-et-libgen.htm|archive-date=3 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Ernesto Van der Sar|url=https://torrentfreak.com/court-orders-french-isps-to-block-sci-hub-and-libgen-190331/|title=French ISPs Ordered to Block Sci-Hub and LibGen|website=TorrentFreak|date=31 March 2019|access-date=2019-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190406133821/https://torrentfreak.com/court-orders-french-isps-to-block-sci-hub-and-libgen-190331/|archive-date=6 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> However, the court order did not affect the academic network [[Renater]], through which most French academic access to Sci-Hub presumably goes.<ref>{{cite web|author=R\u00e9my Gr\u00fcnblatt|url=https://remy.grunblatt.org/la-censure-de-sci-hub-et-libgen-vue-depuis-le-reseau-ripe-atlas.html|title=La censure de Sci-Hub et LibGen vue depuis le r\u00e9seau RIPE Atlas|date=30 March 2019|access-date=2019-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407001643/https://remy.grunblatt.org/la-censure-de-sci-hub-et-libgen-vue-depuis-le-reseau-ripe-atlas.html|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==== Belgium ====\nFollowing the lawsuit by Elsevier in March 2019 in France, Elsevier, [[Springer Science+Business Media|Springer]], [[John Wiley & Son|John Wiley]], and [[Cambridge University Press]] filed a complaint against [[Proximus]], [[VOO]], [[Brut\u00e9l\u00e9]] and [[Telenet (Belgium)|Telenet]] to block access to Sci-Hub and LibGen. The publishers claimed to represent more than half of the scientific publishing sector, and indicated that over 90% of the contents on the sites [[Copyright infringement|infringed copyright laws]]; they won the lawsuit.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lecho.be/entreprises/technologie/les-editeurs-scientifiques-se-liguent-contre-la-piraterie/10172391.html|title=Les \u00e9diteurs scientifiques se liguent contre la piraterie|date=2019-10-16|website=L'Echo|language=fr|access-date=2020-01-14}}</ref> Since then, the two sites are blocked by those [[Internet service provider|ISPs]]; visitors are redirected to a stop page [http://networkmsg.telenet.be/blocked/fccu/] by [[Federal Police (Belgium)|Belgian Federal Police]] instead, citing illegality of the site's content under Belgian legislation.\n\nThe European Commission included Sci-Hub in its \"Piracy Watch List\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://trade.ec.europa.eu/doclib/docs/2018/december/tradoc_157564.pdf|website=European Commission|title=Counterfeit and Piracy Watch List|page=11|date=7 December 2018  |author= }}</ref>\n\n== Website ==\nThe site's operation is financed by user donations.<ref name=Bohannon/>\n\n===Article sourcing ===\nSci-Hub obtains paywalled articles using leaked credentials.<ref name=\"eLife\"/><ref name=RussellSanchez/> The source of the credentials used by Sci-Hub is unclear.<ref name=\"WaPo\" />  Some appear to have been donated,<ref name=\"eLife\" /> some were apparently sold before going to Sci-Hub,<ref name=\"IGS\">{{cite news |last1=Graber-Stiehl |first1=Ian |title=Science's Pirate Queen |url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/2/8/16985666/alexandra-elbakyan-sci-hub-open-access-science-papers-lawsuit |work=The Verge |date=8 February 2018 |access-date=27 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028163915/https://www.theverge.com/2018/2/8/16985666/alexandra-elbakyan-sci-hub-open-access-science-papers-lawsuit |archive-date=28 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> and some appear to have been obtained via [[phishing]] and were then used by Sci-Hub.<ref name=\"Ruff\">{{cite news|url=https://www.chronicle.com/article/Librarians-Find-Themselves/235353|title=Librarians Find Themselves Caught Between Journal Pirates and Publishers|last1=Ruff|first1=Corinne|date=18 February 2016|work=The Chronicle of Higher Education|access-date=28 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028225820/https://www.chronicle.com/article/Librarians-Find-Themselves/235353|archive-date=28 October 2018|url-status=live}}.</ref><ref name=\"RussellSanchez\">{{cite journal |last1=Russell |first1=Carrie |last2=Sanchez |first2=Ed |title=Sci-Hub unmasked: Piracy, information policy, and your library |journal=College & Research Libraries News |date=1 March 2016 |volume=77 |issue=3 |pages=122\u2013125 |doi=10.5860/crln.77.3.9457 |language=en |issn=2150-6698 |doi-access=free }}</ref> Elbakyan denies personally sending any phishing emails and said, \"The exact source of the passwords was never personally important to me.\"<ref name=\"WaPo\" /> According to The Scholarly Kitchen, a blog established by the [[Society for Scholarly Publishing]] whose members are involved in legal action against Sci-Hub, credentials used by Sci-Hub to access paywalled articles are correlated to access of other information on university networks (such as [[cyber spying on universities]]) and credential sales in black markets.<ref name=\"SK\">{{cite news |last1=Pitts |first1=Andrew |title=Guest Post: Think Sci-Hub is Just Downloading PDFs? Think Again - The Scholarly Kitchen |url=https://scholarlykitchen.sspnet.org/2018/09/18/guest-post-think-sci-hub-is-just-downloading-pdfs-think-again/ |work=The Scholarly Kitchen |date=18 September 2018 |access-date=28 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028230037/https://scholarlykitchen.sspnet.org/2018/09/18/guest-post-think-sci-hub-is-just-downloading-pdfs-think-again/ |archive-date=28 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Several articles have reported that Sci-Hub has penetrated the computer networks of more than 370 universities in 39 countries. These include more than 150 institutions in the US, more than 30 in Canada, 39 in the UK and more than 10 in Sweden.&nbsp;The universities in the UK include Cambridge, Oxford, Imperial and King's College, London.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qz.com/1773765/sci-hub-creator-says-shes-not-working-for-russian-intelligence|title=Quarts|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dn.se/ekonomi/spion-eller-en-kunskapens-robin-hood/?site=mobile|title=Spion eller en kunskapens Robin Hood?|last=|first=|date=10 January 2020|website=dn.se|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/russian-pirate-hacked-39-british-universities-6x9335xh9|title=The Times|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tricitynews.com/news/ubc-sfu-allegedly-hacked-by-russian-intelligence-backed-internet-pirates-1.24042570|title=Tri City News|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n===Delivery to users===\nThe Sci-Hub website provides access to articles from almost all [[Academic publishing|academic publishers]], including [[Elsevier]], [[Springer Nature|Springer/Nature]], [[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers]], [[American Chemical Society]], [[Wiley-Blackwell|Wiley Blackwell]], and the [[Royal Society of Chemistry]], as well as open-access works, and distributes them without regard to publishers' copyrights.<ref name=Bohannon/>   It does not require subscriptions or payment.<ref name=\":3\">{{cite journal |last1=Cabanac |first1=Guillaume |title=Bibliogifts in LibGen? A study of a text-sharing platform driven by biblioleaks and crowdsourcing |journal=Journal of the Association for Information Science and Technology |date=2016 |volume=67 |issue=4 |pages=874\u2013884 |doi=10.1002/asi.23445 |url=http://www.irit.fr/publis/SIG/2015_JASIST_C.pdf |accessdate=25 August 2016 |citeseerx=10.1.1.698.4283 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310035801/https://www.irit.fr/publis/SIG/2015_JASIST_C.pdf |archive-date=10 March 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref>{{rp|10}}\n\nUsers can access works from all sources with a unified interface, by entering the [[Digital object identifier|DOI]] in the search bar on the main page or in the Sci-Hub [[URL]] (like some academic link resolvers), or by appending the Sci-Hub domain to the [[internet domain|domain]] of a publisher's URL (like some academic proxies).<ref>{{cite news |last1=Heathers |first1=James |title=Why Sci-Hub Will Win |url=https://medium.com/@jamesheathers/why-sci-hub-will-win-595b53aae9fa |work=James Heathers via Medium |date=2 May 2016 |access-date=28 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180429024908/https://medium.com/@jamesheathers/why-sci-hub-will-win-595b53aae9fa |archive-date=29 April 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>  Sci-Hub redirects requests for some [[gold open access]] works, identified as such beyond the metadata available in [[CrossRef]] and [[Unpaywall]]. Some requests require the user to enter a [[CAPTCHA]].<ref name=SKhow/> Papers can also be accessed using a [[Software agent|bot]] in the  [[instant messaging]] service [[Telegram]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sci-Hub Offers Encrypted Bot to Help Users Stay Safe - Deep Dot Web|url=https://www.deepdotweb.com/2016/05/23/sci-hub-offers-encrypted-bot-help-users-stay-safe/|date=16 May 2016|author=American Guerrilla|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181118182646/https://www.deepdotweb.com/2016/05/23/sci-hub-offers-encrypted-bot-help-users-stay-safe/|archive-date=18 November 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIf the paper is in the repository already, the request is served immediately. If the paper is not already in the repository, a wait screen appears while the site presents someone else's credentials on behalf of the user to a series of [[Proxy server|proxies]] until it finds one that has access to the paper, which is then presented to the user and stored in the repository.<ref name=\"eLife\"/><ref name=Ruff/><ref name=\"ALM\">{{cite journal|last1=Banks|first1=Marcus|date=31 May 2016|title=Sci-Hub: What It Is and Why It Matters|url=https://americanlibrariesmagazine.org/2016/05/31/why-sci-hub-matters/|journal=American Libraries|access-date=23 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918042400/https://americanlibrariesmagazine.org/2016/05/31/why-sci-hub-matters/|archive-date=18 September 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=SKhow>{{cite news |last1=Smith |first1=David |title=Sci-Hub: How Does it Work? |url=https://scholarlykitchen.sspnet.org/2016/02/25/sci-hub-how-does-it-work |work=The Scholarly Kitchen |date=25 February 2016 |access-date=28 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028033628/https://scholarlykitchen.sspnet.org/2016/02/25/sci-hub-how-does-it-work/ |archive-date=28 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nUntil the end of 2014, Sci-Hub relied on [[LibGen]] as storage: papers requested by users were requested from LibGen and served from there if available, otherwise they were fetched by other means and then stored on LibGen.<ref name=\"eLife\" /> The permanent storage made it possible to serve more users than the previous system of deleting the cached content after 6 hours.<ref name=Elbakyan2017>{{cite news|accessdate=2018-04-30|title=Some facts on Sci-Hub that Wikipedia gets wrong|url=https://engineuring.wordpress.com/2017/07/02/some-facts-on-sci-hub-that-wikipedia-gets-wrong/|date=2017-07-02|author=Alexandra Elbakyan|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203192037/https://engineuring.wordpress.com/2017/07/02/some-facts-on-sci-hub-that-wikipedia-gets-wrong/|archive-date=2017-12-03|url-status=live|author-link=Alexandra Elbakyan}}</ref>\n\nSince 2015, Sci-Hub uses its own storage<ref name=\"eLife\" /> for the same purpose.<ref name=Elbakyan2017/> As of 2017 Sci-Hub was continuing to redirect requests for [[electronic books]] to Libgen.<ref name=\"eLife\" /><ref name=Elbakyan2017/>\n\n=== Usage and content statistics ===\n[[File:Sci-hub_downloads.png|thumb|Download rate for articles on Sci-Hub<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Himmelstein|first=Daniel S|last2=Romero|first2=Ariel Rodriguez|last3=Levernier|first3=Jacob G|last4=Munro|first4=Thomas Anthony|last5=McLaughlin|first5=Stephen Reid|last6=Greshake Tzovaras|first6=Bastian|last7=Greene|first7=Casey S|date=2018-03-01|title=Sci-Hub provides access to nearly all scholarly literature|url=https://greenelab.github.io/scihub-manuscript/#fig:downloads|journal=eLife|language=en|volume=7|pages=|doi=10.7554/eLife.32822|issn=2050-084X|pmc=5832410|pmid=29424689|via=|access-date=2019-05-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190521022258/https://greenelab.github.io/scihub-manuscript/#fig:downloads|archive-date=2019-05-21|url-status=live}}</ref>]]\nIn February 2016, the website claimed to serve over 200,000 requests per day<ref name=\"Bohannon\" />\u2014an increase from an average of 80,000 per day before the \"sci-hub.org\" domain was blocked in 2015.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite journal |url= http://www.nature.com/news/pirate-research-paper-sites-play-hide-and-seek-with-publishers-1.18876 |title= Pirate research-paper sites play hide-and-seek with publishers |last= Schiermeier |first= Quirin |date= 4 December 2015 |journal= Nature |accessdate= 6 December 2015 |doi= 10.1038/nature.2015.18876 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20151206032713/http://www.nature.com/news/pirate-research-paper-sites-play-hide-and-seek-with-publishers-1.18876 |archive-date= 6 December 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn early 2016, data released by Elbakyan showed usage in developed countries was high, with a large proportion of the downloads coming from the US and countries within the [[European Union]].<ref name=Bohannon>{{cite journal |last1=Bohannon|first1=John |title= Who's downloading pirated papers? Everyone |journal= [[Science (journal)|Science]] |doi= 10.1126/science.aaf5664 |date=28 April 2016 |volume=352 |number=6285 |pages= 508\u2013512}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2017, the website had 62 million papers in its collection,<ref name=\"greshake\">{{Cite journal|last=Greshake|first=Bastian|date=2017-04-21|title=Looking into Pandora's Box: The Content ofSci-Hub and its Usage|journal=F1000Research|volume=6|pages=541|doi=10.12688/f1000research.11366.1|issn=2046-1402|pmc=5428489|pmid=28529712}}</ref> which were found to include 85% of the articles published in paywalled scholarly journals.<ref name=\"eLife\"/> Although only 69% of all published articles were in the database in March 2017, it has been estimated, based on scholarly citations from articles published between 2015 and July 2017, that at least 96% of requests for paywalled articles are successful.<ref name=\"eLife\" />\n\nA 2019 study of 27.8 million download requests via Sci-Hub indicates that 23.2 million of these were for journal articles, 4.7 million (22%) of which were articles from medical journals.  The requests for medical literature came mostly from middle- and low-income countries (69%); the countries with the most requests in absolute numbers were India, China, the US, Brazil, and Iran.<ref>{{cite journal |journal= Lancet Glob Health |date= January 2019 |volume=7 |issue=1|pages=e30\u2013e31| doi= 10.1016/S2214-109X(18)30388-7 |title=Who is pirating medical literature? A bibliometric review of 28 million Sci-Hub downloads |vauthors=Till BM, Rudolfson N, Saluja S, Gnanaraj J, Samad L, Ljungman D, Shrime M|pmid= 30554757 |doi-access=free }}</ref>\n\nIn the context of the [[big deal (subscription model)|big deal]] cancellations by several library systems in the world, in 2019 the wide usage of Sci-Hub was credited as one of the factors which reduced the apparent value of the subscriptions to [[toll access]] resources.<ref>{{cite journal|first1=Andr\u00e9s|last1=Fern\u00e1ndez-Ramos|first2=Mar\u00eda Blanca|last2=Rodr\u00edguez Bravo|first3=Mar\u00eda Luisa|last3=Alvite D\u00edez|first4=Lourdes|last4=Santos de Paz|title=Evolution of the big deals use in the public universities of the Castile and Leon region, Spain = Evoluci\u00f3n del uso de los big deals en las universidades p\u00fablicas de Castilla y Le\u00f3n|url=https://buleria.unileon.es/handle/10612/11498|journal=El profesional de la informaci\u00f3n|date=2019|volume=28|issue=6|doi=10.3145/epi.2019.nov.19|first5=Mar\u00eda Antonia|last5=Mor\u00e1n Su\u00e1rez|first6=Josefa|last6=Gallego Lorenzo|first7=Isabel|last7=Olea Merino|language=es}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n[[File:Alexandra Elbakyan.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Alexandra Elbakyan]] at a conference at Harvard (2010)]]\nSci-Hub's interface is perceived by users as providing a superior user experience and convenience compared to the typical interfaces available to users who have access to a paid subscription.<ref name=shadowill>{{cite journal|url=http://eprints.rclis.org/30981/|authors=Gardner, Gabriel J. and McLaughlin, Stephen R. and Asher, Andrew D.|title=Shadow Libraries and You: Sci-Hub Usage and the Future of ILL|pages=568\u2013587|series=ACRL 2017, Baltimore, Maryland.|date=25 March 2017|type=conference paper|hdl=10760/30981|journal=|access-date=28 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180128193207/http://eprints.rclis.org/30981/|archive-date=28 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSci-Hub has been lauded as having \"changed how we access knowledge\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bigthink.com/natalie-shoemaker/sci-hub-has-changed-how-we-access-knowledge|title=Which countries are accessing Sci-Hub, created by Alexandra Elbakyan?|last=Shoemaker|first=Natalie|date=3 May 2016|website=Big Think|access-date=2016-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160828141853/http://bigthink.com/natalie-shoemaker/sci-hub-has-changed-how-we-access-knowledge|archive-date=28 August 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> It raised awareness about the scientific publishing business models and its ethics of making researchers' institutions pay for their articles to be published, while providing and reviewing them without payment.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2011/aug/29/academic-publishers-murdoch-socialist|title=Academic publishers make Murdoch look like a socialist {{!}} George Monbiot|last=Monbiot|first=George|date=2011-08-29|work=the Guardian|access-date=2019-03-10|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190307174619/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2011/aug/29/academic-publishers-murdoch-socialist|archive-date=2019-03-07|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSupport for [[open-access]] [[science publishing]] extends beyond Sci-Hub; [[Plan S]] is an initiative launched by [[Science Europe]] on 4 September 2018.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coalition of European Funders Announces \"Plan S\" to Require Full OA, Cap APCs, & Disallow Publication in Hybrid Journals |url=https://sparcopen.org/news/2018/coalition-european-funders-announces-plan-s/ |work=SPARC |date=4 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Plan S: Accelerating the transition to full and immediate Open Access to scientific publications |url=https://www.scienceeurope.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Plan_S.pdf |website=[[Science Europe]] |accessdate=13 September 2018 |date=4 September 2018}}</ref> It is an initiative of \"cOAlition S\",<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.scienceeurope.org/coalition-s/|title=Science Europe \u2013 cOAlition S|website=www.scienceeurope.org|language=en-GB|access-date=2018-09-15}}</ref> a consortium launched by major national research agencies and funders from twelve European countries. The plan requires scientists and researchers who benefit from state-funded research organisations and institutions to publish their work in open repositories or in journals that are available to all by 2021.<ref name=\"Economist\">{{cite news |title=European countries demand that publicly funded research should be free to all |url=https://www.economist.com/science-and-technology/2018/09/15/european-countries-demand-that-publicly-funded-research-should-be-free-to-all |work=[[The Economist]] |date=15 September 2018 |accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref> The initiative is not a law.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/2016/may/28/eu-ministers-2020-target-free-access-scientific-papers|title=All scientific papers to be free by 2020 under EU proposals|last=Khomami|first=Nadia|date=2016-05-28|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-03-10|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190311212159/https://www.theguardian.com/science/2016/may/28/eu-ministers-2020-target-free-access-scientific-papers|archive-date=2019-03-11|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nScientists in some European countries began negotiations with Elsevier and other academic publishers on introducing national open access.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/10/german-researchers-resign-elsevier-journals-push-nationwide-open-access|title=German researchers resign from Elsevier journals in push for nationwide open access|last=VogelOct. 13|first=Gretchen|last2=2017|date=2017-10-13|website=Science {{!}} AAAS|language=en|access-date=2019-03-15|last3=Pm|first3=3:30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322172128/https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/10/german-researchers-resign-elsevier-journals-push-nationwide-open-access|archive-date=2019-03-22|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.enago.com/academy/move-boycott-elsevier-journals-deal-near-dead/|title=Elsevier's Open Access Controversy: German Researchers Resign to Register Protest|date=2017-10-19|website=Enago Academy|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606095631/https://www.enago.com/academy/move-boycott-elsevier-journals-deal-near-dead/|archive-date=2019-06-06|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nPublishers have been very critical of Sci-Hub, going so far as to claim that it is undermining more widely accepted open-access initiatives,<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|last=Banks|first=Marcus|url=https://americanlibrariesmagazine.org/2016/05/31/why-sci-hub-matters/|title=Sci-Hub: What It Is and Why It Matters|date=31 May 2016|website=American Libraries|access-date=2016-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918042400/https://americanlibrariesmagazine.org/2016/05/31/why-sci-hub-matters/|archive-date=18 September 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> and that it ignores how publishers \"work hard\" to make access for third-world nations easier.<ref name=\":5\" /> It has also been criticized by librarians for compromising universities' [[network security]] and jeopardizing legitimate access to papers by university staff.<ref name=\"Ruff\" /><ref name=\"ALM\" /><ref name=\"RussellSanchez\" /><ref name=\"SK\" />\n\nHowever, even prominent western institutions such as [[Harvard University|Harvard]] and [[Cornell University|Cornell]] have had to cut down their access to publications due to ever-increasing subscription costs,<ref>{{Cite web|website=sciencealert.com|url=http://www.sciencealert.com/this-woman-has-illegally-uploaded-millions-of-journal-articles-in-an-attempt-to-open-up-science|title=Researcher illegally shares millions of science papers free online to spread knowledge|date=12 February 2016|last=MacDonald|first=Fiona|access-date=2016-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821054849/http://www.sciencealert.com/this-woman-has-illegally-uploaded-millions-of-journal-articles-in-an-attempt-to-open-up-science|archive-date=21 August 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> potentially causing some of the highest use of Sci-Hub to be in American cities with well-known universities (this may however be down to the convenience of the site rather than a lack of access).<ref name=Bohannon/>  Sci-Hub can be seen as one venue in a general trend in which research is becoming more accessible.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasas-making-it-easier-check-out-research-its-funding-180960172/?no-ist|title=Soon Everyone Will Be Able to Read NASA-Funded Research|date=22 August 2016|last=Lewis|first=Danny|website=smithsonian.com|access-date=2016-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160825073336/http://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasas-making-it-easier-check-out-research-its-funding-180960172/?no-ist|archive-date=25 August 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Many academics, university librarians and longtime advocates for open scholarly research believe Elbakyan is \"giving academic publishers their [[Napster]] moment\", referring to the illegal music-sharing service that \"disrupted and permanently altered the industry\".<ref name=WaPo>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/this-student-put-50-million-stolen-research-articles-online-and-theyre-free/2016/03/30/7714ffb4-eaf7-11e5-b0fd-073d5930a7b7_story.html|title=This student put 50 million stolen research articles online. And they're free.|date=30 March 2016|website=The Washington Post|last1=Rosenwald|first1=Michael S.|access-date=2018-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190414201340/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/this-student-put-50-million-stolen-research-articles-online-and-theyre-free/2016/03/30/7714ffb4-eaf7-11e5-b0fd-073d5930a7b7_story.html|archive-date=14 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nFor her actions in creating Sci-Hub, Elbakyan has been called a hero and \"spiritual successor to [[Aaron Swartz]]\" who in 2010 downloaded millions of academic articles from [[JSTOR]].<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":6\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/13/opinion/sunday/should-all-research-papers-be-free.html|title=Should All Research Papers Be Free?|last=Murphy|first=Kate|date=12 March 2016|newspaper=The New York Times|issn=0362-4331|access-date=2016-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031030302/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/13/opinion/sunday/should-all-research-papers-be-free.html|archive-date=31 October 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> She has also been compared to [[Edward Snowden]] who has sought safety in Russia after having made numerous documents public in violation of American law.<ref name=\":6\" /> She has also been called a modern-day \"[[Robin Hood]]\" and a \"Robin Hood of science\".<ref name=\"bigthink\">{{cite news|url=http://bigthink.com/neurobonkers/a-pirate-bay-for-science|title=Meet the Robin Hood of Science|last=Oxenham|first=Simon|date=10 February 2016|accessdate=22 February 2016|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160217155028/http://bigthink.com/neurobonkers/a-pirate-bay-for-science|archive-date=17 February 2016|publisher=The Big Think, Inc.}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2016, the [[Association of American Publishers]] sent a letter to Gabriel J. Gardner, a researcher at [[California State University]] who has written papers on Sci-Hub and similar sites. The letter asked Gardner to stop promoting the site, which he had discussed at a session of a meeting of the [[American Library Association]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Peet |first1=Lisa |title=Sci-Hub Controversy Triggers Publishers' Critique of Librarian |url=https://www.libraryjournal.com/?detailStory=sci-hub-controversy-triggers-publishers-critique-of-librarian |work=The Library Journal |date=25 August 2016 |access-date=2018-12-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181013211828/https://www.libraryjournal.com/?detailStory=sci-hub-controversy-triggers-publishers-critique-of-librarian |archive-date=13 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> In response the publishing institution was highly criticized for trying to silence legitimate research into the topic, and the letter has since been published in full, and responded to by the dean of library services at [[California State University, Long Beach|Cal State Long Beach]], who supported Gardner's work.<ref>{{cite web|last= Jaschik|first= Scott|url= https://www.insidehighered.com/news/2016/08/08/letter-publishers-group-adds-debate-over-sci-hub-and-librarians-who-study-it|title= Letter from publishers' group adds to debate over Sci-Hub and librarians who study it|date= 8 August 2016|website= Inside Higher Ed|access-date= 2016-08-29|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160814185208/https://www.insidehighered.com/news/2016/08/08/letter-publishers-group-adds-debate-over-sci-hub-and-librarians-who-study-it|archive-date= 14 August 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2016, [[Nature Publishing Group]] named Alexandra Elbakyan as one of the [[Nature's 10|ten people who most mattered]] in 2016.<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite journal|date=2016-12-22|title=Nature's 10|journal=Nature|volume=540|issue=7634|pages=507\u2013515|doi=10.1038/540507a|pmid=30905952|bibcode=2016Natur.540..507.|doi-access=free}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Russian and Mexican entomologists named a species of [[parasitoid wasp]] ''[[Idiogramma elbakyanae]]'' in reference to Sci-Hub's creator, Alexandra Elbakyan. The Russian and Mexican team said this was \"in honour of Alexandra Elbakyan (Kazakhstan/Russia), creator of the web-site Sci-Hub, in recognition of her contribution to making scientific knowledge available for all researchers.\"<ref name=Bookseller20170906/><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Khalaim|first1=Andrey I.|last2=Ru\u00edz-Cancino |first2=Enrique|title=Ichneumonidae (Hymenoptera) associated with xyelid sawflies (Hymenoptera, Xyelidae) in Mexico |journal=Journal of Hymenoptera Research|date=31 August 2017|volume=58|pages=17\u201327|doi=10.3897/jhr.58.12919|doi-access=free}}</ref> Elbakyan was offended by the naming, and subsequently blocked access to Sci-Hub's services in the Russian Federation.<ref name=Bookseller20170906>{{cite news|url=https://www.thebookseller.com/news/elbakyan-pulls-sci-hub-russia-631281|title=Elbakyan pulls Sci-Hub from Russia|work=The Bookseller|date=6 September 2017|first=Benedicte|last=Page|access-date=2018-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190110190320/https://www.thebookseller.com/news/elbakyan-pulls-sci-hub-russia-631281|archive-date=10 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The Russian entomologist responsible for naming the wasp stated that he supports Sci-Hub, and that in any event, the naming was not an insult, in particular because [[parasitoid]]s are closer to [[predator]]s than to [[parasite]]s.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kotlyar|first1=Pavel|title=\u0412\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0441\u044c \u0432 \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0435\u043c \u0434\u0435\u0440\u044c\u043c\u0435 \u0441\u0430\u043c\u0438|url=https://www.gazeta.ru/science/2017/09/05_a_10875050.shtml|publisher=[[Gazeta.ru]]|accessdate=21 October 2017|language=ru|date=5 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171119234104/https://www.gazeta.ru/science/2017/09/05_a_10875050.shtml|archive-date=19 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn response to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], a group of online archivists have used Sci-Hub for creating an archive of over 5000 articles about coronaviruses. They admitted that making the archive openly accessible was illegal, but considered it a [[moral imperative]].<ref name=\"Bender 2020\"/>\n\n==See also==\n{{collist|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Library Genesis]]\n*[[Library.nu]]\n*[[Open access]]\n*[[ResearchGate]]\n*[[The Pirate Bay]]\n*[[Unpaywall]]\n*[[ICanHazPDF|#ICanHazPDF]]\n* [[Aaron Swartz#Open Access|Guerilla Open Access Manifesto]]\n}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"Bender 2020\">{{cite web | last=Bender | first=Maddie | title='It's a Moral Imperative:' Archivists Made a Directory of 5,000 Coronavirus Studies to Bypass Paywalls | website=Vice | date=2020-02-03 | url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/z3b3v5/archivists-are-bypassing-paywalls-to-share-studies-about-coronaviruses | access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* [http://openaccess.unt.edu/symposium/2016/info/transcript-and-translation-sci-hub-presentation Transcript and translation of \"Why Science is Better with Communism? The Case of Sci-Hub\"], a presentation by Alexandra Elbakyan at the University of North Texas Open Access Symposium 2016.\n* [http://www.stephenmclaughlin.net/sci-hub/McLaughlin_Sci-Hub-LibGen-Bib_3-2016.pdf \"Sci-Hub/LibGen in Blogs and the Media (PDF)\"] Stephen Reid McLaughlin, March 2016\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|sci-hub.tw/about}}\n* [http://vertsluisants.fr/index.php?article4/where-scihub-libgen-server-down List of online SciHub servers]\n\n{{Open navbox}}\n{{Intellectual property activism}}\n{{Academic publishing}}\n{{Tor hidden services}}\n{{File sharing}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n\n[[Category:Search engine software]]\n[[Category:Academic publishing]]\n[[Category:Tor onion services]]\n[[Category:File sharing communities]]\n[[Category:Intellectual property activism]]\n[[Category:Open access projects]]\n[[Category:Internet properties established in 2011]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Website providing free access to millions of research papers}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name = Sci-Hub\n| logo = File:Scihub raven.png\n| logo_size = 100px\n| logo_caption = \n| logo_alt = Official logo of Sci-Hub depicting black raven drawing with reddish key in mouth\n| screenshot = \n| screenshot_size = <!-- default 300px -->\n| screenshot_alt = \n| url = [https://sci-hub.tw/about sci-hub.tw]<br/>\n[https://sci-hub.si/about sci-hub.si]<br/>[https://sci-hub.uno/about sci-hub.uno]<br/>[https://sci-hub.ren/about sci-hub.ren]\n| ip = <!-- Not currently accessible via any IP address -->\n| commercial = No\n| type = [[File sharing]]\n| registration = Not required\n| language = {{ubl|English|Russian{{efn|Article viewer only appears in Russian}} }}\n| num_users = \n| content_license = Hosts material without regard to copyright\n| owner = \n| author = [[Alexandra Elbakyan]]\n| editor = \n| launch_date = {{start date and age|2011|04|16|df=yes}}<ref name=\"icann\">{{cite web|title=sci-hub.org|url=https://whois.icann.org/en/lookup?name=sci-hub.org|website=ICANN WHOIS|accessdate=28 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180309140050/https://whois.icann.org/en/lookup?name=sci-hub.org|archive-date=9 March 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| alexa = <!--do not fill: too hard to evaluate due to it having multiple domains and continuously switching domains-->\n| current_status = Active\n}}\n{{File sharing sidebar}}\n'''Sci-Hub''' is a website that provides free access to millions of [[academic paper|research papers]] and books, [[copyright infringement|without regard to copyright]],<ref name=\"eLife\"/> by bypassing publishers' [[paywall]]s in various ways.<ref name=\"eLife\"/><ref name=Bohannon/><ref name=\"Elbakyan2017\" />\n\nSci-Hub was founded by [[Alexandra Elbakyan]] in 2011 in [[Kazakhstan]] in response to the high cost of research papers behind paywalls. The site is extensively used worldwide.<ref name=\"eLife\" /><ref name=Bohannon/> In January 2020, the site's owners said that it contained 78 million academic articles and served approximately 400,000 requests per day.<ref name=\"roskomsvoboda\">{{cite web|url=https://roskomsvoboda.org/49416/|title=Sci-Hub \u043e\u0442\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043b \u0432\u043e\u0441\u044c\u043c\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0435|website=Roskomsvoboda.org|date=6 September 2019|access-date=2019-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191021170135/https://roskomsvoboda.org/49416/|archive-date=21 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The number of articles claimed is frequently updated on the site's home page, being over 81 million in early March 2020.\n\nSci-Hub and Elbakyan were sued twice for [[copyright infringement]] in the United States in 2015 and 2017, and lost both cases, leading to loss of some of its Internet [[domain name]]s.<ref name=Chawla/>  The site has cycled through different domain names since then.<ref name=\"eLife\">{{Cite journal |last=Himmelstein |first=Daniel S |last2=Romero |first2=Ariel Rodriguez |last3=Levernier |first3=Jacob G |last4=Munro |first4=Thomas Anthony |last5=McLaughlin |first5=Stephen Reid |last6=Greshake Tzovaras |first6=Bastian |last7=Greene |first7=Casey S |title=Sci-Hub provides access to nearly all scholarly literature|journal=eLife |volume=7 |doi=10.7554/eLife.32822 |issn=2050-084X |pmc=5832410 |pmid=29424689|year=2018 }}</ref>\n\nSci-Hub has been lauded by some<ref name=WaPo/> in the [[Scientific community|scientific]], academic, and publishing communities<ref name=\":7\" /> for providing access to knowledge generated by the scientific community. Others have criticized it for violating copyright,<ref name=Bohannon/><ref name=\":4\"/> threatening the economic viability of publishers,<ref name=shadowill/> potentially compromising universities' [[network security]] and jeopardizing legitimate access to papers by university staff.<ref name=RussellSanchez/>\n\n==History==\n[[File:Scihub Feb 2016 pop-adjusted.png|thumb|300px|Number of papers downloaded from Sci-Hub per capita by country (September 2015 to February 2016)<ref name=\"datadryad.org\">{{Cite book |last1=Bohannon|first1=John|last2=Elbakyan|first2=Alexandra |title= Data from: Who's downloading pirated papers? Everyone |publisher= Dryad Digital Repository|doi= 10.5061/dryad.q447c |date=2016-04-28|type=Data Set|chapter=Open access}}</ref><ref name=Bohannon/>]]\nSci-Hub was created by [[Alexandra Elbakyan]], who was born in [[Kazakhstan]] in 1988.<ref name=BohannonBio/>  Elbakyan earned her undergraduate degree at [[Satbayev Kazakh National Technical University|Kazakh National Technical University]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Lifeboat Foundation Bios: Alexandra A. Elbakyan|url=http://lifeboat.com/ex/bios.alexandra.a.elbakyan|publisher=Lifeboat Foundation|accessdate=15 February 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100507022228/http://lifeboat.com/ex/bios.alexandra.a.elbakyan|archivedate=7 May 2010|df=}}</ref> studying information technology, then worked for a year for a computer security firm in Moscow, then joined a research team at the [[University of Freiburg]] in Germany in 2010 that was working on a [[brain\u2013computer interface]].<ref name=BohannonBio/> She found the lab dull and became interested in [[transhumanism]].<ref name=BohannonBio/> After attending a transhumanism conference in the United States, Elbakyan spent her remaining time in the country doing a research internship at [[Georgia Institute of Technology]].<ref name=BohannonBio/>  She later returned to Kazakhstan, where her participation in research\u2010sharing forums led her to conceive of a way to automate the process of sharing.<ref name=BohannonBio>{{cite journal |last1=Bohannon |first1=John |title=The frustrated science student behind Sci-Hub |journal=Science |volume=352 |issue=6285 |pages=511 |date=28 April 2016 |url=https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2016/04/frustrated-science-student-behind-sci-hub?IntCmp=scihub-1-11 |language=en |bibcode=2016Sci...352..511B |doi=10.1126/science.352.6285.511 |pmid=27126021 |access-date=27 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181027233538/https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2016/04/frustrated-science-student-behind-sci-hub?IntCmp=scihub-1-11 |archive-date=27 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> The Sci-Hub website was launched on 5 September 2011.<ref name=\"eLife\" />\n\n=== Legal situation ===\n{{See also|Copyright infringement#Legality of downloading}}\nSci-Hub has cycled through domain names, some of which have been blocked by [[domain name registry|domain registry operators]].<ref name=\"eLife\"/> Sci-Hub remained reachable via alternative domains such as [[.io]],<ref name=\"eLife\"/> then [[.cc]], and [[.bz]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Johnston |first1=Joyce |title=Sci-Hub as Criminal: A Publisher's View |url=https://www.oif.ala.org/oif/?p=6905 |work=Office for Intellectual Freedom of the American Library Association: Intellectual Freedom Blog |date=8 July 2016 |access-date=30 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031052322/https://www.oif.ala.org/oif/?p=6905 |archive-date=31 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Sci-Hub has also been accessible at times by directly entering the [[IP address]], or through a [[.onion]] [[Tor (anonymity network)|Tor]] Hidden Service.<ref name=\"Gardner\">{{Cite news |url=https://crl.acrl.org/index.php/crl/article/view/16578 |title=Fast and Furious (at Publishers): The Motivations behind Crowdsourced Research Sharing |last=Gardner |first=Carolyn Caffrey |date=2017-04-19 |work=College & Research Libraries |access-date=2018-10-19 |last2=Gardner |first2=Gabriel J. |issue=2 |volume=78 |language=en |doi=10.5860/crl.78.2.16578 |issn=2150-6701 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181020094951/https://crl.acrl.org/index.php/crl/article/view/16578 |archive-date=2018-10-20 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/05/piracy-site-for-academic-journals-playing-game-of-domain-name-whac-a-mole/|title=Piracy site for academic journals playing game of domain-name Whac-A-Mole|last=Kravets|first=David|date=5 May 2016|work=Ars Technica|access-date=15 June 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170909231538/https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/05/piracy-site-for-academic-journals-playing-game-of-domain-name-whac-a-mole/|archive-date=9 September 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==== United States ====\nIn 2015, [[Elsevier]] filed a lawsuit against Sci-Hub, in ''Elsevier et al. v. Sci-Hub et al.'', at the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of New York]].<ref name=\"Schiermeier2017\" /> [[Library Genesis]] (LibGen) was also a defendant in the case<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web |title= Academic Publishing Giant Fights to Keep Science Paywalled |url= http://www.gizmodo.com.au/2015/06/academic-publishing-giant-fights-to-keep-science-paywalled/ |work= Gizmodo |publisher= Gawker Media |accessdate= 5 October 2015 |first= Maddie |last= Stone |date= 2015-06-15 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20151006170125/http://www.gizmodo.com.au/2015/06/academic-publishing-giant-fights-to-keep-science-paywalled/ |archive-date= 6 October 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |title= Elsevier acts against research article pirate sites and claims irreparable harm |url= https://theconversation.com/elsevier-acts-against-research-article-pirate-sites-and-claims-irreparable-harm-43293 |date= 15 June 2015 |work= The Conversation |publisher= The Conversation Trust |accessdate= 5 October 2015 |first= David |last= Glance |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20151006181704/https://theconversation.com/elsevier-acts-against-research-article-pirate-sites-and-claims-irreparable-harm-43293 |archive-date= 6 October 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|author=Kravets, David|date=2016-04-03|url=https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/04/a-spiritual-successor-to-aaron-swartz-is-angering-publishers-all-over-again/|title=A spiritual successor to Aaron Swartz is angering publishers all over again|website=arstechnica.com|access-date=2016-08-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170111180537/http://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/04/a-spiritual-successor-to-aaron-swartz-is-angering-publishers-all-over-again/|archive-date=2017-01-11|url-status=live}}</ref>  which may be based in either the Netherlands<ref name=\":0\" /> or also in Russia.<ref>{{Cite news |first = Henry |last = Mance |title = Publishers win landmark case against ebook pirates |url = http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/988850e0-038c-11e5-a70f-00144feabdc0.html |newspaper = [[Financial Times]] |issn = 0307-1766 |publisher = [[The Nikkei]] |date = 26 May 2015 |accessdate = 5 October 2015 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150708065407/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/988850e0-038c-11e5-a70f-00144feabdc0.html |archive-date = 8 July 2015 |url-status=live }}{{paywall}}</ref> It was the largest copyright infringement case that had been filed in the US, or in the world, at the time.<ref name=Greco2017>{{cite journal |last1=Greco |first1=Albert N. |title=The Kirtsaeng and SCI-HUB Cases: The Major U.S. Copyright Cases in the Twenty-First Century |journal=Publishing Research Quarterly |date=8 June 2017 |volume=33 |issue=3 |pages=238\u2013253 |doi=10.1007/s12109-017-9522-7}}</ref>  Elsevier alleged that Sci-Hub violated copyright law and induced others to do so, and it alleged violations of the [[Computer Fraud and Abuse Act]] as well as inducements to violate that law.<ref name=Greco2017/> Elsevier asked for monetary damages and an [[injunction]] to stop the sharing of the papers.<ref name=Greco2017/>\n\nAt the time the website was hosted in [[Saint Petersburg|St. Petersburg]], Russia, where judgments made by American courts were not enforceable,<ref name=\":0\" /> and Sci-Hub did not defend the lawsuit.<ref name=\"Schiermeier2017\"/>  In June 2017, the court awarded Elsevier [[US$]]15 million in damages for copyright infringement by Sci-Hub and others in a [[default judgment]].<ref name=\"Schiermeier2017\">{{Cite journal|last=Schiermeier|first=Quirin|title=US court grants Elsevier millions in damages from Sci-Hub|url=http://www.nature.com/news/us-court-grants-elsevier-millions-in-damages-from-sci-hub-1.22196|journal= Nature |language=en|doi=10.1038/nature.2017.22196|year=2017|access-date=2017-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170622200235/http://www.nature.com/news/us-court-grants-elsevier-millions-in-damages-from-sci-hub-1.22196|archive-date=2017-06-22|url-status=live}}</ref> The judgment found that Sci-Hub used accounts of students and academic institutions to access articles through Elsevier's platform [[ScienceDirect]].<ref name=\":0\" /> The judgment also granted the injunction, which led to the loss of the original sci-hub.org domain.<ref name=\"eLife\" /><ref name=shadowill/><ref name=\"independent\">{{cite web|last1=Henderson|first1=Emma|title=Pirate website offering millions of academic papers for free refuses to close despite lawsuit|date=15 February 2016|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/pirate-website-offering-millions-of-academic-papers-for-free-refuses-to-close-despite-law-suit-a6875001.html|work=The Independent|publisher=Independent Print Limited|accessdate=15 February 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160217205512/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/pirate-website-offering-millions-of-academic-papers-for-free-refuses-to-close-despite-law-suit-a6875001.html|archive-date=17 February 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2017, the [[American Chemical Society]] (ACS) filed a lawsuit against Sci-Hub in the [[United States District Court for the Eastern District of Virginia]], alleging copyright and trademark infringement; it sought judgment US$4.8 million from Sci-Hub in damages, and [[Internet service provider]] blocking of the Sci-Hub website.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.insidehighered.com/quicktakes/2017/09/06/american-chemical-society-moves-block-access-sci-hub|title=American Chemical Society Moves to Block Access to Sci-Hub|work=Inside Higher Ed|first=Lindsay|last=McKenzie|date=6 September 2017|access-date=6 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906195809/https://www.insidehighered.com/quicktakes/2017/09/06/american-chemical-society-moves-block-access-sci-hub|archive-date=6 September 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On 6 November 2017, the ACS was granted a [[default judgment]], and a permanent injunction was granted against all parties in active concert or participation with Sci-Hub that has notice of the injunction, \"including any Internet search engines, web hosting and Internet service providers, domain name registrars, and domain name registries\", to cease facilitating access to the service.<ref name=Chawla>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/11/court-demands-search-engines-and-internet-service-providers-block-sci-hub|title=Court demands that search engines and internet service providers block Sci-Hub|work=Science {{!}} AAAS|first=Dalmeet Singh|last=Chawla|date=6 November 2017|language=en|access-date=7 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171123071628/http://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/11/court-demands-search-engines-and-internet-service-providers-block-sci-hub|archive-date=23 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=EFF2017>{{Cite web |url=https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2017/11/another-court-overreaches-site-blocking-order-targeting-sci-hub |title=Another Court Overreaches With Site-Blocking Order Targeting Sci-Hub |last=Stoltz |first=Mitch |date=2017-11-10 |website=Electronic Frontier Foundation |language=en |access-date=2018-10-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181207180328/https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2017/11/another-court-overreaches-site-blocking-order-targeting-sci-hub |archive-date=2018-12-07 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 23 November 2017, four Sci-Hub domains had been rendered inactive by the court order<ref>{{cite news |last1=Silver |first1=Andrew |title=Sci-Hub domains inactive following court order |url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2017/11/23/sci_hubs_become_inactive_following_court_order/ |work=The Register |date=23 November 2017 |language=en |access-date=27 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181017123635/https://www.theregister.co.uk/2017/11/23/sci_hubs_become_inactive_following_court_order/ |archive-date=17 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> and its [[CloudFlare]] account was terminated.<ref name=Scientist2018>{{cite news |last1=Kwon |first1=Diana |title=Sci-Hub Loses Domains and Access to Some Web Services |url=https://www.the-scientist.com/daily-news/sci-hub-loses-domains-and-access-to-some-web-services-30264 |work=The Scientist Magazine |date=20 February 2018 |language=en |access-date=23 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181122145223/https://www.the-scientist.com/daily-news/sci-hub-loses-domains-and-access-to-some-web-services-30264 |archive-date=22 November 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 2018 and 2019, the White House Office of the US Trade Representative named Sci-Hub as one of the most \"notorious market\" sites in the world.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ustr.gov/sites/default/files/2018_Notorious_Markets_List.pdf|title=USTR|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019, ''[[The Washington Post]]'' reported that the US Justice Department was investigating whether Sci-Hub founder Alexandra Elbakyan had links with Russian intelligence, in part due to the suspicion that tacit approval or assistance of the Russians is required for an operation of the scale of Sci-Hub.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/justice-department-investigates-sci-hub-founder-on-suspicion-of-working-for-russian-intelligence/2019/12/19/9dbcb6e6-2277-11ea-a153-dce4b94e4249_story.html|title= Justice Department Investigates Sci-Hub Founder on Suspicion of Working For Russian Intelligence|work=Washington Post|last=|first=|date=December 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Sweden ====\nIn October 2018, Swedish [[ISP]]s were forced to block access to Sci-Hub after a court case instigated by Elsevier; [[Bahnhof]], a large Swedish ISP, in return soft-blocked the Elsevier website.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://thewire.in/the-sciences/elsevier-forces-isp-to-block-access-to-sci-hub-isp-blocks-elsevier-as-well/|title=Elsevier Forces ISP to Block Access to Sci-Hub, ISP Blocks Elsevier as Well|date=2018-11-05|access-date=2018-12-04|work=The Wire|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205003221/https://thewire.in/the-sciences/elsevier-forces-isp-to-block-access-to-sci-hub-isp-blocks-elsevier-as-well|archive-date=2018-12-05|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==== Russia ====\nIn November 2018, Russia's [[Federal Service for Supervision of Communications, Information Technology and Mass Media]]  blocked Sci-Hub and its mirror websites after a [[Moscow City Court]] ruling to comply with Elsevier's and [[Springer Nature]]'s complaints regarding intellectual property infringement.<ref>{{cite web|author=Dalmeet Singh Chawla|url=https://www.chemistryworld.com/news/sci-hub-blocked-in-russia-following-ruling-by-moscow-court/3009838.article|title=Sci-Hub blocked in Russia following ruling by Moscow court|website=Chemistry World|publisher=Royal Society of Chemistry|date=3 December 2018|access-date=2018-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181215224127/https://www.chemistryworld.com/news/sci-hub-blocked-in-russia-following-ruling-by-moscow-court/3009838.article|archive-date=15 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The site moved to another domain and is still available online as of 22 October 2019.<ref name=\"roskomsvoboda\" />\n\n==== France ====\nOn 7 March 2019, following a complaint by Elsevier and Springer Nature, a French court ordered French [[ISP]]s to block access to Sci-Hub and [[Library Genesis]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Marc Rees|url=https://www.nextinpact.com/news/107689-les-principaux-fai-francais-doivent-bloquer-sci-hub-et-libgen.htm|title=Les principaux FAI fran\u00e7ais doivent bloquer Sci-Hub et LibGen|website=NextInpact|date=30 March 2019|access-date=2019-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403021242/https://www.nextinpact.com/news/107689-les-principaux-fai-francais-doivent-bloquer-sci-hub-et-libgen.htm|archive-date=3 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Ernesto Van der Sar|url=https://torrentfreak.com/court-orders-french-isps-to-block-sci-hub-and-libgen-190331/|title=French ISPs Ordered to Block Sci-Hub and LibGen|website=TorrentFreak|date=31 March 2019|access-date=2019-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190406133821/https://torrentfreak.com/court-orders-french-isps-to-block-sci-hub-and-libgen-190331/|archive-date=6 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> However, the court order did not affect the academic network [[Renater]], through which most French academic access to Sci-Hub presumably goes.<ref>{{cite web|author=R\u00e9my Gr\u00fcnblatt|url=https://remy.grunblatt.org/la-censure-de-sci-hub-et-libgen-vue-depuis-le-reseau-ripe-atlas.html|title=La censure de Sci-Hub et LibGen vue depuis le r\u00e9seau RIPE Atlas|date=30 March 2019|access-date=2019-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407001643/https://remy.grunblatt.org/la-censure-de-sci-hub-et-libgen-vue-depuis-le-reseau-ripe-atlas.html|archive-date=7 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==== Belgium ====\nFollowing the lawsuit by Elsevier in March 2019 in France, Elsevier, [[Springer Science+Business Media|Springer]], [[John Wiley & Son|John Wiley]], and [[Cambridge University Press]] filed a complaint against [[Proximus]], [[VOO]], [[Brut\u00e9l\u00e9]] and [[Telenet (Belgium)|Telenet]] to block access to Sci-Hub and LibGen. The publishers claimed to represent more than half of the scientific publishing sector, and indicated that over 90% of the contents on the sites [[Copyright infringement|infringed copyright laws]]; they won the lawsuit.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lecho.be/entreprises/technologie/les-editeurs-scientifiques-se-liguent-contre-la-piraterie/10172391.html|title=Les \u00e9diteurs scientifiques se liguent contre la piraterie|date=2019-10-16|website=L'Echo|language=fr|access-date=2020-01-14}}</ref> Since then, the two sites are blocked by those [[Internet service provider|ISPs]]; visitors are redirected to a stop page [http://networkmsg.telenet.be/blocked/fccu/] by [[Federal Police (Belgium)|Belgian Federal Police]] instead, citing illegality of the site's content under Belgian legislation.\n\nThe European Commission included Sci-Hub in its \"Piracy Watch List\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://trade.ec.europa.eu/doclib/docs/2018/december/tradoc_157564.pdf|website=European Commission|title=Counterfeit and Piracy Watch List|page=11|date=7 December 2018  |author= }}</ref>\n\n== Website ==\nThe site's operation is financed by user donations.<ref name=Bohannon/>\n\n===Article sourcing ===\nSci-Hub obtains paywalled articles using leaked credentials.<ref name=\"eLife\"/><ref name=RussellSanchez/> The source of the credentials used by Sci-Hub is unclear.<ref name=\"WaPo\" />  Some appear to have been donated,<ref name=\"eLife\" /> some were apparently sold before going to Sci-Hub,<ref name=\"IGS\">{{cite news |last1=Graber-Stiehl |first1=Ian |title=Science's Pirate Queen |url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/2/8/16985666/alexandra-elbakyan-sci-hub-open-access-science-papers-lawsuit |work=The Verge |date=8 February 2018 |access-date=27 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028163915/https://www.theverge.com/2018/2/8/16985666/alexandra-elbakyan-sci-hub-open-access-science-papers-lawsuit |archive-date=28 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> and some appear to have been obtained via [[phishing]] and were then used by Sci-Hub.<ref name=\"Ruff\">{{cite news|url=https://www.chronicle.com/article/Librarians-Find-Themselves/235353|title=Librarians Find Themselves Caught Between Journal Pirates and Publishers|last1=Ruff|first1=Corinne|date=18 February 2016|work=The Chronicle of Higher Education|access-date=28 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028225820/https://www.chronicle.com/article/Librarians-Find-Themselves/235353|archive-date=28 October 2018|url-status=live}}.</ref><ref name=\"RussellSanchez\">{{cite journal |last1=Russell |first1=Carrie |last2=Sanchez |first2=Ed |title=Sci-Hub unmasked: Piracy, information policy, and your library |journal=College & Research Libraries News |date=1 March 2016 |volume=77 |issue=3 |pages=122\u2013125 |doi=10.5860/crln.77.3.9457 |language=en |issn=2150-6698 |doi-access=free }}</ref> Elbakyan denies personally sending any phishing emails and said, \"The exact source of the passwords was never personally important to me.\"<ref name=\"WaPo\" /> According to The Scholarly Kitchen, a blog established by the [[Society for Scholarly Publishing]] whose members are involved in legal action against Sci-Hub, credentials used by Sci-Hub to access paywalled articles are correlated to access of other information on university networks (such as [[cyber spying on universities]]) and credential sales in black markets.<ref name=\"SK\">{{cite news |last1=Pitts |first1=Andrew |title=Guest Post: Think Sci-Hub is Just Downloading PDFs? Think Again - The Scholarly Kitchen |url=https://scholarlykitchen.sspnet.org/2018/09/18/guest-post-think-sci-hub-is-just-downloading-pdfs-think-again/ |work=The Scholarly Kitchen |date=18 September 2018 |access-date=28 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028230037/https://scholarlykitchen.sspnet.org/2018/09/18/guest-post-think-sci-hub-is-just-downloading-pdfs-think-again/ |archive-date=28 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Several articles have reported that Sci-Hub has penetrated the computer networks of more than 370 universities in 39 countries. These include more than 150 institutions in the US, more than 30 in Canada, 39 in the UK and more than 10 in Sweden.&nbsp;The universities in the UK include Cambridge, Oxford, Imperial and King's College, London.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qz.com/1773765/sci-hub-creator-says-shes-not-working-for-russian-intelligence|title=Quarts|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dn.se/ekonomi/spion-eller-en-kunskapens-robin-hood/?site=mobile|title=Spion eller en kunskapens Robin Hood?|last=|first=|date=10 January 2020|website=dn.se|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/russian-pirate-hacked-39-british-universities-6x9335xh9|title=The Times|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tricitynews.com/news/ubc-sfu-allegedly-hacked-by-russian-intelligence-backed-internet-pirates-1.24042570|title=Tri City News|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n===Delivery to users===\nThe Sci-Hub website provides access to articles from almost all [[Academic publishing|academic publishers]], including [[Elsevier]], [[Springer Nature|Springer/Nature]], [[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers]], [[American Chemical Society]], [[Wiley-Blackwell|Wiley Blackwell]], and the [[Royal Society of Chemistry]], as well as open-access works, and distributes them without regard to publishers' copyrights.<ref name=Bohannon/>   It does not require subscriptions or payment.<ref name=\":3\">{{cite journal |last1=Cabanac |first1=Guillaume |title=Bibliogifts in LibGen? A study of a text-sharing platform driven by biblioleaks and crowdsourcing |journal=Journal of the Association for Information Science and Technology |date=2016 |volume=67 |issue=4 |pages=874\u2013884 |doi=10.1002/asi.23445 |url=http://www.irit.fr/publis/SIG/2015_JASIST_C.pdf |accessdate=25 August 2016 |citeseerx=10.1.1.698.4283 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310035801/https://www.irit.fr/publis/SIG/2015_JASIST_C.pdf |archive-date=10 March 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref>{{rp|10}}\n\nUsers can access works from all sources with a unified interface, by entering the [[Digital object identifier|DOI]] in the search bar on the main page or in the Sci-Hub [[URL]] (like some academic link resolvers), or by appending the Sci-Hub domain to the [[internet domain|domain]] of a publisher's URL (like some academic proxies).<ref>{{cite news |last1=Heathers |first1=James |title=Why Sci-Hub Will Win |url=https://medium.com/@jamesheathers/why-sci-hub-will-win-595b53aae9fa |work=James Heathers via Medium |date=2 May 2016 |access-date=28 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180429024908/https://medium.com/@jamesheathers/why-sci-hub-will-win-595b53aae9fa |archive-date=29 April 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>  Sci-Hub redirects requests for some [[gold open access]] works, identified as such beyond the metadata available in [[CrossRef]] and [[Unpaywall]]. Some requests require the user to enter a [[CAPTCHA]].<ref name=SKhow/> Papers can also be accessed using a [[Software agent|bot]] in the  [[instant messaging]] service [[Telegram]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sci-Hub Offers Encrypted Bot to Help Users Stay Safe - Deep Dot Web|url=https://www.deepdotweb.com/2016/05/23/sci-hub-offers-encrypted-bot-help-users-stay-safe/|date=16 May 2016|author=American Guerrilla|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181118182646/https://www.deepdotweb.com/2016/05/23/sci-hub-offers-encrypted-bot-help-users-stay-safe/|archive-date=18 November 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIf the paper is in the repository already, the request is served immediately. If the paper is not already in the repository, a wait screen appears while the site presents someone else's credentials on behalf of the user to a series of [[Proxy server|proxies]] until it finds one that has access to the paper, which is then presented to the user and stored in the repository.<ref name=\"eLife\"/><ref name=Ruff/><ref name=\"ALM\">{{cite journal|last1=Banks|first1=Marcus|date=31 May 2016|title=Sci-Hub: What It Is and Why It Matters|url=https://americanlibrariesmagazine.org/2016/05/31/why-sci-hub-matters/|journal=American Libraries|access-date=23 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918042400/https://americanlibrariesmagazine.org/2016/05/31/why-sci-hub-matters/|archive-date=18 September 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=SKhow>{{cite news |last1=Smith |first1=David |title=Sci-Hub: How Does it Work? |url=https://scholarlykitchen.sspnet.org/2016/02/25/sci-hub-how-does-it-work |work=The Scholarly Kitchen |date=25 February 2016 |access-date=28 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028033628/https://scholarlykitchen.sspnet.org/2016/02/25/sci-hub-how-does-it-work/ |archive-date=28 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nUntil the end of 2014, Sci-Hub relied on [[LibGen]] as storage: papers requested by users were requested from LibGen and served from there if available, otherwise they were fetched by other means and then stored on LibGen.<ref name=\"eLife\" /> The permanent storage made it possible to serve more users than the previous system of deleting the cached content after 6 hours.<ref name=Elbakyan2017>{{cite news|accessdate=2018-04-30|title=Some facts on Sci-Hub that Wikipedia gets wrong|url=https://engineuring.wordpress.com/2017/07/02/some-facts-on-sci-hub-that-wikipedia-gets-wrong/|date=2017-07-02|author=Alexandra Elbakyan|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203192037/https://engineuring.wordpress.com/2017/07/02/some-facts-on-sci-hub-that-wikipedia-gets-wrong/|archive-date=2017-12-03|url-status=live|author-link=Alexandra Elbakyan}}</ref>\n\nSince 2015, Sci-Hub uses its own storage<ref name=\"eLife\" /> for the same purpose.<ref name=Elbakyan2017/> As of 2017 Sci-Hub was continuing to redirect requests for [[electronic books]] to Libgen.<ref name=\"eLife\" /><ref name=Elbakyan2017/>\n\n=== Usage and content statistics ===\n[[File:Sci-hub_downloads.png|thumb|Download rate for articles on Sci-Hub<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Himmelstein|first=Daniel S|last2=Romero|first2=Ariel Rodriguez|last3=Levernier|first3=Jacob G|last4=Munro|first4=Thomas Anthony|last5=McLaughlin|first5=Stephen Reid|last6=Greshake Tzovaras|first6=Bastian|last7=Greene|first7=Casey S|date=2018-03-01|title=Sci-Hub provides access to nearly all scholarly literature|url=https://greenelab.github.io/scihub-manuscript/#fig:downloads|journal=eLife|language=en|volume=7|pages=|doi=10.7554/eLife.32822|issn=2050-084X|pmc=5832410|pmid=29424689|via=|access-date=2019-05-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190521022258/https://greenelab.github.io/scihub-manuscript/#fig:downloads|archive-date=2019-05-21|url-status=live}}</ref>]]\nIn February 2016, the website claimed to serve over 200,000 requests per day<ref name=\"Bohannon\" />\u2014an increase from an average of 80,000 per day before the \"sci-hub.org\" domain was blocked in 2015.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite journal |url= http://www.nature.com/news/pirate-research-paper-sites-play-hide-and-seek-with-publishers-1.18876 |title= Pirate research-paper sites play hide-and-seek with publishers |last= Schiermeier |first= Quirin |date= 4 December 2015 |journal= Nature |accessdate= 6 December 2015 |doi= 10.1038/nature.2015.18876 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20151206032713/http://www.nature.com/news/pirate-research-paper-sites-play-hide-and-seek-with-publishers-1.18876 |archive-date= 6 December 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn early 2016, data released by Elbakyan showed usage in developed countries was high, with a large proportion of the downloads coming from the US and countries within the [[European Union]].<ref name=Bohannon>{{cite journal |last1=Bohannon|first1=John |title= Who's downloading pirated papers? Everyone |journal= [[Science (journal)|Science]] |doi= 10.1126/science.aaf5664 |date=28 April 2016 |volume=352 |number=6285 |pages= 508\u2013512}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2017, the website had 62 million papers in its collection,<ref name=\"greshake\">{{Cite journal|last=Greshake|first=Bastian|date=2017-04-21|title=Looking into Pandora's Box: The Content ofSci-Hub and its Usage|journal=F1000Research|volume=6|pages=541|doi=10.12688/f1000research.11366.1|issn=2046-1402|pmc=5428489|pmid=28529712}}</ref> which were found to include 85% of the articles published in paywalled scholarly journals.<ref name=\"eLife\"/> Although only 69% of all published articles were in the database in March 2017, it has been estimated, based on scholarly citations from articles published between 2015 and July 2017, that at least 96% of requests for paywalled articles are successful.<ref name=\"eLife\" />\n\nA 2019 study of 27.8 million download requests via Sci-Hub indicates that 23.2 million of these were for journal articles, 4.7 million (22%) of which were articles from medical journals.  The requests for medical literature came mostly from middle- and low-income countries (69%); the countries with the most requests in absolute numbers were India, China, the US, Brazil, and Iran.<ref>{{cite journal |journal= Lancet Glob Health |date= January 2019 |volume=7 |issue=1|pages=e30\u2013e31| doi= 10.1016/S2214-109X(18)30388-7 |title=Who is pirating medical literature? A bibliometric review of 28 million Sci-Hub downloads |vauthors=Till BM, Rudolfson N, Saluja S, Gnanaraj J, Samad L, Ljungman D, Shrime M|pmid= 30554757 |doi-access=free }}</ref>\n\nIn the context of the [[big deal (subscription model)|big deal]] cancellations by several library systems in the world, in 2019 the wide usage of Sci-Hub was credited as one of the factors which reduced the apparent value of the subscriptions to [[toll access]] resources.<ref>{{cite journal|first1=Andr\u00e9s|last1=Fern\u00e1ndez-Ramos|first2=Mar\u00eda Blanca|last2=Rodr\u00edguez Bravo|first3=Mar\u00eda Luisa|last3=Alvite D\u00edez|first4=Lourdes|last4=Santos de Paz|title=Evolution of the big deals use in the public universities of the Castile and Leon region, Spain = Evoluci\u00f3n del uso de los big deals en las universidades p\u00fablicas de Castilla y Le\u00f3n|url=https://buleria.unileon.es/handle/10612/11498|journal=El profesional de la informaci\u00f3n|date=2019|volume=28|issue=6|doi=10.3145/epi.2019.nov.19|first5=Mar\u00eda Antonia|last5=Mor\u00e1n Su\u00e1rez|first6=Josefa|last6=Gallego Lorenzo|first7=Isabel|last7=Olea Merino|language=es}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n[[File:Alexandra Elbakyan.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Alexandra Elbakyan]] at a conference at Harvard (2010)]]\nSci-Hub's interface is perceived by users as providing a superior user experience and convenience compared to the typical interfaces available to users who have access to a paid subscription.<ref name=shadowill>{{cite journal|url=http://eprints.rclis.org/30981/|authors=Gardner, Gabriel J. and McLaughlin, Stephen R. and Asher, Andrew D.|title=Shadow Libraries and You: Sci-Hub Usage and the Future of ILL|pages=568\u2013587|series=ACRL 2017, Baltimore, Maryland.|date=25 March 2017|type=conference paper|hdl=10760/30981|journal=|access-date=28 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180128193207/http://eprints.rclis.org/30981/|archive-date=28 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSci-Hub has been lauded as having \"changed how we access knowledge\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bigthink.com/natalie-shoemaker/sci-hub-has-changed-how-we-access-knowledge|title=Which countries are accessing Sci-Hub, created by Alexandra Elbakyan?|last=Shoemaker|first=Natalie|date=3 May 2016|website=Big Think|access-date=2016-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160828141853/http://bigthink.com/natalie-shoemaker/sci-hub-has-changed-how-we-access-knowledge|archive-date=28 August 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> It raised awareness about the scientific publishing business models and its ethics of making researchers' institutions pay for their articles to be published, while providing and reviewing them without payment.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2011/aug/29/academic-publishers-murdoch-socialist|title=Academic publishers make Murdoch look like a socialist {{!}} George Monbiot|last=Monbiot|first=George|date=2011-08-29|work=the Guardian|access-date=2019-03-10|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190307174619/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2011/aug/29/academic-publishers-murdoch-socialist|archive-date=2019-03-07|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSupport for [[open-access]] [[science publishing]] extends beyond Sci-Hub; [[Plan S]] is an initiative launched by [[Science Europe]] on 4 September 2018.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coalition of European Funders Announces \"Plan S\" to Require Full OA, Cap APCs, & Disallow Publication in Hybrid Journals |url=https://sparcopen.org/news/2018/coalition-european-funders-announces-plan-s/ |work=SPARC |date=4 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Plan S: Accelerating the transition to full and immediate Open Access to scientific publications |url=https://www.scienceeurope.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Plan_S.pdf |website=[[Science Europe]] |accessdate=13 September 2018 |date=4 September 2018}}</ref> It is an initiative of \"cOAlition S\",<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.scienceeurope.org/coalition-s/|title=Science Europe \u2013 cOAlition S|website=www.scienceeurope.org|language=en-GB|access-date=2018-09-15}}</ref> a consortium launched by major national research agencies and funders from twelve European countries. The plan requires scientists and researchers who benefit from state-funded research organisations and institutions to publish their work in open repositories or in journals that are available to all by 2021.<ref name=\"Economist\">{{cite news |title=European countries demand that publicly funded research should be free to all |url=https://www.economist.com/science-and-technology/2018/09/15/european-countries-demand-that-publicly-funded-research-should-be-free-to-all |work=[[The Economist]] |date=15 September 2018 |accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref> The initiative is not a law.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/2016/may/28/eu-ministers-2020-target-free-access-scientific-papers|title=All scientific papers to be free by 2020 under EU proposals|last=Khomami|first=Nadia|date=2016-05-28|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-03-10|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190311212159/https://www.theguardian.com/science/2016/may/28/eu-ministers-2020-target-free-access-scientific-papers|archive-date=2019-03-11|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nScientists in some European countries began negotiations with Elsevier and other academic publishers on introducing national open access.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/10/german-researchers-resign-elsevier-journals-push-nationwide-open-access|title=German researchers resign from Elsevier journals in push for nationwide open access|last=VogelOct. 13|first=Gretchen|last2=2017|date=2017-10-13|website=Science {{!}} AAAS|language=en|access-date=2019-03-15|last3=Pm|first3=3:30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322172128/https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/10/german-researchers-resign-elsevier-journals-push-nationwide-open-access|archive-date=2019-03-22|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.enago.com/academy/move-boycott-elsevier-journals-deal-near-dead/|title=Elsevier's Open Access Controversy: German Researchers Resign to Register Protest|date=2017-10-19|website=Enago Academy|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606095631/https://www.enago.com/academy/move-boycott-elsevier-journals-deal-near-dead/|archive-date=2019-06-06|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nPublishers have been very critical of Sci-Hub, going so far as to claim that it is undermining more widely accepted open-access initiatives,<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|last=Banks|first=Marcus|url=https://americanlibrariesmagazine.org/2016/05/31/why-sci-hub-matters/|title=Sci-Hub: What It Is and Why It Matters|date=31 May 2016|website=American Libraries|access-date=2016-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918042400/https://americanlibrariesmagazine.org/2016/05/31/why-sci-hub-matters/|archive-date=18 September 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> and that it ignores how publishers \"work hard\" to make access for third-world nations easier.<ref name=\":5\" /> It has also been criticized by librarians for compromising universities' [[network security]] and jeopardizing legitimate access to papers by university staff.<ref name=\"Ruff\" /><ref name=\"ALM\" /><ref name=\"RussellSanchez\" /><ref name=\"SK\" />\n\nHowever, even prominent western institutions such as [[Harvard University|Harvard]] and [[Cornell University|Cornell]] have had to cut down their access to publications due to ever-increasing subscription costs,<ref>{{Cite web|website=sciencealert.com|url=http://www.sciencealert.com/this-woman-has-illegally-uploaded-millions-of-journal-articles-in-an-attempt-to-open-up-science|title=Researcher illegally shares millions of science papers free online to spread knowledge|date=12 February 2016|last=MacDonald|first=Fiona|access-date=2016-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821054849/http://www.sciencealert.com/this-woman-has-illegally-uploaded-millions-of-journal-articles-in-an-attempt-to-open-up-science|archive-date=21 August 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> potentially causing some of the highest use of Sci-Hub to be in American cities with well-known universities (this may however be down to the convenience of the site rather than a lack of access).<ref name=Bohannon/>  Sci-Hub can be seen as one venue in a general trend in which research is becoming more accessible.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasas-making-it-easier-check-out-research-its-funding-180960172/?no-ist|title=Soon Everyone Will Be Able to Read NASA-Funded Research|date=22 August 2016|last=Lewis|first=Danny|website=smithsonian.com|access-date=2016-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160825073336/http://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasas-making-it-easier-check-out-research-its-funding-180960172/?no-ist|archive-date=25 August 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Many academics, university librarians and longtime advocates for open scholarly research believe Elbakyan is \"giving academic publishers their [[Napster]] moment\", referring to the illegal music-sharing service that \"disrupted and permanently altered the industry\".<ref name=WaPo>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/this-student-put-50-million-stolen-research-articles-online-and-theyre-free/2016/03/30/7714ffb4-eaf7-11e5-b0fd-073d5930a7b7_story.html|title=This student put 50 million stolen research articles online. And they're free.|date=30 March 2016|website=The Washington Post|last1=Rosenwald|first1=Michael S.|access-date=2018-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190414201340/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/this-student-put-50-million-stolen-research-articles-online-and-theyre-free/2016/03/30/7714ffb4-eaf7-11e5-b0fd-073d5930a7b7_story.html|archive-date=14 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nFor her actions in creating Sci-Hub, Elbakyan has been called a hero and \"spiritual successor to [[Aaron Swartz]]\" who in 2010 downloaded millions of academic articles from [[JSTOR]].<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":6\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/13/opinion/sunday/should-all-research-papers-be-free.html|title=Should All Research Papers Be Free?|last=Murphy|first=Kate|date=12 March 2016|newspaper=The New York Times|issn=0362-4331|access-date=2016-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031030302/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/13/opinion/sunday/should-all-research-papers-be-free.html|archive-date=31 October 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> She has also been compared to [[Edward Snowden]] who has sought safety in Russia after having made numerous documents public in violation of American law.<ref name=\":6\" /> She has also been called a modern-day \"[[Robin Hood]]\" and a \"Robin Hood of science\".<ref name=\"bigthink\">{{cite news|url=http://bigthink.com/neurobonkers/a-pirate-bay-for-science|title=Meet the Robin Hood of Science|last=Oxenham|first=Simon|date=10 February 2016|accessdate=22 February 2016|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160217155028/http://bigthink.com/neurobonkers/a-pirate-bay-for-science|archive-date=17 February 2016|publisher=The Big Think, Inc.}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2016, the [[Association of American Publishers]] sent a letter to Gabriel J. Gardner, a researcher at [[California State University]] who has written papers on Sci-Hub and similar sites. The letter asked Gardner to stop promoting the site, which he had discussed at a session of a meeting of the [[American Library Association]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Peet |first1=Lisa |title=Sci-Hub Controversy Triggers Publishers' Critique of Librarian |url=https://www.libraryjournal.com/?detailStory=sci-hub-controversy-triggers-publishers-critique-of-librarian |work=The Library Journal |date=25 August 2016 |access-date=2018-12-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181013211828/https://www.libraryjournal.com/?detailStory=sci-hub-controversy-triggers-publishers-critique-of-librarian |archive-date=13 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> In response the publishing institution was highly criticized for trying to silence legitimate research into the topic, and the letter has since been published in full, and responded to by the dean of library services at [[California State University, Long Beach|Cal State Long Beach]], who supported Gardner's work.<ref>{{cite web|last= Jaschik|first= Scott|url= https://www.insidehighered.com/news/2016/08/08/letter-publishers-group-adds-debate-over-sci-hub-and-librarians-who-study-it|title= Letter from publishers' group adds to debate over Sci-Hub and librarians who study it|date= 8 August 2016|website= Inside Higher Ed|access-date= 2016-08-29|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160814185208/https://www.insidehighered.com/news/2016/08/08/letter-publishers-group-adds-debate-over-sci-hub-and-librarians-who-study-it|archive-date= 14 August 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2016, [[Nature Publishing Group]] named Alexandra Elbakyan as one of the [[Nature's 10|ten people who most mattered]] in 2016.<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite journal|date=2016-12-22|title=Nature's 10|journal=Nature|volume=540|issue=7634|pages=507\u2013515|doi=10.1038/540507a|pmid=30905952|bibcode=2016Natur.540..507.|doi-access=free}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Russian and Mexican entomologists named a species of [[parasitoid wasp]] ''[[Idiogramma elbakyanae]]'' in reference to Sci-Hub's creator, Alexandra Elbakyan. The Russian and Mexican team said this was \"in honour of Alexandra Elbakyan (Kazakhstan/Russia), creator of the web-site Sci-Hub, in recognition of her contribution to making scientific knowledge available for all researchers.\"<ref name=Bookseller20170906/><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Khalaim|first1=Andrey I.|last2=Ru\u00edz-Cancino |first2=Enrique|title=Ichneumonidae (Hymenoptera) associated with xyelid sawflies (Hymenoptera, Xyelidae) in Mexico |journal=Journal of Hymenoptera Research|date=31 August 2017|volume=58|pages=17\u201327|doi=10.3897/jhr.58.12919|doi-access=free}}</ref> Elbakyan was offended by the naming, and subsequently blocked access to Sci-Hub's services in the Russian Federation.<ref name=Bookseller20170906>{{cite news|url=https://www.thebookseller.com/news/elbakyan-pulls-sci-hub-russia-631281|title=Elbakyan pulls Sci-Hub from Russia|work=The Bookseller|date=6 September 2017|first=Benedicte|last=Page|access-date=2018-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190110190320/https://www.thebookseller.com/news/elbakyan-pulls-sci-hub-russia-631281|archive-date=10 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The Russian entomologist responsible for naming the wasp stated that he supports Sci-Hub, and that in any event, the naming was not an insult, in particular because [[parasitoid]]s are closer to [[predator]]s than to [[parasite]]s.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kotlyar|first1=Pavel|title=\u0412\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0441\u044c \u0432 \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0435\u043c \u0434\u0435\u0440\u044c\u043c\u0435 \u0441\u0430\u043c\u0438|url=https://www.gazeta.ru/science/2017/09/05_a_10875050.shtml|publisher=[[Gazeta.ru]]|accessdate=21 October 2017|language=ru|date=5 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171119234104/https://www.gazeta.ru/science/2017/09/05_a_10875050.shtml|archive-date=19 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn response to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], a group of online archivists have used Sci-Hub for creating an archive of over 5000 articles about coronaviruses. They admitted that making the archive openly accessible was illegal, but considered it a moral imperative.<ref name=\"Bender 2020\"/>\n\n==See also==\n{{collist|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Library Genesis]]\n*[[Library.nu]]\n*[[Open access]]\n*[[ResearchGate]]\n*[[The Pirate Bay]]\n*[[Unpaywall]]\n*[[ICanHazPDF|#ICanHazPDF]]\n* [[Aaron Swartz#Open Access|Guerilla Open Access Manifesto]]\n}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"Bender 2020\">{{cite web | last=Bender | first=Maddie | title='It's a Moral Imperative:' Archivists Made a Directory of 5,000 Coronavirus Studies to Bypass Paywalls | website=Vice | date=2020-02-03 | url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/z3b3v5/archivists-are-bypassing-paywalls-to-share-studies-about-coronaviruses | access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* [http://openaccess.unt.edu/symposium/2016/info/transcript-and-translation-sci-hub-presentation Transcript and translation of \"Why Science is Better with Communism? The Case of Sci-Hub\"], a presentation by Alexandra Elbakyan at the University of North Texas Open Access Symposium 2016.\n* [http://www.stephenmclaughlin.net/sci-hub/McLaughlin_Sci-Hub-LibGen-Bib_3-2016.pdf \"Sci-Hub/LibGen in Blogs and the Media (PDF)\"] Stephen Reid McLaughlin, March 2016\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|sci-hub.tw/about}}\n* [http://vertsluisants.fr/index.php?article4/where-scihub-libgen-server-down List of online SciHub servers]\n\n{{Open navbox}}\n{{Intellectual property activism}}\n{{Academic publishing}}\n{{Tor hidden services}}\n{{File sharing}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n\n[[Category:Search engine software]]\n[[Category:Academic publishing]]\n[[Category:Tor onion services]]\n[[Category:File sharing communities]]\n[[Category:Intellectual property activism]]\n[[Category:Open access projects]]\n[[Category:Internet properties established in 2011]]\n", "name_user": "Cheater no1", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReception:link to \"moral imperative\"", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sci-Hub"}
{"title_page": "Peg o' My Heart (1922 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|1922 film}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Peg o' My Heart\n| image          = Peg O' My Heart 1922 poster.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[King Vidor]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = [[J. Hartley Manners]]<br>[[Mary O'Hara (author)|Mary O'Hara]]\n| starring       = [[Laurette Taylor]]\n| cinematography = [[George Barnes (cinematographer)|George Barnes]]\n| editing        = \n| distributor    = [[Metro Pictures]]\n| released       = {{film date|1922|12|18}}\n| runtime        = 80 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = Silent (English [[intertitle]]s)\n}}\n[[File:Laurette Taylor in Peg o' My Heart.jpg|right|thumb|Lionel Belmore, Laurette Taylor and Russell Simpson in ''Peg o' My Heart''.]]\n\n'''''Peg o' My Heart''''' is a 1922 American [[silent film|silent]] [[drama film]] directed by [[King Vidor]] and starring [[Laurette Taylor]]. It is based on the 1912 play written by Taylor's husband  J. Hartley Manners. The play starred [[Laurette Taylor]] and famously ran a record number of performances on Broadway. Six reels of the original eight reels survive at the [[Library of Congress]].<ref name=\"silentera\">{{cite web |url=http://www.silentera.com/PSFL/data/P/PegOMyHeart1922.html|title=Progressive Silent Film List: ''Peg o' My Heart'' |accessdate=March 8, 2008|work=Silent Era}}</ref>\n\n==Proposed Paramount film==\nIn 1919 [[Famous Players-Lasky]] filmed a version of the play and it starred newcomer [[Wanda Hawley]]. However, because of legal issues with Laurette Taylor and her husband J. Hartley Manners -- ultimately decided in the [[United States Supreme Court]] case ''[[Manners v. Morosco]]'' -- the film was never released.<ref>Blum, Daniel (c. 1953), ''Pictorial History of the Silent Film'', p. 238.</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nAs described in a film publication,<ref>{{cite journal | editor1-last=Pardy |editor1-first=George T.  |title=Illustrated Screen Report: ''Peg o' My Heart'' |journal=Exhibitor's Trade Review |volume=13 |issue=4 |page=215 |publisher=Exhibitor's Trade Review, Inc. |location=East Stroudsberg, Pennsylvania |date=December 23, 1922 |url=https://archive.org/details/exhibitorst00newy |accessdate=April 29, 2014}}</ref> Margaret \"Peg\" O'Connell (Taylor), according to her uncle's will, is to be educated in England under the supervision of her aunt, Mrs. Chichester (Lewis). Upon her arrival from Ireland, she is looked down upon by the Chichester household for her lack of culture, and she vows never to become a lady. She meets Jerry, a young man from a neighboring estate, who becomes her friend. Then she discovers that he is Sir Gerald Adair (Hamilton) and rebels at the deception he has been conducting. She also finds out that the only reason her aunt is keeping her is because of compensation from the will. Peg leaves to return home, but finds that she is in love with Gerald. Gerald follows her and proposes.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Laurette Taylor]] as Margaret O'Connell\n* [[Mahlon Hamilton]] as Sir Gerald Adair\n* [[Russell Simpson (actor)|Russell Simpson]] as Jim O'Connell\n* [[Ethel Grey Terry]] as Ethel Chichester\n* [[Nigel Barrie]] as Charistian Brent\n* [[Lionel Belmore]] as Hawks\n* [[Vera Lewis]] as Mrs. Chichester\n* [[Fred Huntley]] as Jarvis, the butler (as Fred Huntly)\n\n==Preservation status==\n*Copies exist at Cinematheque Royale de Belgique Brussels, Museum of Modern Art New York, Cinematheque Quebecoise, Montreal and Filmoteca Espanola, Madrid.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://memory.loc.gov/diglib/ihas/loc.mbrs.sfdb.780/default.html|title=Peg O' My Heart|date=October 29, 2017|website=Memory.loc.gov|accessdate=October 29, 2017}}</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20141225003106/http://www.thegreatstars.com/lost_film_wanted.htm Peg O'My Heart at TheGreatStars.com; Lost Films Wanted](Wayback Machine)..Retrieved July 21, 2018</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*{{IMDb title|0013488}}\n*[http://www.virtual-history.com/movie/film/6452/peg-o-my-heart ''Peg o' My Heart''] at Virtual History\n\n{{King Vidor}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Peg O My Heart}}\n[[Category:1922 films]]\n[[Category:1922 drama films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American drama films]]\n[[Category:American silent feature films]]\n[[Category:American black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by King Vidor]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by J. Hartley Manners]]\n[[Category:Metro Pictures films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1922 film}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Peg o' My Heart\n| image          = Peg O' My Heart 1922 poster.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[King Vidor]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = [[J. Hartley Manners]]<br>[[Mary O'Hara (author)|Mary O'Hara]]\n| starring       = [[Laurette Taylor]]\n| cinematography = [[George Barnes (cinematographer)|George Barnes]]\n| editing        = \n| distributor    = [[Metro Pictures]]\n| released       = {{film date|1922|12|18}}\n| runtime        = 80 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = Silent (English [[intertitle]]s)\n}}\n[[File:Laurette Taylor in Peg o' My Heart.jpg|right|thumb|Lionel Belmore, Laurette Taylor and Russell Simpson in ''Peg o' My Heart''.]]\n\n'''''Peg o' My Heart''''' is a 1922 American [[silent film|silent]] [[drama film]] directed by [[King Vidor]] and starring [[Laurette Taylor]]. It is based on the 1912 play written by Taylor's husband  J. Hartley Manners. The play starred [[Laurette Taylor]] and famously ran a record number of performances on Broadway. Six reels of the original eight reels survive at the [[Library of Congress]].<ref name=\"silentera\">{{cite web |url=http://www.silentera.com/PSFL/data/P/PegOMyHeart1922.html|title=Progressive Silent Film List: ''Peg o' My Heart'' |accessdate=March 8, 2008|work=Silent Era}}</ref>\n\n==Proposed Paramount film==\nIn 1919 [[Famous Players-Lasky]] filmed a version of the play and it starred newcomer [[Wanda Hawley]]. However, because of legal issues with Laurette Taylor and her husband J. Hartley Manners -- ultimately decided in the [[United States Supreme Court]] case ''[[Manners v. Morosco]]'' -- the film was never released.<ref>Blum, Daniel (c. 1953), ''Pictorial History of the Silent Film'', p. 238.</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nAs described in a film publication,<ref>{{cite journal | editor1-last=Pardy |editor1-first=George T.  |title=Illustrated Screen Report: ''Peg o' My Heart'' |journal=Exhibitor's Trade Review |volume=13 |issue=4 |page=215 |publisher=Exhibitor's Trade Review, Inc. |location=East Stroudsberg, Pennsylvania |date=December 23, 1922 |url=https://archive.org/details/exhibitorst00newy |accessdate=April 29, 2014}}</ref> Margaret \"Peg\" O'Connell (Taylor), according to her uncle's will, is to be educated in England under the supervision of her aunt, Mrs. Chichester (Lewis). Upon her arrival from Ireland, she is looked down upon by the Chichester household for her lack of culture, and she vows never to become a lady. She meets Jerry, a young man from a neighboring estate, who becomes her friend. Then she discovers that he is Sir Gerald Adair (Hamilton) and rebels at the deception he has been conducting. She also finds out that the only reason her aunt is keeping her is because of compensation from the will. Peg leaves to return home, but finds that she is in love with Gerald. Gerald follows her and proposes.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Laurette Taylor]] as Margaret O'Connell\n* [[Mahlon Hamilton]] as Sir Gerald Adair\n* [[Russell Simpson (actor)|Russell Simpson]] as Jim O'Connell\n* [[Ethel Grey Terry]] as Ethel Chichester\n* [[Nigel Barrie]] as Charistian Brent\n* [[Lionel Belmore]] as Hawks\n* [[Vera Lewis]] as Mrs. Chichester\n* [[Fred Huntley]] as Jarvis, the butler (as Fred Huntly)\n\n==Preservation status==\n*Copies exist at Cinematheque Royale de Belgique Brussels, Museum of Modern Art New York, Cinematheque Quebecoise, Montreal and Filmoteca Espanola, Madrid.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://memory.loc.gov/diglib/ihas/loc.mbrs.sfdb.780/default.html|title=Peg O' My Heart|date=October 29, 2017|website=Memory.loc.gov|accessdate=October 29, 2017}}</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20141225003106/http://www.thegreatstars.com/lost_film_wanted.htm Peg O'My Heart at TheGreatStars.com; Lost Films Wanted](Wayback Machine)..Retrieved July 21, 2018</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*{{IMDb title|0013488}}\n*[http://www.virtual-history.com/movie/film/6452/peg-o-my-heart ''Peg o' My Heart''] at Virtual History\n\n{{King Vidor}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Peg O My Heart}}\n[[Category:1922 films]]\n[[Category:1922 drama films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American drama films]]\n[[Category:American silent feature films]]\n[[Category:American black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by King Vidor]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by J. Hartley Manners]]\n[[Category:Metro Pictures films]]\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peg_o%27_My_Heart_(1922_film)"}
{"title_page": "Norman Davidson (biochemist)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name              = Professor Norman Davidson\n| birth_name       = James Norman Davidson\n| native_name_lang  = \n| image             = <!--(as myimage.jpg, no 'File:')-->\n| image_size        = \n| alt               = \n| caption           = \n| birth_date        =  {{Birth date|df=y|1911|3|5}}\n| birth_place       = \n| death_date        = {{Death date and age|df=y|1972|9|11|1911|3|5}}\n| death_place       = \n| resting_place     = \n| resting_place_coordinates = <!--\n                      {{Coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} -->\n| other_names       = \n| residence         = \n| citizenship       = \n| nationality       = \n| fields            = [[Biochemistry]]\n| workplaces        = [[University of Aberdeen]]<br>[[University of St Andrews]]<ref name=\"frs\"/><br>[[University of Glasgow]]\n| alma_mater        = [[University of Edinburgh]]<ref name=\"frs\"/>\n| thesis_title      = \n| thesis_url        = \n| thesis_year       = \n| doctoral_advisor  = \n| academic_advisors = \n| doctoral_students = \n| notable_students  = \n| known_for         = \n| author_abbrev_bot = \n| author_abbrev_zoo = \n| influences        = \n| influenced        = \n| awards            = [[Fellow of the Royal Society]]<br>[[Royal Society of Edinburgh|FRSE]]\n| signature         = <!--(filename only)-->\n| signature_alt     = \n| website           = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} -->\n| footnotes         = \n| spouse            = \n| children          = \n}}\n\n'''James Norman Davidson''' [[CBE]] [[President of the Royal Society of Edinburgh|PRSE]] [[Fellow of the Royal Society of London|FRS]] (5 March 1911 \u2013 11 September 1972) was a Scottish [[biochemist]], pioneer [[molecular biologist]] and textbook author. The '''Davidson Building''' at [[Glasgow University]] is named for him.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.universitystory.gla.ac.uk/biography/?id=WH0157&type=P |title = University of Glasgow :: Story :: Biography of Norman Davidson}}</ref>\n\n==Life==\nHe was the only child of James Davidson [[FRSE]] FSA (1873-1956) a lawyer, Treasurer of the [[Carnegie Trust for the Universities of Scotland]], originally from Aberdeenshire, and his wife, Wilhelmina Ibberson Foote. He was born in [[Edinburgh]] on 5 March 1911 and lived in the family home of 30 Bruntsfield Gardens in the south of the city.<ref>Edinburgh and Leith Post Office Directory 1910-11</ref> He was educated locally, at [[George Watson's College]], where he was dux.<ref name=\"royalsoced.org.uk\">https://www.royalsoced.org.uk/cms/files/fellows/biographical_index/fells_indexp1.pdf</ref><ref name=\"ReferenceA\">Oxford Dictionary of National Biography: Norman Davidson</ref>\n\nHe then studied Medicine and Organic Chemistry at the [[University of Edinburgh]] graduating [[Bachelor of Science|BSc]] degree in 1934,<ref name=\"frs\">{{cite journal |title=James Norman Davidson, 1911-1972 |journal=Biographical Memoirs of Fellows of the Royal Society |date=January 1997 |volume=19 |pages=280\u2013303 |doi=10.1098/rsbm.1973.0011 |doi-access=free }}</ref> MB ChB in 1937, MD in 1939 and gained a D.Sc. with a thesis on Biochemical investigations on cellular proliferation from the University of Edinburgh in 1945.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Davidson|first=J. Norman|date=1945|title=Biochemical investigations on cellular proliferation|url=https://era.ed.ac.uk/handle/1842/32509|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn 1937/38 he studied under [[Otto Heinrich Warburg]] in Berlin-Dahlem, in the turbulent pre-war days. He returned to [[Scotland]] in autumn of 1938 to begin lecturing in Biochemistry at [[St Andrews University]]. From 1940 to 45 he was Senior Lecturer in Biochemistry at [[Aberdeen University]].<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n\nIn 1941 he was elected a Fellow of the [[Royal Society of Edinburgh]]. His proposers were [[James Kendall (chemist)|James P Kendall]], [[Ernest Cruickshank]], [[Robert Campbell Garry]], and [[Anderson Gray M'Kendrick]].<ref name=\"royalsoced.org.uk\"/> He was Secretary to the society 1949-1954, Vice President 1955-58 and served two terms as President from 1958\u201359 and 1964-67.<ref>[http://www.gla.ac.uk/services/archives/news/dunaskinnews200207/jamesnormandavidson1911-72professorofbiochemistry1947-72/ James Norman Davidson (1911-72), Professor of Biochemistry, 1947-72, University of Glasgow]</ref> He was elected as a Fellow of the Royal Society in 1960.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=4ys1AAAAIBAJ&pg=2537%2C3442240 |title=Glasgow Professor elected FRS |work=The Glasgow Herald |date=25 March 1960 |page=14 |accessdate=14 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nDavidson was Professor of Biochemistry at the [[University of Glasgow]] from 1947 to 1972. in 1949 he brought in [[Martin Smellie]] as his assistant.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.universitystory.gla.ac.uk/biography/?id=WH2061&type=P |title = University of Glasgow :: Story :: Biography of Martin Smellie}}</ref> \n\nIn 1958 he succeeded [[George M. Wishart]] as the Gardiner Professor of Phsiology at Glasgow University.<ref>{{cite journal |title=University of Glasgow: Chair of Physiological Chemistry |journal=Nature |date=1 July 1947 |volume=160 |issue=4054 |pages=51 |doi=10.1038/160051c0 |bibcode=1947Natur.160S..51. |doi-access=free }}</ref>\n\nHe was made a Commander of the Order of the British Empire (CBE) in 1967.\n\nHe died of a heart attack in [[Bearsden]] in [[Glasgow]] on 11 September 1972.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.gla.ac.uk/services/archives/news/dunaskinnews200207/jamesnormandavidson1911-72professorofbiochemistry1947-72/ | title=University of Glasgow - MyGlasgow - Archive Services - News - Dunaskin News 2002/07 - James Norman Davidson (1911-72), Professor of Biochemistry, 1947-72}}</ref>\n\n==Publications==\n\n*''The Biochemistry of Nucleic Acids'' (1950)\n\n==Family==\n\nIn 1938 he married Morag McLeod (now Dr Morag Davidson). Their children included [[Rona McLeod MacKie]] [[FRSE]] (b.1940) and [[Ailsa Morag Campbell]] [[FRSE]] (b.1943).<ref name=\"royalsoced.org.uk\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Davidson, J. Norman}}\n[[Category:1911 births]]\n[[Category:1972 deaths]]\n[[Category:Scottish biologists]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Edinburgh]]\n[[Category:Academics of the University of Aberdeen]]\n[[Category:Academics of the University of Dundee]]\n[[Category:Academics of the University of Glasgow]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal Society]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Royal Society of Edinburgh]]\n[[Category:Commanders of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:Scottish biochemists]]\n[[Category:British molecular biologists]]\n[[Category:People educated at George Watson's College]]\n[[Category:People from Edinburgh]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal College of Physicians and Surgeons of Glasgow]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal College of Physicians of Edinburgh]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name              = Professor Norman Davidson\n| birth_name       = James Norman Davidson\n| native_name_lang  = \n| image             = <!--(as myimage.jpg, no 'File:')-->\n| image_size        = \n| alt               = \n| caption           = \n| birth_date        =  {{Birth date|df=y|1911|3|5}}\n| birth_place       = \n| death_date        = {{Death date and age|df=y|1972|9|11|1911|3|5}}\n| death_place       = \n| resting_place     = \n| resting_place_coordinates = <!--\n                      {{Coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} -->\n| other_names       = \n| residence         = \n| citizenship       = \n| nationality       = \n| fields            = [[Biochemistry]]\n| workplaces        = [[University of Aberdeen]]<br>[[University of St Andrews]]<ref name=\"frs\"/><br>[[University of Glasgow]]\n| alma_mater        = [[University of Edinburgh]]<ref name=\"frs\"/>\n| thesis_title      = \n| thesis_url        = \n| thesis_year       = \n| doctoral_advisor  = \n| academic_advisors = \n| doctoral_students = \n| notable_students  = \n| known_for         = \n| author_abbrev_bot = \n| author_abbrev_zoo = \n| influences        = \n| influenced        = \n| awards            = [[Fellow of the Royal Society]]<br>[[Royal Society of Edinburgh|FRSE]]\n| signature         = <!--(filename only)-->\n| signature_alt     = \n| website           = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} -->\n| footnotes         = \n| spouse            = \n| children          = \n}}\n\n'''James Norman Davidson''' [[CBE]] [[President of the Royal Society of Edinburgh|PRSE]] [[Fellow of the Royal Society of London|FRS]] (5 March 1911 \u2013 11 September 1972) was a Scottish [[biochemist]], pioneer [[molecular biologist]] and textbook author. The '''Davidson Building''' at [[Glasgow University]] is named for him.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.universitystory.gla.ac.uk/biography/?id=WH0157&type=P |title = University of Glasgow :: Story :: Biography of Norman Davidson}}</ref>\n\n==Life==\nHe was the only child of James Davidson [[FRSE]] FSA (1873-1956) a lawyer, Treasurer of the [[Carnegie Trust for the Universities of Scotland]], originally from Aberdeenshire, and his wife, Wilhelmina Ibberson Foote. He was born in [[Edinburgh]] on 5 March 1911 and lived in the family home of 30 Bruntsfield Gardens in the south of the city.<ref>Edinburgh and Leith Post Office Directory 1910-11</ref> He was educated locally, at [[George Watson's College]], where he was dux.<ref name=\"royalsoced.org.uk\">https://www.royalsoced.org.uk/cms/files/fellows/biographical_index/fells_indexp1.pdf</ref><ref name=\"ReferenceA\">Oxford Dictionary of National Biography: Norman Davidson</ref>\n\nHe then studied Medicine and Organic Chemistry at the [[University of Edinburgh]] graduating [[Bachelor of Science|BSc]] degree in 1934,<ref name=\"frs\">{{cite journal |title=James Norman Davidson, 1911-1972 |journal=Biographical Memoirs of Fellows of the Royal Society |date=January 1997 |volume=19 |pages=280\u2013303 |doi=10.1098/rsbm.1973.0011 |doi-access=free }}</ref> MB ChB in 1937, MD in 1939 and gained a D.Sc. with a thesis on Biochemical investigations on cellular proliferation from the University of Edinburgh in 1945.\n\nIn 1937/38 he studied under [[Otto Heinrich Warburg]] in Berlin-Dahlem, in the turbulent pre-war days. He returned to [[Scotland]] in autumn of 1938 to begin lecturing in Biochemistry at [[St Andrews University]]. From 1940 to 45 he was Senior Lecturer in Biochemistry at [[Aberdeen University]].<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n\nIn 1941 he was elected a Fellow of the [[Royal Society of Edinburgh]]. His proposers were [[James Kendall (chemist)|James P Kendall]], [[Ernest Cruickshank]], [[Robert Campbell Garry]], and [[Anderson Gray M'Kendrick]].<ref name=\"royalsoced.org.uk\"/> He was Secretary to the society 1949-1954, Vice President 1955-58 and served two terms as President from 1958\u201359 and 1964-67.<ref>[http://www.gla.ac.uk/services/archives/news/dunaskinnews200207/jamesnormandavidson1911-72professorofbiochemistry1947-72/ James Norman Davidson (1911-72), Professor of Biochemistry, 1947-72, University of Glasgow]</ref> He was elected as a Fellow of the Royal Society in 1960.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=4ys1AAAAIBAJ&pg=2537%2C3442240 |title=Glasgow Professor elected FRS |work=The Glasgow Herald |date=25 March 1960 |page=14 |accessdate=14 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nDavidson was Professor of Biochemistry at the [[University of Glasgow]] from 1947 to 1972. in 1949 he brought in [[Martin Smellie]] as his assistant.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.universitystory.gla.ac.uk/biography/?id=WH2061&type=P |title = University of Glasgow :: Story :: Biography of Martin Smellie}}</ref> \n\nIn 1958 he succeeded [[George M. Wishart]] as the Gardiner Professor of Phsiology at Glasgow University.<ref>{{cite journal |title=University of Glasgow: Chair of Physiological Chemistry |journal=Nature |date=1 July 1947 |volume=160 |issue=4054 |pages=51 |doi=10.1038/160051c0 |bibcode=1947Natur.160S..51. |doi-access=free }}</ref>\n\nHe was made a Commander of the Order of the British Empire (CBE) in 1967.\n\nHe died of a heart attack in [[Bearsden]] in [[Glasgow]] on 11 September 1972.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.gla.ac.uk/services/archives/news/dunaskinnews200207/jamesnormandavidson1911-72professorofbiochemistry1947-72/ | title=University of Glasgow - MyGlasgow - Archive Services - News - Dunaskin News 2002/07 - James Norman Davidson (1911-72), Professor of Biochemistry, 1947-72}}</ref>\n\n==Publications==\n\n*''The Biochemistry of Nucleic Acids'' (1950)\n\n==Family==\n\nIn 1938 he married Morag McLeod (now Dr Morag Davidson). Their children included [[Rona McLeod MacKie]] [[FRSE]] (b.1940) and [[Ailsa Morag Campbell]] [[FRSE]] (b.1943).<ref name=\"royalsoced.org.uk\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Davidson, J. Norman}}\n[[Category:1911 births]]\n[[Category:1972 deaths]]\n[[Category:Scottish biologists]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Edinburgh]]\n[[Category:Academics of the University of Aberdeen]]\n[[Category:Academics of the University of Dundee]]\n[[Category:Academics of the University of Glasgow]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal Society]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Royal Society of Edinburgh]]\n[[Category:Commanders of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:Scottish biochemists]]\n[[Category:British molecular biologists]]\n[[Category:People educated at George Watson's College]]\n[[Category:People from Edinburgh]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal College of Physicians and Surgeons of Glasgow]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal College of Physicians of Edinburgh]]\n", "name_user": "Bellgraham66", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added link to author's thesis", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norman_Davidson_(biochemist)"}
